1	devforum	45863	About the Scripting Support category	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/45863	Scripting	Guidelines and requirements for posting help requests in the Scripting Support category.	\N	f	beginner	{}	{}	f	An AI assistant could help users by pre-formatting their code with triple backticks and ensuring they provide the three required answers (objective, issue, tried solutions) before they submit their post.	88770	1203	1	2017-07-28 20:23:07.029	2026-01-08 17:05:12.32278	{"views": 88770, "content": " This is a support category for help on everything related to  scripting  on the Roblox platform, from extremely basic to even the most technical of issues. \\n Make sure to search the forum before creating a new topic, many beginner / learning resources have already been created, or maybe your problem has already been solved by someone else. \\n If you’re looking to show off your project and get opinions and feedback, please use         Creations Feedback   instead! \\n Please do not post bug reports or feature requests here! Always pick the right category for your topic! \\n   How should I write my topic? \\n You can write your topic however you want, but you need to answer these questions: \\n \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  Keep it simple and clear! \\n \\n \\n  What is the issue?  Include screenshots / videos if possible! \\n \\n \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Did you look for solutions on the  Creator Hub ? \\n \\n \\n After that, you should include more details if you have any. Try to make your topic as descriptive as possible, so that it’s easier for people to help you! \\n Please do not post screenshots of code.  Instead, format blocks of code by wrapping it in triple backticks (`) like this: \\n \\n ``` \\n-- Code \\n``` \\n \\n Please do not ask people to write entire scripts or design entire systems for you. If you can’t answer the three questions above, you should probably pick a different category. \\n   Who can post here? \\n \\n All members of the forum can create topics in this category and reply to topics. \\n Everyone can read all the contents in this category, even when not logged in. \\n \\n   Got an issue to post, but you’re not a forum member yet? \\n See  this post  for more information on how to contribute. ", "upvotes": 1203, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2017-07-28T20:23:07.029Z"}
2	devforum	4232004	How do Roblox animations work?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4232004	Animation	Understanding the internal mechanics of Roblox animations, including how KeyframeSequences are processed, how Pose data affects Motor6Ds via the Transform property, and why Welds cannot be animated.	KeyframeSequences contain Keyframe instances that group Pose objects. Each Pose contains CFrame data that is applied to the 'Transform' property of a Motor6D. During playback, the Animator interpolates (blends) between the CFrames of the two nearest Keyframes based on the AnimationTrack's TimePosition. Welds cannot be animated because they lack the Transform property; only Motor6Ds, AnimationConstraints, and Bones are supported. The Animator system blends multiple playing tracks based on priority and weight.	t	intermediate	{Keyframe,KeyframeSequence,Motor6D,Pose,Animator,AnimationTrack,Weld,AnimationConstraint,Bone,CFrame}	{}	t	A coding agent could help by generating scripts to programmatically build KeyframeSequences, or by creating custom procedural animation controllers that manipulate the Motor6D.Transform property directly based on math functions.	64	0	3	2026-01-08 18:14:19.498	2026-01-08 17:05:12.906615	{"views": 64, "content": " \\n Hi, \\nI am making a roblox animation plugin. \\n \\n I’m trying to understand how Roblox animations work beyond just creating and playing them in Studio. \\n Could someone explain: \\n \\n How  Keyframes / KeyframeSequences  are processed when an animation plays \\n How animations affect  Motor6Ds , and why they don’t seem to affect  Welds  \\n How the  Animator / AnimationTrack  system applies pose data to a rig \\n \\n I already know how to make and play animations, but I want a clearer understanding of what’s happening behind the scenes. \\n \\n I did read the roblox docs but didnt understand anything. \\n \\n Thanks! ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-08T18:14:19.498Z"}
3	devforum	4228881	Made an ability that teleports another user, they disappear for a second and then come back immediately	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4228881	Networking	Teleporting another player's character via a server-side script causes the target to immediately snap back or rubberband to their original position, likely due to client-side physics ownership overriding the server change.	\N	f	intermediate	{PivotTo,CFrame,Vector3,Humanoid,HumanoidRootPart,GetAttribute,GetChildren}	{}	t	A coding agent could identify that the target character's NetworkOwnership is likely held by the other player's client. It could suggest temporarily setting the NetworkOwner to nil (the server) before the teleport or using a RemoteEvent to request the client to perform the teleport locally to ensure physics consistency.	82	0	10	2026-01-08 01:59:04.955	2026-01-08 17:05:14.521427	{"views": 82, "content": " So I am making an ability that during a certain step of it on the server side, it teleports another player that isn’t the user 5000 studs upwards for positioning reasons. Although it works when I manually make the victim myself, as in my own character, when I make it actually another user as intended they vanish, presumably to the correct position (although we have no proof it was the correct position just making it clear, so take it with a grain of salt), but then to appear back a frame later. \\n This is the part of my code that does the positioning, specifically at the end: \\n  local function CreateObby(character:Model)\\n\\tlocal humanoid:Humanoid = character:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\")\\n\\tlocal humanoidRootPart:BasePart = character:FindFirstChild(\\"HumanoidRootPart\\")\\n\\tlocal obbyLevel = humanoid:GetAttribute(\\"BloxxerGrabObbyLevel\\")\\n\\tlocal startPosition = Vector3.new(humanoidRootPart.Position.X,humanoidRootPart.Position.Y + 5000, humanoidRootPart.Position.Z)\\n\\tlocal nextPosition = CFrame.new(startPosition)\\n\\tlocal obbySelection = easyObbies:GetChildren()\\n\\tfor i = 0, 3 + obbyLevel, 1 do\\n\\t\\tlocal selectedObby:Model = obbySelection[math.random(1,#obbySelection)]:Clone()\\n\\t\\tselectedObby:PivotTo(nextPosition)\\n\\t\\tselectedObby.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\tnextPosition = selectedObby.ObbyEnd.CFrame\\n\\tend\\n\\tlocal newObbyComplete = obbyComplete:Clone()\\n\\tobbyComplete.CFrame = nextPosition\\n\\tnewObbyComplete.Parent = workspace\\n\\thumanoidRootPart.CFrame = CFrame.new(startPosition + Vector3.new(0,5,0))\\nend\\n  \\n I have verified that the start position itself should be correct so its something else. \\n Here is a video of this happening: \\n              \\n ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 10, "created_at": "2026-01-08T01:59:04.955Z"}
