5	devforum	4224784	How Can I Add Delta Time To Make Framerates The Same?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4224784	Physics	Implementing frame-rate independent spring physics where higher framerates cause unstable or 'harsh' simulation behavior due to incorrect delta time integration.	\N	f	intermediate	{RunService.PreSimulation}	{}	t	Provide a robust integration method for spring physics, such as semi-implicit Euler or an analytic solution, ensuring delta time is applied consistently to both velocity and position calculations.	93	2	5	2026-01-07 08:19:21.134	2026-01-08 17:05:18.836023	{"views": 93, "content": " Hello, I have been following a tutorial on how to implement a physics-simulated spring for my game, but was unable to sync movements across multiple framerates. I have researched on how to do this but have had no luck in my attempts, as I am fairly new to using deltatime. \\n  function Spring:Simulate(delta : number)\\n\\tlocal time = delta * 60\\n\\t\\n\\tself.velocity += (-self.tension * (self.position - self.target)) - (self.dampening * self.velocity) * time\\n\\tself.position += self.velocity\\nend\\n  \\n Any help would be appreciated! ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-07T08:19:21.134Z"}
6	devforum	4157666	Magnitude breaks after a few minutes of testing	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4157666	Scripting	NPC hit range calculations using magnitude become inconsistent and laggy after several minutes of gameplay, likely due to performance degradation.	\N	f	intermediate	{RunService,PathfindingService,CollectionService,IKControl,Debris,Humanoid,tick}	{}	t	Replace the custom C_WAIT function, which uses a high-CPU busy-wait loop (repeat until tick()), with task.wait(). Additionally, investigate if event connections are being properly cleaned up when NPCs are destroyed to prevent memory leaks.	157	3	13	2025-12-17 06:06:59.693	2026-01-08 17:05:23.019653	{"views": 157, "content": " I’m making a decaying winter npc testing type of game and I’ve been having this bug for a while. So I use magnitude to calculate how far an npc can hit but every few minutes the npc begins to lag a bit then the magnitude calculation will break, and will cause the npc not to melee in the same range as it was before the problem starts happening. \\n Npc Module Shortened \\n  local PathfindModule = require(script.Parent.NPC_PathFind)\\nlocal CombatModule = require(script.Parent.NPC_Combat)\\nlocal NPC = {}\\nlocal effectModule = require(game.ReplicatedStorage.gunstats.EffectStats)\\nNPC.__index = NPC\\nlocal events = game.ReplicatedStorage.Events\\n\\nlocal cosmetics = game.ReplicatedStorage.Cosmetics\\n\\nlocal Debris = game:GetService(\\"Debris\\")\\n\\nlocal C_WAIT = function(dt)\\n\\tdt = dt or 1/60\\n\\tlocal now = tick()\\n\\trepeat\\n\\t\\tgame:GetService('RunService').Heartbeat:Wait() \\n\\tuntil tick() - now &gt;= dt\\nend\\n\\nlocal MAIN = require(script.Parent.Main)\\n\\nNPC.CURRENTNPCS = {}\\n\\nNPC.Faction = 2\\n\\nlocal Dialogues = require(script.Parent.NPC_Dialogue)\\n\\nfunction NPC:CreateNPC(NPCMODEL : Model,Time : number,Range : number,turnspeed : number,faction:number,speed: number,attackplrs)\\n\\tlocal self = setmetatable({},NPC)\\n\\tself.NPC = NPCMODEL\\n\\tprint(NPC.CURRENTNPCS)\\n\\tself.ThirdMain = {}\\n\\tself.MoveTime = Time\\n\\tif not speed then\\n\\t\\tself.speed = 1\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tself.speed = speed\\n\\tend\\n\\tself.Range = Range\\n\\tself.Turned = false\\n\\tself.Targets = {}\\n\\tself.Target = nil\\n\\tself.CANSEE = false\\n\\tself.Crouching = false\\n\\tself.Pathing = false\\n\\tself.Tick = tick()\\n\\tself.CurrentAttack = nil\\n\\tif self.NPC:FindFirstChild(\\"AttackPlayers\\") then\\n\\t\\tself.AttackPlayers = true\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tself.AttackPlayers = false\\n\\tend\\n\\tself.Warning = 0\\n\\tself.Path = game:GetService(\\"PathfindingService\\"):CreatePath(PathfindModule.ReturnPathParams())\\n\\tself.Root = self.NPC.PrimaryPart\\n\\tself.Head = self.NPC.Head\\n\\tself.OGHEADC0 = self.NPC.Torso.Neck.C0\\n\\tself.Ignore = {self.NPC,workspace.Terrain}\\n\\tself.Weapon = nil\\n\\tself.NPCGOAL = nil\\n\\tself.pathFailCount = 0 \\n\\tself.Ping =0\\n\\tself", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2025-12-17T06:06:59.693Z"}
