ig (a Duck) uses Motor6Ds for animation. I want to dynamically change the “Hat” accessory by updating its  MeshId  and  TextureId  via a script when the player equips a new skin. The Hat should continue to animate (bob/tilt) along with the head/beak just like the default hat does. \\n   What is the issue? \\n The default hat animates perfectly (Screenshot 1). However, as soon as my script changes the  MeshId  of the Hat part (using  ApplyMesh  or manual property assignment),  the Hat stops animating . (Screenshot 3, the one below) \\n         image  778×800 45.6 KB         \\n It seems like the AnimationTrack no longer “recognizes” the part once the MeshId changes, causing the Hat to freeze in place relative to the RootPart, even though it is still named “Ha", "upvotes": 0, "category": "building-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-12-06T16:21:51.649Z"}
