91	devforum	4227047	I need help with mortor6ds for a camera system thing	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4227047	Scripting	Motor6D camera tracking fails when the model is rotated because look-at calculations are done in world space instead of object space, causing mirrored or incorrect movement.	Convert the world-space target CFrame into the base part's local space using CFrame:ToObjectSpace() before applying it to the Motor6D.C0 property, and use RunService.Heartbeat for frame-rate independent updates.	t	intermediate	{TweenService,Players,RunService,CFrame,Motor6D,RunService.Heartbeat,CFrame:ToObjectSpace}	{}	t	An automated tool could detect when a developer is assigning world-space CFrame calculations directly to Motor6D properties like C0 or C1 without using ToObjectSpace, and suggest the appropriate transformation logic.	29	1	2	2026-01-07 20:42:07.238	2026-01-08 17:06:58.51374	{"views": 29, "content": " so when the model is untouched the camera is able to look at the player. but when I rotate the camera 90 to 180 degrees the camera doesn’t track the player correctly when you look at it from the front and still tried to track the player as if it wasn’t rotated. is there a way to make it work regardless of the models rotation \\n sadly it’s not letting me provide a video so I’ll use screenshots: \\n zero rotation: \\n         image  355×534 38.5 KB         \\n180 rotation: (the camera will look but mirrored) \\n         image  471×579 49.2 KB         \\n this is the entire script at the moment: \\n  local tweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\nlocal players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\n\\nlocal tweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(.8,Enum.EasingStyle.Quad,Enum.EasingDirection.Out)\\n\\nlocal s = script.Parent\\nlocal mainCameraHead = s.MainCameraHead.MainCameraHead\\nlocal yAxis = s.Arm.SecondXaxis.YAxis\\nlocal xAxis = s.Arm.ArmContainer.XAxis\\n\\nlocal LookAtPart\\n\\nlocal function FindClosestPlayer()\\n\\tfor _, v in players:GetPlayers() do\\n\\t\\tlocal Character = v.Character\\n\\n\\t\\tif Character then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Head = Character:WaitForChild(\\"Head\\")\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tif not LookAtPart then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tLookAtPart = Head\\n\\t\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif (mainCameraHead.Position - LookAtPart.Position).Magnitude &gt; (mainCameraHead.Position - Head.Position).Magnitude then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tLookAtPart = Head\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nwhile true do\\n\\tif LookAtPart then\\n\\t\\tlocal CameraDirectionH = CFrame.new(mainCameraHead.Position,LookAtPart.Position).RightVector\\n\\t\\tlocal CameraDirectionV = CFrame.new(mainCameraHead.Position,LookAtPart.Position).UpVector * -1.5\\n\\t\\tlocal Goal = CFrame.new(-xAxis.C1.Y, _,_) * CFrame.Angles(0, math.asin(CameraDirectionH.z), 0)\\n\\t\\tlocal Goal2 = CFrame.new(_, -yAxis.C1.Y,_) * CFrame.Angles(math.asin(CameraDirectionV.z), 0, 0)\\n\\t\\tlocal Tween = tweenService:Create(xAxis, tweenInfo, {C1 = Goal}):Play()\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif CameraDirectionV.Y &lt; -1.2 then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Tween2 = tweenService:Create(yAxis, tweenInfo, {C1 = Goal2}):Play()\\n\\t\\t\\t--print(\\"breaking.\\")\\n", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-07T20:42:07.238Z"}
