92	devforum	4207467	How would I filter custom emojis	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4207467	Scripting	Custom chat emojis bypass the Roblox chat filter because the filter doesn't recognize emoji codes as the letters they represent, allowing users to spell prohibited words.	Map custom emoji codes (e.g., ':alpha_F:') to their literal text counterparts, run the translated string through TextService:FilterStringAsync, and compare the result. If the translated string is filtered (contains '#'), block or filter the original emoji string.	t	intermediate	{TextService,FilterStringAsync,GetNonChatStringForBroadcastAsync,string.gsub}	{}	t	A script could be generated to automatically create a dictionary mapping for all letter-based emoji assets and wrap the TextService filtering logic into a reusable utility function.	165	14	13	2026-01-02 05:10:44.989	2026-01-08 17:06:59.988751	{"views": 165, "content": " \\n cc  @Real_BenTheMiner   @PotatoCommuter  \\n \\n Hello. I am working on a custom chat system for a Roblox game, and it has the functionality to provide users with custom emojis. These work perfectly fine. \\n The game in question, however, is a transit game (Potato City Subway), and we are giving users access to route bullets for better roleplay and interactivity. \\n  \\n   example above \\n The issue is, this flies entirely over roblox’s filter, and inputting swears does not provoke the chat filter at all. We want to give a way for the chat filter to actually recognize these to check for swears and banned words, but we aren’t sure how. \\n It seems nobody else has encountered such a problem, and because we want a vast variety of emojis, a solution has been hard to come by. \\n Any help would be greatly appreciated with this problem. ", "upvotes": 14, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2026-01-02T05:10:44.989Z"}
