f CFrame.Angles() is given an X-value of -15, a Y-value of counter, and a Z-value of 0, the Part’s X-value will be -15, the Y-value will be equal to counter, and the Z-value will be equal to 0. But the video shows that doesn’t happen, which is why I’m confused. \\n I’m not setting the rotation directly using a Vector3 value, as I need to use CFrames to rotate models and cameras. I’m using a Part to show the unexpected rotational behavior. \\n What am I missing? Thank you for any help! ", "upvotes": 7, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 28, "created_at": "2025-12-30T21:14:38.288Z"}
122	devforum	4225060	How to increase size of part in only one direction	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4225060	Scripting	Resizing a BasePart (player's arm) expands it symmetrically from the center rather than growing in a single direction.	Adjust the part's Pivot Point or manually offset the CFrame position by half of the size change to compensate for the expansion in both directions.	f	beginner	{BasePart.Size,BasePart.PivotOffset,TweenService}	{}	t	Create a function that calculates the CFrame offset required when Tweening size, or set the WorldPivot/PivotOffset to the edge of the part before the size change occurs.	51	2	3	2026-01-07 11:00:15.32	2026-01-08 17:07:30.840983	{"views": 51, "content": " I’m making a game involving combat &amp; Powers, and one of them, “Rubber” stretches the player’s arms. \\n I want this to go only forwards, but it balances out the size increase and extends it backwards as well as forwards. \\n Is there any way to make it go forward only? \\n All help appreciated. \\n  if received == \\"RubberZ\\" then \\n\\t\\tfor _, x in plr.Character:GetChildren() do -- Ignore this for loop\\n\\t\\t\\tif x:IsA(\\"BasePart\\") then \\n\\t\\t\\t\\tx.CanCollide = false \\n\\t\\t\\t\\tx.Anchored = true \\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tplr.Character[\\"Right Arm\\"].Orientation = Vector3.new(90,0,0)\\n\\n\\t\\tAnimation.Size(plr.Character[\\"Right Arm\\"], 1,1,40) -- ! PROBLEM !\\nend\\n  \\n For more info, Animation.Size is a tween from a module script that changes size. ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-07T11:00:15.320Z"}
144	devforum	4223073	Other Clients sees you play emote 2 times, but in the Emote client you play it once	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4223073	Animation	Emote animations play twice on remote clients but only once on the local client due to redundant triggering between manual networking and Roblox's automatic animation replication.	\N	f	intermediate	{AnimationTrack:Play,AnimationTrack:Stop,Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter,RemoteEvent:FireServer,Instance:SetAttribute,AnimationTrack.Ended,task.spawn,task.wait}	{}	t	Refactor the logic to account for Roblox's built-in animation replication. If the animator is inside the player character, calling Play() on the client replicates to others automatically; the script should avoid manually firing a RemoteEvent that tells other clients to Play() the same animation track.	27	2	2	2026-01-06 20:54:02.902	2026-01-08 17:08:09.24334	{"views": 27, "content": " hi, im making emotes for my game, and i change it to client, basicly \\nserver shoots a string value, client process the value, \\nplays emotes. \\n simple right??? \\nbut theres a problem, because is client, i have to check who is doing the emote, specially if i want to use remote events, wich is important too. \\nnow i fixed that ofc, but i notice that other clients sees you playing the emote 2 times, but the client that is doing the emote, just did it once. \\nlike it says on the tittle. \\n so im confused of how i solved this?: \\n heres the function that plays the animation: \\n  function module.playEmote(char: Model, emoteName: string)\\n\\tlocal data = EmoteCache[char]\\n\\tif not data then return end\\n\\tlocal plr = Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(char)\\n\\tlocal track = data.Tracks[emoteName]\\n\\tif not track then\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"Emote not preloaded:\\", emoteName)\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\tlocal Anbimation = data.AnimationsC[emoteName]\\n\\tif not Anbimation then\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"Emote Not Animation:\\", emoteName)\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal Owner = (plr == Players.LocalPlayer)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal Velocity = 0\\n\\t\\n\\tif Anbimation:FindFirstChild(\\"Velocity\\") then\\n\\t\\tVelocity = Anbimation:FindFirstChild(\\"Velocity\\").Value\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tVelocity = 0.05\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tif data.Current then\\n\\t\\tdata.Current:Stop()\\n\\tend\\n\\tif valuestop[char.Name] then\\n\\t\\tif Owner then\\n\\t\\t\\tBasicRemote:FireServer({Action = \\"AttackDestroy\\"})\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tvaluestop[char.Name] = true\\n\\t\\n\\tif Owner then\\n\\t\\tdata.Current = track\\n\\t\\ttrack:Play()\\n\\t\\tchar:SetAttribute(\\"DoingEmote\\", true)\\n\\t\\tBasicRemote:FireServer({Action = \\"AttackD\\", walkspeed = Velocity, jumpforce = 0})\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\tfor i, v in pairs(Anbimation:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\t\\tif v:IsA(\\"ModuleScript\\") and v.Name == \\"Function\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal scrippt = require(v)\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tscrippt.Act(track, char)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend)\\n\\n\\ttrack.Ended:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tif data.Current == track then\\n\\t\\t\\tdata.Current = nil\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\ttask.wait(0.1)\\n\\n\\t\\tif not data.Current and valuestop[char.Name] then\\n\\t\\t\\tvaluestop[char.Name] = nil\\n\\t\\t\\tchar:SetAttribute(\\"DoingE", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-06T20:54:02.902Z"}
117	devforum	4220085	How do I allow player to aim with 2 fingers on mobile?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4220085	Scripting	Implementing simultaneous multi-touch camera control on mobile where a player can aim using both the finger holding a shoot button and a secondary finger, while preventing the default 'pinch-to-zoom' gesture from blocking rotation.	\N	f	advanced	{GuiButton.Active}	{}	t	Provide a script that utilizes UserInputService to track multiple Touch inputs manually, calculating camera rotation deltas while bypassing the default camera module's input sinking and pinch-to-zoom logic.	49	1	3	2026-01-06 00:34:40.409	2026-01-08 17:07:26.573943	{"views": 49, "content": " For example, on the game Rivals, if you hold your finger on the shoot button, you can use that finger to aim while shooting, OR you can also use a second finger to aim while holding the shoot button with your first finger. \\n I have already tried to implement this by setting the Active property of the GuiButton to false, but when I try to aim with another finger, it does not let me move my camera. I believe this is because roblox detects it as being a pinch to zoom in/out and when you are zooming in/out on mobile, you cannot move your camera up/down/left/right. \\n Also when the Active property of the GuiButton is true, it allows me to aim with my second finger but not my first (the one pressing the shoot button) because when Active is true, the button becomes an input sink. \\n I have looked on other posts but haven’t been able to find a solution to this. Any help would be appreciated! ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-06T00:34:40.409Z"}
119	devforum	4227047	I need help with mortor6ds for a camera system thing	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4227047	Scripting	Motor6D-controlled camera tracking fails or mirrors when the base model is rotated because the CFrame calculation is performed in world space rather than relative to the base's object space.	Use CFrame:ToObjectSpace() to convert the world-space target CFrame (pointing from the camera to the player) into the local coordinate system of the camera's base. This ensures that the Motor6D rotation remains correct regardless of the model's orientation.	t	intermediate	{TweenService,RunService,Players,CFrame,Motor6D,ToObjectSpace,Lerp}	{}	t	A coding agent can automatically identify world-space CFrame assignments to Motor6D properties and suggest or apply ToObjectSpace transformations relative to the Parent or connected Part0/Part1 to maintain local orientation.	29	1	2	2026-01-07 20:42:07.238	2026-01-08 17:07:27.446813	{"views": 29, "content": " so when the model is untouched the camera is able to look at the player. but when I rotate the camera 90 to 180 degrees the camera doesn’t track the player correctly when you look at it from the front and still tried to track the player as if it wasn’t rotated. is there a way to make it work regardless of the models rotation \\n sadly it’s not letting me provide a video so I’ll use screenshots: \\n zero rotation: \\n         image  355×534 38.5 KB         \\n180 rotation: (the camera will look but mirrored) \\n         image  471×579 49.2 KB         \\n this is the entire script at the moment: \\n  local tweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\nlocal players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\n\\nlocal tweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(.8,Enum.EasingStyle.Quad,Enum.EasingDirection.Out)\\n\\nlocal s = script.Parent\\nlocal mainCameraHead = s.MainCameraHead.MainCameraHead\\nlocal yAxis = s.Arm.SecondXaxis.YAxis\\nlocal xAxis = s.Arm.ArmContainer.XAxis\\n\\nlocal LookAtPart\\n\\nlocal function FindClosestPlayer()\\n\\tfor _, v in players:GetPlayers() do\\n\\t\\tlocal Character = v.Character\\n\\n\\t\\tif Character then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Head = Character:WaitForChild(\\"Head\\")\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tif not LookAtPart then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tLookAtPart = Head\\n\\t\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif (mainCameraHead.Position - LookAtPart.Position).Magnitude &gt; (mainCameraHead.Position - Head.Position).Magnitude then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tLookAtPart = Head\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nwhile true do\\n\\tif LookAtPart then\\n\\t\\tlocal CameraDirectionH = CFrame.new(mainCameraHead.Position,LookAtPart.Position).RightVector\\n\\t\\tlocal CameraDirectionV = CFrame.new(mainCameraHead.Position,LookAtPart.Position).UpVector * -1.5\\n\\t\\tlocal Goal = CFrame.new(-xAxis.C1.Y, _,_) * CFrame.Angles(0, math.asin(CameraDirectionH.z), 0)\\n\\t\\tlocal Goal2 = CFrame.new(_, -yAxis.C1.Y,_) * CFrame.Angles(math.asin(CameraDirectionV.z), 0, 0)\\n\\t\\tlocal Tween = tweenService:Create(xAxis, tweenInfo, {C1 = Goal}):Play()\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif CameraDirectionV.Y &lt; -1.2 then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Tween2 = tweenService:Create(yAxis, tweenInfo, {C1 = Goal2}):Play()\\n\\t\\t\\t--print(\\"breaking.\\")\\n", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-07T20:42:07.238Z"}
121	devforum	4207467	How would I filter custom emojis	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4207467	Scripting	Custom emoji codes in chat systems bypass Roblox's content filter because the filter does not recognize the associated graphics as letters, allowing users to spell prohibited words using icons.	Map each custom emoji code to its corresponding alphanumeric character, convert the raw message into a plain text string using this mapping, pass the plain text through TextService:FilterStringAsync(), and if the filtered result contains hashes or changes, block or hash the original emoji-based message.	t	intermediate	{TextService,FilterStringAsync,GetNonChatStringForBroadcastAsync,string.gsub}	{}	t	An AI agent can automate the generation of the character-to-emoji mapping table and the string substitution logic required to sanitize the input before it reaches the filtering API.	165	14	13	2026-01-02 05:10:44.989	2026-01-08 17:07:30.300814	{"views": 165, "content": " \\n cc  @Real_BenTheMiner   @PotatoCommuter  \\n \\n Hello. I am working on a custom chat system for a Roblox game, and it has the functionality to provide users with custom emojis. These work perfectly fine. \\n The game in question, however, is a transit game (Potato City Subway), and we are giving users access to route bullets for better roleplay and interactivity. \\n  \\n   example above \\n The issue is, this flies entirely over roblox’s filter, and inputting swears does not provoke the chat filter at all. We want to give a way for the chat filter to actually recognize these to check for swears and banned words, but we aren’t sure how. \\n It seems nobody else has encountered such a problem, and because we want a vast variety of emojis, a solution has been hard to come by. \\n Any help would be greatly appreciated with this problem. ", "upvotes": 14, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2026-01-02T05:10:44.989Z"}
