129	devforum	4224359	Best way to organize multiple values on datastore and game	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4224359	DataStore	Efficiently organizing and saving complex, nested player data for multiple characters and skin selections in a DataStore.	Use a single, nested dictionary (table) structure to represent player data, categorizing by role (Survivor/Killer), character, and skin status (Owned/Equipped), which can be saved to a single DataStore key.	t	intermediate	{JSONEncode,JSONDecode,DataStoreService}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a standard DataStore module and a data template representing the nested table structure, along with helper functions to update specific keys (e.g., 'EquipSkin') within the table.	61	1	3	2026-01-07 04:27:51.682	2026-01-08 17:07:38.920086	{"views": 61, "content": " I wasn’t sure on how to write the title but I’ll explain it better here. I’m a mediocre scripter and I’m making and asymmetric game (Like forsaken, dead by daylight or any other game like this), and Eventually i will make skins for each survivor character and also each killer character, and I just realized that I’ll have to somehow save the player’s equipped skin for each killer and survivor in a way that both the game and the data store could access it easily, I could make multiple values on a data store and this would probably work but it just doesn’t sound like a good way to do it. I need to find a way to do this in a more efficient way, if there is one of course. Thanks! ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-07T04:27:51.682Z"}
130	devforum	3550319	How do i put the characters default chosen face from avatar catalog that they have equipped onto a custom starter character?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/3550319	Scripting	Setting a Decal's Texture property to the Asset ID returned by HumanoidDescription.Face results in a blank image because the Catalog ID must be converted to an Image ID for raw Decal usage.	\N	f	intermediate	{Players:GetHumanoidDescriptionFromUserId,PlayerAdded,CharacterAdded,Instance.new,WaitForChild}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest using Humanoid:ApplyDescription() instead of manual Decal manipulation, or use InsertService:LoadAsset() to retrieve the actual Decal object contained within the Catalog ID asset.	230	0	6	2025-03-14 22:01:47.737	2026-01-08 17:07:41.120506	{"views": 230, "content": " Im trying to put the default avatars face on a custom avatar. The custom avatar is just an R6 Rig. \\n This is what i have. I dont understand why this doesn’t work. Let me know if anyone can see the issue with this. \\n  game.Players.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tplayer.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(character)\\n\\t\\tlocal head = character:WaitForChild(\\"Head\\")\\n\\n\\t\\t-- Removes existing face decal from StarterCharacter\\n\\t\\tlocal existingFace = head:FindFirstChild(\\"face\\")\\n\\t\\tif existingFace then\\n\\t\\t\\texistingFace:Destroy()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t-- Clone the player's face decal\\n\\t\\tlocal face = game.Players:GetHumanoidDescriptionFromUserId(player.UserId).Face\\n\\t\\tif face and face ~= 0 then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal newFace = Instance.new(\\"Decal\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tnewFace.Name = \\"face\\"\\n\\t\\t\\tnewFace.Texture = \\"rbxassetid://\\" .. tostring(face)\\n\\t\\t\\tnewFace.Parent = head\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend)\\nend)\\n\\n  \\n Extra. \\n → This is a ServerScript located in ServerScriptService \\n → This is done on a Roblox Default R6 Rig Custom Character. (Rig Isn’t Custom. Its made by Roblox) ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-03-14T22:01:47.737Z"}
750	devforum	4098850	IKControl not resetting after enabled disable	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4098850	Animation	IKControl maintains its previous transform state after being disabled and re-enabled, causing visual snapping and glitches instead of resetting to the current character pose.	Apply an idle animation to the character to ensure the motor transforms are updated, which prevents the IKControl from using stale transform data when re-activated.	t	intermediate	{IKControl,HumanoidRootPart,UpperTorso}	{}	t	An automated script can verify if an AnimationTrack is actively playing on the Animator before enabling an IKControl to ensure valid pose data.	37	1	2	2025-11-26 18:01:30.341	2026-01-08 17:19:12.657461	{"views": 37, "content": " So I’m making an aiming system for my game where the player can shoot in a cone in front and slightly behind. To animate the character aiming, I’ve been using IKControl objects. \\n When the player flips from shooting either left or right, I want the character to rotate around the forward LookVector, otherwise, the legs get all twisted up. However, I’m trying to disable the IKControl for the upper torso, and then enable it again after the legs have turned around, where the UpperTorso starts from a neutral position. \\n Here is a video of the problem: \\n https://gyazo.com/f4ac54ac332094c35e4b36fd3dddf716  \\n You can see the snapping and glitches happening as a result of my issue. \\n Here is a slowed-down version of what’s going on. \\n https://gyazo.com/636735c8c2b805f2dabd5c57a5d581e7  \\n You can see i disable the IKControl for the upperTorso(Red), and it falls in line with the HRP (green) \\nThis allows me to rotate the HRP to face the new point without the legs twisting. \\n Finally, I enable the IKControls again, but instead of the UpperTorso starting from its current position, it seems to remember its old offset and resets to that point, instead of the new neutral point while it’s disabled. \\n I know this probably wasn’t the best explanation of what’s going on, but any help on how to prevent this snapping from happening would be greatly appreciated ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "building-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-11-26T18:01:30.341Z"}
