160	devforum	4220538	Is there a better (alternative) to ZonePlus for Voice Chat manipulation?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4220538	Scripting	Seeking an alternative to ZonePlus for spatial detection to manipulate VoiceChatService behavior based on a player's physical location within zones.	A community-created module named 'Zones' which uses math and boolean logic for spatial checks instead of spatial queries like GetPartsInPart or Touched.	f	intermediate	{VoiceChatService,ZonePlus}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a custom Region3 or math-based volume check script that toggles voice chat properties or state when a player's character position is detected within specific boundaries.	37	0	2	2026-01-06 03:13:38.975	2026-01-08 17:08:47.447112	{"views": 37, "content": " I have been wanting to making a system that involves voice chat service and its usage within zones. \\n I was planning on using  ZonePlus  but I have read that they are planning their own rework for the module.  My worry is deprecation after writing it , so I wanted to know if there was any other module or package that is currently being used to complete this task.  I currently don’t have a package manager  so I am also just overall kind of in the dark on the module. \\n  If there was any sort of tutorial for a system that was built from scratch that allowed for physical zoning with voice chat I would appreciate a reference or link to it in this thread, as I could attempt to recreate it instead of depending on zoneplus (or alternative). And obviously if someone might have experience making a voice chat system like such, add your suggestions or tips for making it  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-06T03:13:38.975Z"}
161	devforum	1538802	How to turn look vector into a rotational cframe	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/1538802	Scripting	Converting a LookVector into a rotational CFrame, specifically for reconstructing a turret's orientation after clamping its direction vector.	A LookVector alone is insufficient to define a CFrame; you must also define an UpVector. The solution involves using the cross product of the LookVector and a global UpVector (0, 1, 0) to find the RightVector, then finding the orthogonal UpVector by crossing the LookVector and RightVector. These vectors can then be passed into CFrame.fromMatrix.	t	intermediate	{CFrame,Vector3:Cross,CFrame.fromMatrix,lookVector}	{}	t	Create a utility function that accepts a LookVector and an optional UpVector (defaulting to Vector3.new(0, 1, 0)) to return a CFrame via CFrame.fromMatrix, handling cases where the look direction is parallel to the UpVector.	4154	5	6	2021-11-07 04:11:56.797	2026-01-08 17:08:48.184909	{"views": 4154, "content": " I tried looking on  CFrame  for a way to do this but i am stuck. Also it is not relative to any part just the workspace. \\n The reason why i need this is so i can restrict the movements of a turret im making. For example i get teh look vector, then clamp the y value, but then i need to turn it back into a cframe. ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2021-11-07T04:11:56.797Z"}
162	devforum	4218369	Can Roblox prune Studio-facing data?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4218369	Scripting	Inquiry regarding whether Studio-specific properties like Instance.Locked can be pruned during game compilation to improve replication performance and memory footprint at runtime.	Roblox does not prune these properties because they have a negligible memory footprint (defined once per class via reflection) and removing them would break backward compatibility for scripts that reference them in production environments.	t	intermediate	{Locked}	{}	f	An agent cannot modify engine-level compilation behavior, but it could lint scripts to identify usage of properties intended for Studio use to ensure they are not being relied upon for critical production logic.	147	9	5	2026-01-05 13:46:01.433	2026-01-08 17:08:48.963297	{"views": 147, "content": " I want to know if there exist some properties or information tied to classes, like .Locked, that could be removed when the game is compiled outside of Studio. Or, if Roblox has tried anything like this in the past. \\n I feel like this could improve replication performance, and I don’t know if many use .Locked on runtime outside of Studio testing ", "upvotes": 9, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-05T13:46:01.433Z"}
