do\\n\\t\\tlocal selectedObby:Model = obbySelection[math.random(1,#obbySelection)]:Clone()\\n\\t\\tselectedObby:PivotTo(nextPosition)\\n\\t\\tselectedObby.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\tnextPosition = selectedObby.ObbyEnd.CFrame\\n\\tend\\n\\tlocal newObbyComplete = obbyComplete:Clone()\\n\\tobbyComplete.CFrame = nextPosition\\n\\tnewObbyComplete.Parent = workspace\\n\\thumanoidRootPart.CFrame = CFrame.new(startPosition + Vector3.new(0,5,0))\\nend\\n  \\n I have verified that the start position itself should be correct so its something else. \\n Here is a video of this happening: \\n              \\n ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 10, "created_at": "2026-01-08T01:59:04.955Z"}
168	devforum	4220149	.Touched Problems	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4220149	Scripting	Character detection logic fails when a player holds a tool because the script only checks two levels up the hierarchy (Parent and Parent.Parent) to find the character from a touching part.	\N	f	beginner	{workspace:GetPartsInPart,Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter,CollectionService:HasTag,CollectionService:AddTag,CollectionService:RemoveTag}	{}	t	An AI coding agent could suggest using a recursive 'findFirstAncestorOfClass' or 'GetPlayerFromPart' helper function to reliably identify a player regardless of how many nested parts a tool or accessory contains.	53	0	2	2026-01-06 00:58:33.757	2026-01-08 17:08:58.094525	{"views": 53, "content": " Currently I am making a king system where you have to touch a part. When there is no tool being held and player is standing still it counts, but when a tool is held and a player is standing still it stops. Please help \\n   \\n     \\n  local function awardKingSeconds()\\n\\tfor _, throne in pairs(kingThrones:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\tif throne:HasTag(\\"KingSpot\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t-- Get everything touching the throne\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal touchingParts = workspace:GetPartsInPart(throne)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal playersRewarded = {} -- Prevent double-counting if multiple limbs touch\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, part in pairs(touchingParts) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t-- Check if part.Parent is the character OR if part.Parent.Parent is (for tools)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal character = part.Parent\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(character)\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t-- If not found, check one level up (for tool parts)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif not player then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcharacter = part.Parent.Parent\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayer = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(character)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif player and not playersRewarded[player] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal leaderstats = player:FindFirstChild(\\"leaderstats\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal kingSeconds = leaderstats and leaderstats:FindFirstChild(\\"Seconds Ruled\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif kingSeconds then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tkingSeconds.Value += 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayersRewarded[player] = true\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayer:AddTag(\\"King\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t-- Remove King tag from players no longer on throne\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, player in pairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif player:HasTag(\\"King\\") and not playersRewarded[player] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayer:RemoveTag(\\"King\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n (ignore it not counting anymore I had an error) ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-06T00:58:33.757Z"}
169	devforum	4219878	Single Remote Event & Function Networking	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4219878	Networking	Whether using a centralized single RemoteEvent and RemoteFunction for all network traffic (middleware pattern) is efficient and best practice in Roblox.	A centralized networking system is acceptable for organization; however, for high-frequency traffic, developers should consider multiple events or highly compacted data packets to avoid overhead and potential bottlenecks.	t	intermediate	{RemoteEvent,RemoteFunction,RunService,ReplicatedStorage,FireClient,FireServer,InvokeServer,FireAllClients}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate standardized networking wrappers that include automated route registration, rate limiting, and payload serialization to ensure best practices are followed.	56	1	2	2026-01-05 23:23:50.625	2026-01-08 17:08:59.194572	{"views": 56, "content": " I have a question regarding networking in Roblox. Is it a good practice to handle all server–client and client–server communication through a single  RemoteEvent  and  RemoteFunction ? \\n Below is a custom networking module I created to handle interactions between client &amp; server &amp; server to client. \\n Both the server and clients can register  “binds” , which act as named route associated with callback functions. \\n For example, if a client registers a bind called  \\"UpdateXPVisuals\\" , the server can invoke it as follows: \\n  --Server \\nNetwork.Push(Player, \\"UpdateXPVisuals\\", {PlayerXPData}\\n\\n--Clients can react by doing--\\nNetwork.ClientBind(\\"UpdateXPVisuals\\", function(Data)\\n\\t\\t--some visual effect here--\\n\\tend)\\n\\n  \\n  local RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal Network = {}\\nNetwork.RATE_LIMIT = 20 --calls per route\\nNetwork.RATE_WINDOW = 1\\nNetwork.RATE_LIMITER = {}\\n\\nNetwork.Routes = { --server specific\\n\\t\\n}\\n\\nNetwork.ClientRoutes = {\\n\\t\\n}\\n\\n\\nlocal EventsFolder = ReplicatedStorage:FindFirstChild(\\"Events\\")\\n\\n\\n\\nlocal RemoteEvent = EventsFolder:FindFirstChild(\\"NetworkEvent\\")\\nlocal RemoteFunction = EventsFolder:FindFirstChild(\\"NetworkFunction\\")\\n\\n\\nif RunService:IsServer() then\\n\\tif not RemoteEvent then\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent.Name = \\"NetworkEvent\\"\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent.Parent = EventsFolder\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tif not RemoteFunction then\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction = Instance.new(\\"RemoteFunction\\")\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction.Name = \\"NetworkFunction\\"\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction.Parent = EventsFolder\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\n\\nNetwork.RemoteEvent = RemoteEvent\\nNetwork.RemoteFunction = RemoteFunction\\n\\n\\n\\n-- SERVER ONLY: bind a route \\n--where we define the routes/functionalities\\nfunction Network.ServerBind(name : string, callback )\\n\\tNetwork.Routes[name] = callback\\nend\\n\\n\\nfunction Network.ClientBind(name: string, callback)\\n\\tif RunService:IsServer() then\\n\\t\\terror(\\"ClientBind can only be called from client\\")\\n\\tend\\n\\tNetwork.ClientRoutes[name] = callback", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-05T23:23:50.625Z"}
