198	devforum	4212980	Need help with resolving extreme memory leaks for endurance racing league	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212980	Networking	Extreme network throughput and script execution rate (448k/s) leading to memory/performance failure during long-duration racing sessions, likely caused by unoptimized RemoteEvent broadcasting of large data tables.	\N	f	advanced	{RunService,RemoteEvent,ModuleScript,FireAllClients,PlayerAdded,pcall}	{}	t	Identify and flag patterns where `FireAllClients` is used to send large, nested tables within high-frequency loops or event triggers, and suggest delta-compression or property-based updates instead.	191	2	12	2026-01-03 19:57:00.91	2026-01-08 17:09:28.345843	{"views": 191, "content": " Hi, I own a roblox racing league called REC. We host long endurance races that last upwards of 2 hours to 4 hours, and I’ve noticed a very important issue that needs to be resolved that I cannot figure out. During the race, the total kb/s went up to 9gb per second, and never went down. The rate/s for the main script also went up - to almost 448,000 - and kept rising exponentially. \\n  picture of the kb/s at one point in the race  \\n  \\n Some quick background on how the systems work: \\nThere is a main script in the workspace called Systems, which loads the other modules that control timing systems, pitstops, etc. The heirarchy looks like this: \\n          image  150×342 8.12 KB         \\n(The Scripts folder has been ruled out as a source of the lag) \\n The Systems script looks like this: \\n  print(\\"[Systems] Loading systems...\\")\\n\\nlocal Data = require(script.Data)\\nData:Load()\\n\\n-- Load Modules with tracking\\nfor _, Module in script.Modules:GetChildren() do\\n\\tlocal s, m = pcall(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal mod = require(Module)\\n\\t\\tmod:Load()\\n\\tend)\\n\\n\\tif not s then\\n\\t\\twarn(`Error loading module {Module.Name}: {m}`)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\n-- Load Static with tracking\\nfor _, Module in script.Static:GetChildren() do\\n\\tlocal s, m = pcall(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal mod = require(Module)\\n\\t\\tmod:Load()\\n\\tend)\\n\\n\\tif not s then\\n\\t\\twarn(`Error loading module {Module.Name}: {m}`)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n  The rate for this script rose to over 400,000/s and never stopped rising.  \\n The timing systems involve position roughly 150 parts around the track, that when a player touches them, it stores this in the user’s CarData. All car data is controlled in one module script, Data, whose structure looks like this: \\n  local Data = {\\n\\tCars = {},\\n\\t\\n\\tAuthorized = {\\n\\t\\t1382359571,\\n\\t\\t-1,\\n\\t\\t-2\\n\\t},\\n\\t\\n\\tCarTemplate = {\\n\\t\\tTeamName = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarClass = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarNumber = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarName = nil,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tCarModel = nil,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tDriving = nil,\\n\\t\\tSessionFinished = false,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tMembers = {},\\n\\t\\tAvailableMembers = {},\\n\\t},\\n}\\n\\nlocal Utils = require(workspace.Systems.Utils)\\nlocal", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 12, "created_at": "2026-01-03T19:57:00.910Z"}
753	devforum	4098802	I need help with a question about shadows and all of optimization in Roblox Studio	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4098802	Other	Excessive shadow recalculations and high shadow draw calls where moving a single object triggers a global shadow update, leading to a massive increase in polygon count and significant FPS drops.	\N	f	advanced	{}	{}	f	A coding agent cannot fix engine-level rendering bugs, but it could assist by writing scripts to programmatically disable 'CastShadow' on non-essential parts or manage light source visibility based on distance to reduce the rendering load.	91	4	2	2025-11-26 17:39:24.379	2026-01-08 17:19:17.168934	{"views": 91, "content": " Hello everyone, I need help with a question about shadows. \\n  Does anyone know exactly how shadow rendering works in the engine? And also, which graphics settings are responsible for what? (Specifically from level 0 to level 21).  \\n The whole problem is described here:  Shadow Draw Calls are broken  and here:  Roblox lags, sheduler render is broken.. were are optimization in roblox????? - #3 by d_HaKeRo4eK228sky  \\n I contacted Roblox support, wrote to staff, and posted on this forum - zero results. No one has helped me so far. Why does this problem affect everyone? \\n Because it’s a question about the optimization of the engine itself and the future development of the engine. The introduction of something new, more large-scale. \\n My questions about shadow rendering optimization started in the summer, and then after one of the updates, a problem with the Scheduler began - it started to grow in many places, and the general picture is that FPS dropped everywhere by about 20%. This affects all high-quality, complex places in Roblox. Even popular ones like Doors or Pressure. \\n I can’t explain the shadow recalculations and why we have such low performance. The Dump file doesn’t provide much information for me. I wanted to find the source code for Roblox Studio to understand how the rendering works there - because it uses its own algorithm. The only thing that’s clear in the game itself is that due to the movement of a single object, literally any movement, shadow calculation is activated for almost the entire map. And the more details there are on the map, the larger its scale, the more polygons the shadow calculation consumes. And imagine, shadows are consuming about 15 million polygons. This drops the FPS significantly. The on-screen scene is only 2 million polygons (Depth + Scene), but if you add Shadows, it’s already 17 million. \\n The strangest thing is that in popular games outside of Roblox, even projects from 2017-2020, don’t have problems with lighting; they creat", "upvotes": 4, "category": "building-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-11-26T17:39:24.379Z"}
