802	devforum	4080020	Looking for Optimization Insight	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4080020	3D Modeling	Optimizing a high-fidelity 1:1 scale city environment to prevent freeze frames during streaming and ensure compatibility across low-end devices.	\N	f	advanced	{StreamingEnabled,StreamingMesh,ReplicatedStorage}	{"As soon as a new chunk renders, with a smaller radius it just completely freeze frames"}	t	An automation tool could audit the workspace to identify high-part-count areas, automatically set RenderFidelity to 'Performance' on distant meshes, or programmatically convert legacy textures/decals into PBR Materials to optimize draw calls.	157	10	8	2025-11-18 19:30:56.943	2026-01-08 17:20:09.447152	{"views": 157, "content": " Hi all, hoping to get insights and or some tips towards optimizing a  very  large experience \\n My group, which is currently holding a closed beta of our game,  https://www.roblox.com/share?code=6e02a96b617ab54eb6755d15b412a6fc&amp;type=ExperienceDetails&amp;stamp=1763493670336 , is struggling with optimization \\n Our game is a 1 to 1 recreation of an entire city block in Kyoto, meaning: intensely detailed. I’d go as far as to say it is a showcase game attempting to house a roleplay game \\n          image-37  1920×884 175 KB         \\n That obviously poses a lot of issues from an optimization front, aside from the clear issues of some devices being alienated from gameplay - we really want to try to find a way to balance a stunning artistic experience, with an optimized game that is playable on all devices \\n \\n Here are some steps we have taken, that have obviously helped, but are not enough right now: \\n \\n \\n VisTools is being used for a very stringent LOD system. The amount of buildings is massive, so the  entire  building is being turned into a singular block LOD as soon as you get out of direct eyeshot of it. I believe this is set to around 120 studs before it turns \\n \\n \\n Smaller details such as mailboxes, lamp posts, small furniture, flower pots etc are all set to detail_tiny using VisTools at radius of 45 and are removed from the workspace at that radius \\n \\n \\n Streaming is on, with a min radius of 1024. I wanted to keep this a lot smaller, but this was not possible - I believe due to the amount of items in the workspace. As soon as a new chunk renders, with a smaller radius it just completely freeze frames \\n \\n \\n StreamingMesh has not really been played around with at all, everything is currently set to default \\n \\n \\n Almost all interior lights and exterior lights are radius based, and are put into ReplicatedStorage by default – only being turned “on” with a scripted light switch. The only outstanding lights are street lights at night (scripted) \\n \\n \\n Optimizations hav", "upvotes": 10, "category": "building-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2025-11-18T19:30:56.943Z"}
