215	devforum	4218467	Bytenet problem	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4218467	Networking	ByteNet 'attempt to index nil with read' error caused by mismatched packet struct definitions between the client and server.	Ensure that both the client and server utilize the exact same namespace and packet definitions. This is best achieved by sharing a single ModuleScript for definitions to prevent discrepancies in field names, order, or data types.	t	intermediate	{ByteNet.defineNamespace,ByteNet.definePacket,ByteNet.struct,ByteNet.bool,ByteNet.float32}	{"ReplicatedStorage.Packages._Index.ffrostflame_bytenet@0.4.6.bytenet.dataTypes.struct:62: attempt to index nil with ‘read’"}	t	A static analysis tool or linter could compare the networking definition modules used by the client and server to identify schema mismatches or verify that the arguments passed to :send align with the defined struct schema.	70	0	2	2026-01-05 14:40:20.88	2026-01-08 17:09:43.924069	{"views": 70, "content": " You can write your topic however you want, but you need to answer these questions: \\n \\n \\n **What do you want to achieve? : want to solve this bug \\n \\n \\n  What is the issue?  : \\nutility snippet \\nlocal PlayerService: PlayerService = { \\nbyteNetData = {}, \\nconfig = { \\ndataLoadTimeout = 12, \\n}, \\n} \\n \\n \\n PlayerService.byteNetData.Communication = ByteNet.defineNamespace(“Communication”, function() \\nreturn { \\nClientLoaded = ByteNet.definePacket({ \\nvalue = ByteNet.struct({ \\nsuccess = ByteNet.bool, \\n}), \\n}), \\nServerLoaded = ByteNet.definePacket({ \\nvalue = ByteNet.struct({ \\nsuccess = ByteNet.bool, \\nduration = ByteNet.float32, \\n}), \\n}), \\n} \\nend) \\nclient snippet \\nlocal Utils = require(script.Utils) \\n function PlayerService.SendClientLoaded(self: PlayerService) \\nUtils.byteNetData.Communication.ClientLoaded:send({ success = true }) – HELLO SERVER? \\nend \\n Utils.byteNetData.Communication.ServerLoaded:listen(function(data) \\nPlayerService.status.isServerLoaded = true – SERVER ACTIVATED ME WOO HOO! \\nPlayerService.status.success = data.success \\nPlayerService.status.duration = data.duration \\nend) \\n   server snippet \\nUtils.byteNetData.Communication.ServerLoaded:send({ success = true, duration = durationTookToInit }, player) \\n Utils.byteNetData.Communication.ClientLoaded:listen(function(player: Player, data) – HAPPENS AFTER CLIENT LOADS \\nif not data.success then \\nPlayerService:HandleLeave(player, “Client failed to load data”, false) – Like, client might got a device problem or smth occurres rarely \\nend \\nend) \\n error log part \\n23:22:46.756  ReplicatedStorage.Packages._Index.ffrostflame_bytenet@0.4.6.bytenet.dataTypes.struct:62: attempt to index nil with ‘read’  -  Client - struct:62 \\n23:22:46.756  Stack Begin  -  Studio \\n23:22:46.757  Script ‘ReplicatedStorage.Packages._Index.ffrostflame_bytenet@0.4.6.bytenet.dataTypes.struct’, Line 62  -  Studio - struct:62 \\n23:22:46.757  Script ‘ReplicatedStorage.Services.PlayerService.Utils’, Line 49  -  Studio - Utils:49 \\n23:22:46.757  Script ‘Replicated", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-05T14:40:20.880Z"}
218	devforum	4186615	Npc Follow Player Script Not Workng	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4186615	Scripting	The script attempts to use 'game.Players.LocalPlayer' within a server-side Script located in a Workspace NPC model, which returns nil and results in the logic failing silently.	Replace the use of 'LocalPlayer' with logic that iterates through all players on the server (e.g., using game.Players:GetPlayers()) to determine if any player is in the zone, or change the Script's RunContext property to 'Client'.	t	beginner	{game.Players.LocalPlayer,RunService.Heartbeat,Humanoid:MoveTo,BasePart:IsPointInRegion3,RunContext}	{}	t	Scan for instances where 'game.Players.LocalPlayer' is used in Scripts (server-side) located in the Workspace, as this will always return nil.	90	2	3	2025-12-26 19:16:34.159	2026-01-08 17:09:46.962559	{"views": 90, "content": " Hi, I’m trying to make a npc that follows the player while they’re in a zone (part), but the script isn’t working. There’s no errors in the output, and the script is located in the npc. Pls pls help Here’s the code: \\n  local zonePart = game.Workspace.Zone1\\nlocal npc = script.Parent  \\nlocal humanoid = npc:FindFirstChildOfClass(\\"Humanoid\\")  \\nlocal followSpeed = 16  \\n\\nlocal function isPlayerInZone(player)\\n   local character = player.Character\\n   if character then\\n       local humanoidRootPart = character:FindFirstChild(\\"HumanoidRootPart\\")\\n       if humanoidRootPart then\\n           return zonePart:IsPointInRegion3(humanoidRootPart.Position)\\n       end\\n   end\\n   return false\\nend\\n\\nlocal function followPlayer(player)\\n   local character = player.Character\\n   local humanoidRootPart = character:FindFirstChild(\\"HumanoidRootPart\\")\\n   if humanoidRootPart then\\n       local direction = (humanoidRootPart.Position - npc.HumanoidRootPart.Position).unit\\n       humanoid:MoveTo(npc.HumanoidRootPart.Position + direction * followSpeed)\\n   end\\nend\\n\\ngame:GetService(\\"RunService\\").Heartbeat:Connect(function()\\n   local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer \\n   if player and isPlayerInZone(player) then\\n       followPlayer(player)\\n   end\\nend)\\n\\nzonePart.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\\n   local character = hit.Parent\\n   local player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(character)\\n   \\n   if player then\\n       if isPlayerInZone(player) then\\n           followPlayer(player)\\n       else\\n           humanoid:MoveTo(npc.Position)  \\n       end\\n   end\\nend)  ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-26T19:16:34.159Z"}
