213	devforum	4225407	Help understanding discrepancy of HumanoidStateTypes between PC and mobile	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4225407	Scripting	Discrepancy in HumanoidStateType when checking GetState() during input events: PC (InputBegan) reports 'Running' while Mobile (MouseButton1Click) reports 'Freefall', causing inconsistent double-jump logic.	\N	f	intermediate	{Humanoid.ChangeState,Humanoid.GetState,Enum.HumanoidStateType,UserInputService.InputBegan,Humanoid.StateChanged}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest moving the multi-jump logic to a StateChanged listener or utilizing UserInputService.JumpRequest to normalize behavior across platforms, as state updates can occur at different points in the frame's task scheduler relative to input.	131	15	13	2026-01-07 13:23:22.589	2026-01-08 17:09:43.10829	{"views": 131, "content": " \\n  What do you want to achieve?  Keep it simple and clear! \\nDouble/triple jump system that uses InputBegan/Mouse1Click and humanoid:ChangeState(Enum.HumanoidStateType.Jumping, true) to listen and action jumps for mobile and PC. \\n  What is the issue?  Include screenshots / videos if possible! \\nI have a check in my script to only permit a double/triple jump to occur if humanoid is in Enum.HumanoidStateType.Freefall state but when jumping on PC via space bar the HumanoidStateType for humanoid results in ‘Running’ but on mobile pressing the jump button results in ‘Freefall’ (both tests conducted while character is standing still). This causes a problem as PC will allow for an extra jump and mobile will be at a disadvantage. \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Did you look for solutions on the Creator Hub? \\nI don’t want to go down the route of attempting to intercept jump requests nor use JumpRequest event as it feels unreliable to me - i’m hoping that understanding the reason behind this discrepancy will help me fix the logic. \\n \\n  local jumpUsage = 0\\n\\nif rebirth.Value &gt;= 1 and rebirth.Value &lt; 5 then\\n\\tjumpUsage = 1\\nelseif rebirth.Value &gt;= 5 then\\n\\tjumpUsage = 2\\nend\\n\\nlocal mobileJumpButton = CheckForMobileJumpButton()\\nif mobileJumpButton then\\n\\tmobileJumpButton.MouseButton1Click:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tif humanoidRootPart and humanoid then\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(humanoid:GetState()) -- results in 'Freefall'\\n\\t\\t\\tif humanoid:GetState() == Enum.HumanoidStateType.Freefall then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tprint(humanoid:GetState()) -- results in 'Freefall'\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif rebirth.Value &gt;= 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif jumpUsage &gt;= 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tjumpUsage -= 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\thumanoid:ChangeState(Enum.HumanoidStateType.Jumping, true)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tprint(jumpUsage)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\thumanoid.StateChanged:Connect(function(old, new)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif new == Enum.HumanoidStateType.Landed then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif rebirth.Value &gt;= 1 and rebirth.Value &lt; 5 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tjumpUsage = 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\telseif rebirth.Value &gt;= 5 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tjumpUsage = 2\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend", "upvotes": 15, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2026-01-07T13:23:22.589Z"}
216	devforum	4231704	Are hingeconstraints server or client sided?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4231704	Physics	Determining whether HingeConstraint physics calculations occur on the server or client and how network ownership affects player interaction.	HingeConstraints are physics constraints where movement is calculated by the network owner of the parts. Setting the network owner determines which side handles the physics simulation.	t	beginner	{HingeConstraint}	{}	t	Generate a server script that identifies parts with HingeConstraints and sets their network ownership using SetNetworkOwner(nil) to ensure consistent server-side physics for all players.	37	2	4	2026-01-08 17:03:26.03	2026-01-08 17:09:45.847086	{"views": 37, "content": " This is just a quick question, I never really investigated in that theme until now. If they are client then all good, but if they are server, then that’s a problem for me, would i just change the network ownership of them? Thanks for the help (basically, it’s for an obby and i need players to step on these rotating parts) ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-08T17:03:26.030Z"}
217	devforum	3933900	AlignOrientation moves the position of the object	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/3933900	Physics	AlignOrientation is causing a part to shift its physical position when unanchored, rather than only affecting its rotation.	\N	f	intermediate	{AlignOrientation,Attachment,Touched,TouchEnded,Humanoid}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest checking the 'ReactionForceEnabled' property of the AlignOrientation or recommend using a Motor6D or CFrame logic to rotate the NPC head without physics-induced positional drift.	153	3	2	2025-09-14 00:54:21.131	2026-01-08 17:09:46.656445	{"views": 153, "content": " So I’m trying to make an NPC face the player when they’re near. However, that moves the position of the head as well, and it’s very unnatural. \\n  \\n    \\nAnchoring the part fixes its position, but it won’t rotate; unanchoring the head produces this result.  \\n My script essentially sets the  Attachment1  of the AlignOrientation object to a specific attachment on the player when they enter the zone, and sets  Attachment1  to  nil  when there are no players inside the zone. \\n Here’s my script: \\n  local alignment = script.Parent.Parent.Guard.AlignOrientation\\nlocal zone = script.Parent\\nlocal list = {}\\n\\nfunction addWithoutDuplicate(value)\\n\\tfor _, v in list do\\n\\t\\tif v == value then\\n\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\ttable.insert(list, value)\\nend\\n\\nfunction remove(value)\\n\\tfor i, v in list do\\n\\t\\tif v == value then\\n\\t\\t\\ttable.remove(list, i)\\n\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nzone.Touched:Connect(function(part)\\n\\tif part:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\taddWithoutDuplicate(part)\\n\\telseif part.Parent:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Parent.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\taddWithoutDuplicate(part.Parent)\\n\\telseif part.Parent.Parent:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Parent.Parent.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\taddWithoutDuplicate(part.Parent.Parent)\\n\\telseif part.Parent.Parent.Parent:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Parent.Parent.Parent.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\taddWithoutDuplicate(part.Parent.Parent.Parent)\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tif #list == 0 then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = nil\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n\\nzone.TouchEnded:Connect(function(part)\\n\\tif part:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\tremove(part)\\n\\telseif part.Parent:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Parent.Head.FaceFrontAttachment\\n\\t\\tremove(part.Parent)\\n\\telseif part.Parent.Parent:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\talignment.Attachment1 = part.Parent.Parent.Head.FaceFront", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-09-14T00:54:21.131Z"}
219	devforum	4231030	Help with Implementing Lag Compensation	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4231030	Networking	Discrepancy in server-side lag compensation rewind logic causing a 1-2 stud offset between client-side visual hits and server-calculated historical positions.	\N	f	advanced	{RunService,Players,ReplicatedStorage,RemoteEvent,CFrame,HumanoidRootPart,Heartbeat}	{}	t	An AI agent could provide a more robust time-synchronization system using 'workspace:GetServerTimeNow()' and ensure the rewind logic correctly accounts for half the Round Trip Time (RTT/2) plus client-side interpolation delay.	46	0	3	2026-01-08 13:31:22.692	2026-01-08 17:09:49.342444	{"views": 46, "content": " So, recently, I am trying to make a lag compensation script because I want to try to make a battleground game. \\n I do this because I am think if client side create hitbox will cause a security issue, on the other hand, create a hitbox on the server side also will cause a delay issue: attacker may hit a player already in his view, but can’t do damage actually. \\n Therefore, I want to create a lag compensation script. By rewinding on the server side using the ping of a player, it can calculate the position of a player in the seconds of delay ago. \\n Below are script on the server side and client side. Client side script create a green box when I click on the mouse. After it reach server, it create another red box after calculating the position using the ping. \\n However, the issue is that the red box is still far away from the green box (around 1-2studs). I don’t expect they can have a completely same position, but I expect it at least near to each other. \\n Why this happening, could anyone help me? I would really happy if anyone can provide the reason and answer for this. Thank you \\n  Scripts are written by AI, but i checked that the code are all make sense for me  \\n Server Script Code: \\n  local RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal Debris = game:GetService(\\"Debris\\")\\n\\n-- SETUP REMOTE EVENT\\nlocal hitEvent = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\nhitEvent.Name = \\"HitRequest\\"\\nhitEvent.Parent = ReplicatedStorage\\n\\n-- CONFIGURATION\\nlocal BUFFER_TIME = 1.0 -- How many seconds of history to keep\\n\\n-- DATA STORAGE: PlayerHistory[Player] = { {Time = 10, CFrame = ...}, ... }\\nlocal PlayerHistory = {}\\n\\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n-- HELPER: CALCULATE POSITION AT EXACT TIME (Step 3)\\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nlocal function GetCFrameAtTime(targetPlayer, targetTime)\\n\\tlocal histo", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-08T13:31:22.692Z"}
222	devforum	4231644	Large Scale Lighting is Inconsistent	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4231644	Other	Sudden and jarring lighting changes (eye adaptation/auto-exposure) when transitioning between bright outdoor areas and dark interior environments like caves.	Adjust the Ambient and OutdoorAmbient properties within the Lighting service to create a better balance between interior visibility and exterior brightness.	t	beginner	{Lighting,Ambient}	{}	t	A script can be used to monitor the player's camera position or region and smoothly interpolate ExposureCompensation or Ambient lighting values to prevent jarring transitions.	22	0	2	2026-01-08 16:47:49.202	2026-01-08 17:09:51.497662	{"views": 22, "content": " Does anyone know how to fix this? The lighting jarringly changes its properties when entering dark areas such as caves, is there a way to disable this or at least minimize its effects? or is this something I’m just going to need to build around. \\n   \\n     ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-08T16:47:49.202Z"}
234	devforum	4226093	:ApplyImpulseAtPosition() works strange?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4226093	Physics	ApplyImpulseAtPosition applies physics forces to a part even when the specified position vector is outside the physical bounds of the assembly.	The method is designed to calculate torque and linear velocity based on the point's offset from the center of mass without performing collision or bounds checks. To restrict impulse to actual contact, developers must manually verify proximity using methods like BasePart:GetClosestPointOnSurface().	t	intermediate	{ApplyImpulseAtPosition,GetClosestPointOnSurface}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a wrapper function that checks if a point is within a specific threshold of a part's surface or bounding box before executing the impulse logic.	72	1	5	2026-01-07 16:58:52.005	2026-01-08 17:10:02.075533	{"views": 72, "content": " I tried to apply impulse at position which is not even a point inside of part. But I still have impulse applied to the part. How? \\n Here is a file: \\n  impulseatposition.rbxl  (57.5 KB) ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-07T16:58:52.005Z"}
223	devforum	4196104	How to code a phone like system in Roblox	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196104	Scripting	Designing an optimized architecture for a UI-based phone simulator, specifically deciding which logic belongs on the server vs. client to minimize network overhead and memory usage.	Shift the majority of game logic to the client side (UI, apps, notifications) to reduce network traffic and CPU load. The server should be used primarily for persistent data storage via DataStoreService (e.g., security PINs). Additionally, for a purely UI-based experience, disable character auto-spawning and minimize Workspace instances to reduce memory usage.	t	intermediate	{ReplicatedStorage,RemoteEvent,Players,DataStoreService,math.clamp,os.time,task.spawn,task.wait}	{}	t	An automated tool could generate a boilerplate for a client-side state management system and provide a standard module for secure server-client communication that only handles persistent data saving/loading.	168	9	14	2025-12-29 18:36:43.688	2026-01-08 17:09:53.422649	{"views": 168, "content": " Hello members of the forum! \\n I recently saw a game on Roblox which is basically a phone system on Roblox where you can actually use a phone \\n Here is it: \\n \\n   \\n       \\n\\n       Roblox \\n   \\n\\n   \\n       \\n\\n  Phone OS [EMULATOR] [💵APP MAKER!]  \\n\\n   This is a single-player game that simulates an Android phone experience — you’re in full control of your virtual device\\n[This is an unofficial emulator/game]\\n\\nStart by powering on your phone, setting it up with a name and background, and then you're... \\n\\n\\n   \\n\\n   \\n    \\n    \\n   \\n\\n    \\n \\n\\n As the title states I want to know how to code a phone that is somewhat like this with things like functioning apps and notifications. \\n I did try making it but I wanted to know if there’s anything I need to add or if you would do something else. \\n My code: \\n  local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal PhoneFolder = ReplicatedStorage:FindFirstChild(\\"Phone\\")\\nif not PhoneFolder then\\n\\tPhoneFolder = Instance.new(\\"Folder\\")\\n\\tPhoneFolder.Name = \\"Phone\\"\\n\\tPhoneFolder.Parent = ReplicatedStorage\\nend\\n\\nlocal function makeRemote(name)\\n\\tlocal r = PhoneFolder:FindFirstChild(name)\\n\\tif not r then\\n\\t\\tr = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\n\\t\\tr.Name = name\\n\\t\\tr.Parent = PhoneFolder\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn r\\nend\\n\\nlocal SendMessage = makeRemote(\\"SendMessage\\")\\nlocal ReceiveMessage = makeRemote(\\"ReceiveMessage\\")\\nlocal BatteryUpdate = makeRemote(\\"BatteryUpdate\\")\\n\\nlocal Profiles = {}\\n\\nlocal function newProfile()\\n\\treturn {\\n\\t\\tBattery = 100,\\n\\t\\tMessages = {},\\n\\t\\tUnlocked = true\\n\\t}\\nend\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tProfiles[player] = newProfile()\\n\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\twhile player.Parent do\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(60)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal profile = Profiles[player]\\n\\t\\t\\tif profile then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tprofile.Battery = math.clamp(profile.Battery - 1, 0, 100)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tBatteryUpdate:FireClient(player, profile.Battery)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend)\\nend)\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tProfiles[player] = nil\\nend)\\n\\nSendMessage.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, targetUserId, text)\\n", "upvotes": 9, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 14, "created_at": "2025-12-29T18:36:43.688Z"}
226	devforum	4217768	Character jittering up and down when moving	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217768	Physics	Character jittering on the Y-axis at high velocities when using VectorForce and AlignOrientation due to friction-induced tilting and physics correction cycles.	\N	f	advanced	{VectorForce,AlignOrientation,PreSimulation,Heartbeat}	{}	t	Implement a raycast-based hover or suspension system to maintain a fixed distance from the ground, or use a PID controller to manage orientation without triggering physics engine bounce.	76	1	4	2026-01-05 07:46:55.893	2026-01-08 17:09:54.944652	{"views": 76, "content": " I am making my own character movement system, and I use  VectorForce  to apply force to the character. \\nWhen the character has lower velocities, like being under 16 studs/second, it moves smoothly. \\nBut once the velocity gets higher and reaches about 15, the character starts to vibrate/jitter up and down. \\nI’ve found out this happens because while moving the bottom part is in contact with the ground, which causes it to tilt slightly forward, and when that happens, its position gets slightly up on the Y axis, and to remove the tilting, I use  AlignOrientation  constraint with rigidity enabled. \\nThe problem with this approach is that  AlignOrientation  with rigidity enabled wont actually lock the rotation of the character but applies force in such a way that the object’s orientation matches the target orientation. \\n So this is what is happening, the contact with the ground slightly tilts the character forward causing its position to get incremented slightly upwards. Then the align orientation constraint makes its rotation back to by applying torque force. \\nBut as the position of the cylinder was incremented previously, the cylinder is slightly above the ground in the next frame, and in the next next frame it comes down, and this process repeats. \\n Isnt there another approach to this? Like in unity we can just tell the game engine to just lock the rotation of an object on a certain axis. \\n This is what i’ve tried so far: \\n \\n Setting the density of the character very high (increases mass) \\n Setting the friction of the character and baseplate to 0 \\n Applying the force on the bottom of the character \\n Forcing the CFrame of the character to have 0 rotation in both the  PreSimulation  and  Heartbeat  (After simulation of the frame is completed) events. \\n \\n All these methods have reduced the jittering by a lot but not completely. \\nHere’s the video, in the last part i show what happens when I disable  AlignOrientation  and as you can see it tilts in the direction of movement", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-05T07:46:55.893Z"}
227	devforum	4215962	How do I filter a text box?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4215962	Scripting	Filtering user-generated text from a TextBox to prevent profanity and ensure compliance with Roblox safety standards for text visible to multiple players.	Use TextService on the server. Call FilterStringAsync with the raw text and the sender's UserId, then call GetChatForUserAsync on the resulting TextFilterResult to get the safe version for public display.	t	beginner	{TextService,FilterStringAsync,GetChatForUserAsync,RemoteEvent,ReplicatedStorage}	{}	t	A coding agent can generate the boilerplate code for a server-side RemoteEvent listener that wraps TextService calls in a pcall for error handling and returns the filtered string.	176	6	18	2026-01-04 17:49:51.212	2026-01-08 17:09:55.81766	{"views": 176, "content": " I’ve been recently working on a system where players can write notes and place them on the ground. This works well but I’m unsure on how to filter the text so that people can’t cuss when writing. ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 18, "created_at": "2026-01-04T17:49:51.212Z"}
229	devforum	4216760	Speed / flying anti-cheat help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4216760	Scripting	Server-side performance degradation in a 40-player server caused by high-frequency (60Hz) per-player CFrame tracking for anti-cheat logic.	Reduce the polling frequency of position checks from 60 times per second to a lower rate, such as 10 times per second, to decrease CPU overhead.	t	intermediate	{CFrame}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the detection loop to use a configurable heartbeat or task.wait interval and implement distance-over-time calculations that are independent of frame rate.	191	3	13	2026-01-04 22:52:10.615	2026-01-08 17:09:58.079096	{"views": 191, "content": " Yo so I spent 13 hours creating an anti-cheat against exploiters who increase their speed or fly really fast. My goal isn’t to 100% eliminate speed exploiting, but to mostly reduce it. \\n Here’s my method: \\n \\n Tracking every player’s CFrame at 60 times a second for up to 2 seconds \\n Compare the distance between the latest and second latest CFrame \\n if movement detected is too fast, add it to a counter that resets every 9 seconds \\n Every 3 seconds check if that counter has reached 90 (because sometimes the system falsely thinks the player moving too fast) \\n Kick them \\n \\n The issue is, in a 40 player server, most players started noticing performance issues because each player who is playing a match is being tracked at 60 FPS. \\n What better ways can I go about this? Is 60 fps too fast? I appreciate all the help I can get. ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2026-01-04T22:52:10.615Z"}
232	devforum	4215991	Make gun follow mouse	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4215991	Scripting	Implementing a system where a character's gun and arms dynamically aim toward the mouse cursor using R15 Inverse Kinematics.	Utilize IKControl instances (LookAt and Rotation types) to link the character's Head and RightHand to an Attachment that is updated every frame to the Mouse.Hit position via RunService.PreRender.	t	intermediate	{IKControl,Attachment,RunService,CFrame.lookAlong,Player:GetMouse,Instance.new}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate the logic to instantiate IKControl objects, define ChainRoot and EndEffector properties, and create a RenderStepped or PreRender connection to update the target attachment's CFrame.	75	2	4	2026-01-04 18:01:03.795	2026-01-08 17:10:00.74801	{"views": 75, "content": " I want to make the gun aim where the mouse aims. \\n Issue is that most approaches i try usually fail or look really weird \\n         image  510×463 48.2 KB         \\n I tried making shoulders face the mouse but it usually failed, didnt work as expected \\n Any help is appreciated ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-04T18:01:03.795Z"}
233	devforum	4216658	Animation doesn't play on NPC with SimplePath	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4216658	Animation	Animations fail to play on NPCs because the Animate script is a LocalScript, which does not execute when placed inside a non-player Character on the server.	Convert the Animate LocalScript into a Server Script (Script) and modify the code to remove client-side dependencies such as LocalPlayer, Chat connections, or UI references that do not exist on the server.	t	beginner	{SimplePath}	{}	t	An automated tool can detect if a LocalScript is childed to a Character model that lacks a corresponding Player object, and suggest converting it to a Server Script while highlighting client-only global variables like game.Players.LocalPlayer.	41	2	3	2026-01-04 22:03:44.298	2026-01-08 17:10:00.979161	{"views": 41, "content": " I recently ran into a problem where the Animate script. Walking, running, and jumping animations do not play on NPCs with SimplePath, and it’s not just a problem with the Animate script — I just can’t get any animations to play on NPCs with SimplePath. \\nHere is my ai script: \\n ai.rbxm  (8,7 КБ) \\nAnd here is my Animate and SimplePath script: \\n Animate.rbxm  (8,5 КБ) \\n SimplePath.rbxm  (6,3 КБ) \\n          image  425×454 24.3 KB         \\n I dont know what to do ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-04T22:03:44.298Z"}
224	devforum	4226487	Is there a way to make server changes in studio while playtesting?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4226487	Networking	Persisting changes made to server-side objects or properties during a Play Solo session in Roblox Studio.	Roblox Studio does not natively support saving changes made during a playtest session back to the edit-time environment; all modifications are reverted when the test ends. Users can toggle views using the 'Current Client/Server' icon or use 'Run' mode for server-only testing.	f	beginner	{}	{}	f	A Studio plugin could be developed to track property changes during a playtest and provide a 'Sync' button to apply those specific values back to the objects in edit mode after the session terminates.	82	5	7	2026-01-07 18:39:46.35	2026-01-08 17:09:53.432904	{"views": 82, "content": " Going back and forth from client to server while playtesting is tedious. Is there a shortcut or a different playtest option? I could have sworn there was a studio feature like this some years back that allowed you to edit the server while in solo play \\n Edit: People are saying they’re confused. Im wondering if there is a test type that allows the changes I make to save without having to toggle between server and client. ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2026-01-07T18:39:46.350Z"}
225	devforum	4211707	How to start freecam on a phone?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4211707	Scripting	Activating the built-in Roblox developer Freecam on mobile devices where the keyboard shortcut (Shift+P) is not available.	Access the Freecam GUI within the PlayerGui and toggle the 'FreecamEnabled' attribute on the FreecamScript. This can be done via a LocalScript that triggers when a UI button is pressed.	t	beginner	{Players.LocalPlayer,PlayerGui,SetAttribute,GetAttribute,WaitForChild}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a utility script that detects if a user is on mobile, then creates a ScreenGui with a toggle button that modifies the 'FreecamEnabled' attribute on the standard Roblox Freecam system.	78	1	3	2026-01-03 11:12:57.007	2026-01-08 17:09:54.702324	{"views": 78, "content": " First, my English isn’t great, so I’ll be using translation tools, and my English might sound a bit off sometimes. \\n On PC, you can activate the official Roblox developer’s Freecam by pressing the Shift and P keys simultaneously. \\nHowever, looking at the script, it seems likely that it’s also possible on mobile devices. (This is because the control method mentions thumbsticks.) \\nSo, how can you use Freecam on a mobile phone? Or is it not possible? ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-03T11:12:57.007Z"}
228	devforum	4230182	Issue with SpringConstraint	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4230182	Physics	Vehicle SpringConstraint suspension incorrectly returns to equilibrium when center of mass is shifted and vehicle is in motion via CylindricalConstraints.	\N	f	intermediate	{SpringConstraint,CylindricalConstraint,PrismaticConstraint}	{}	f	A coding agent could perform automated stress-testing by programmatically adjusting center-of-mass and velocity properties to log suspension compression data for debugging physics anomalies.	50	0	3	2026-01-08 08:21:10.62	2026-01-08 17:09:56.279435	{"views": 50, "content": " Not sure if this is the right category, but I’m having an issue with the spring constraints on my vehicle:  here a clip of the problem  \\n When the center of mass is centered, the suspension behaves correctly. However, when I shift the center of mass by adding parts to the left side, the vehicle tilts left as expected, but then the suspension is strangely pushed back up as if the vehicle were in equilibrium which shouldn’t be possible, since most of the mass is concentrated on the left side. \\n I tried playing with SpringConstraint properties (increasing damping and stiffness) but it didn’t work. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-08T08:21:10.620Z"}
230	devforum	4217021	LocalScript randomly not working	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217021	Scripting	LocalScript not executing reliably or at all because it is parented to a Part in the Workspace.	LocalScripts do not run when placed directly inside Workspace objects (unless they are part of the Player's Character). The logic should be moved to a ServerScript, or the LocalScript should be relocated to StarterPlayerScripts or StarterGui, using RemoteEvents for server-client communication.	t	beginner	{TweenService,Touched,GetPlayerFromCharacter,FireServer,SoundService}	{}	t	Check the parent of LocalScripts; if a LocalScript is found inside a Workspace Part, flag it as a non-executable location and suggest moving it to StarterPlayerScripts or using a ServerScript.	110	1	8	2026-01-05 00:46:46.283	2026-01-08 17:09:59.509238	{"views": 110, "content": " For some reason, a localscript in a part in which touched makes a gui appear, sometimes does not seem to succeed. It seems to have a random chance between executing the action and failing to do so. The script is below: \\n  local TS = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\n\\nscript.Parent.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\\n\\tprint(\\"fired\\")\\n\\tscript.Parent.CanTouch = false\\n\\tif game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(hit.Parent) then\\n\\t\\tlocal player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(hit.Parent)\\n\\t\\tif player.PlayerGui:FindFirstChild(\\"TeleportScreen\\") then else\\n\\t\\t\\tgame.ReplicatedStorage.paint:FireServer()\\n\\t\\t\\tplayer.Character:FindFirstChild(\\"HumanoidRootPart\\").Anchored = true\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"found\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tgame.SoundService.painting:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal clone = script.TeleportScreen:Clone()\\n\\t\\t\\tclone.Parent = player.PlayerGui\\n\\t\\t\\tclone.Enabled = true\\n\\t\\t\\tTS:Create(clone.TextLabel, TweenInfo.new(1), {BackgroundTransparency = 0, TextTransparency = 0}):Play()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\telse print (\\"failed\\")\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  \\n As you can imagine, the console will print “failed” on the times it does not succeed. Is there a solution to this? ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2026-01-05T00:46:46.283Z"}
