235	devforum	4217465	How to place the new procedural generated room? (Position and Rotation)	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217465	Scripting	Properly aligning and offsetting procedurally generated rooms so they connect at waypoints instead of spawning directly on top of the waypoint's center.	\N	f	intermediate	{PivotTo,CFrame,Vector3,GetChildren,ReplicatedStorage}	{}	t	A script could be generated to calculate the offset between a room's 'Entrance' part and its PrimaryPart, then apply that offset to the 'Exit' waypoint's CFrame to ensure seamless alignment.	81	2	6	2026-01-05 04:21:42.707	2026-01-08 17:10:04.192708	{"views": 81, "content": " Trying to make a procedural dungeon generation, but now, how do I make for the new rooms spawn right in front of the waypoint instead of inside of it? \\n  local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal AssetsFolder = ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\\"AssetsFolder\\")\\nlocal Rooms = AssetsFolder:GetChildren()\\n\\nlocal StartPos = Vector3.new(0, 0, 0)\\nlocal MaxRooms = 100\\n\\nprint(Rooms)\\n\\nlocal function Generate(StartPos, MaxRooms)\\n\\n\\tlocal LastRoomGenerated\\n\\n\\t--Spawn First Room\\n\\tlocal StarterRoom = AssetsFolder.StarterRoom:Clone() :: Model\\n\\tStarterRoom.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\n\\ttable.remove(Rooms, table.find(Rooms, StarterRoom))\\n\\n\\tlocal AmountOfRoomsGenerated = 1\\n\\tLastRoomGenerated = StarterRoom\\n\\n\\t--Generation\\t\\n\\twhile AmountOfRoomsGenerated &lt; MaxRooms do\\n\\t\\twait(0.125)\\n\\t\\tfor _, waypoint in LastRoomGenerated:GetChildren() do\\n\\t\\t\\tif waypoint.Name == \\"Waypoints\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal RandomRoom = Rooms[math.random(1, #Rooms)]:Clone() :: Model\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tRandomRoom.Parent = workspace.Generation\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tRandomRoom:PivotTo(waypoint.CFrame)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tAmountOfRoomsGenerated += 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tLastRoomGenerated = RandomRoom\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tprint(\\"done\\")\\nend\\n\\nGenerate(StartPos, MaxRooms)\\n  ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2026-01-05T04:21:42.707Z"}
