267	devforum	4174701	How Lag Compensation Of Projectiles Should Be Handled With Server-Auth?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4174701	Networking	Implementing server-authoritative lag compensation for projectiles (unlike hitscan) using Roblox's server authority system, specifically regarding how to reconcile latency-induced delays through rewind and fast-forward logic without over-taxing server resources.	\N	f	advanced	{"Server Authority"}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a template for a snapshot-based projectile system that implements a rewind buffer for hitboxes and sub-stepping logic to catch up on missed simulation frames based on the client's round-trip time (RTT).	321	5	11	2025-12-22 22:25:46.499	2026-01-08 17:10:37.012675	{"views": 321, "content": " First of all i want to mention i really searched so much but i just find out limited sources/articles about lag compensation for projectiles, and it made me create this post \\n With Robloxs  server auth  system i guess things are deterministic and it should be possible to process rollback/rewind type lag compensations \\n When u want to create a server auth projectiles probably u would look logic of libraries like  SecureCast  and  Chickynoid  then u apply same logic to ur game with robloxs new server auth system everything should be fine right? \\n         image  1011×347 13.9 KB         \\nThere is how networking of that logic would look like, it is possible to reduce delay 2x at end for hit info packet server to shooter client. When u apply this logic at the moment server receives first request it calculates the latency and rewinds the time but there is no fast forward, simulation of server and shooters client never get synced its reason of the problem on that schema \\n This is whats my solution to it: \\n         image  858×419 18.9 KB         \\nThe server processes the  all of snapshots got affected by latency  at the frame receives packet and i guess this would be expensive for server. \\n So why i created this post; i inspired that fast forward logic just by one not solved unity forum post i dont even know this logic exist in real games applying lag compensation for projectiles like overwatch and etc. \\n So whats correct way to implementation of rewind lag compensation for projectiles? ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2025-12-22T22:25:46.499Z"}
268	devforum	4213101	How do I detect if PlayerRemoving is due to server restart?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4213101	Scripting	Distinguishing between a player manually leaving and a server shutdown/restart, because the PlayerRemoving event fires before the game:BindToClose() callback.	Use game:BindToClose() to set a flag or record the server's JobId in a DataStore upon shutdown. When a player joins a new session, check the status of their previous server's JobId to determine if the disconnection was due to a restart.	t	intermediate	{PlayerRemoving,game:BindToClose,DataStore,game.JobId,Enum.CloseReason}	{}	t	Create a boilerplate system that wraps PlayerRemoving logic with a short delay or a check against a 'isShuttingDown' boolean that is set to true immediately inside a BindToClose callback.	85	1	4	2026-01-03 20:40:24.45	2026-01-08 17:10:38.156224	{"views": 85, "content": " I’m trying to detect whether a player left the game due to a server restart. My game is centered around dueling, and players who leave mid-match are punished with losing their win streak, however server restarts run PlayerRemoving before game:BindToClose(), and I’m not sure how to prevent punishing players for server restarts. \\n I’ve already tried game:BindToClose(), storing a variable stating server shut down is true, and then preventing punishing players who are mid-match, however I soon figured out that PlayerRemoving happens before game:BindToClose(), therefore I can’t capture the reason PlayerRemoving happened in the first place. \\n I’ve read more than 5 dev forum posts specifically about this issue, and I can’t find a solution, even with posts that were marked with a solution, and ones specifically about logging and win streaks. I also spent 4 hours attempting solutions and using Roblox’s documentation, without any successful attempts detecting if PlayerRemoving was caused by a server restart. \\n I appreciate any help I can get. ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-03T20:40:24.450Z"}
