pting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-04T02:51:22.488Z"}
314	devforum	4212427	Detect turning with ShiftLock enabled	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212427	Scripting	Detecting player turning for a drifting mechanic consistently across different control schemes (A/D keys vs. ShiftLock/First Person) because Humanoid.MoveDirection remains 0 in ShiftLock mode.	Use RootPart.CFrame:VectorToObjectSpace(Camera.CFrame.LookVector).X to detect the camera's rotation relative to the character, though this may require further normalization to match the magnitude of keyboard input.	f	intermediate	{Humanoid.MoveDirection,CFrame.VectorToObjectSpace,Camera.CFrame,RootPart.CFrame,ControlModule:GetMoveVector}	{}	t	Implement a unified input-handling function that combines Humanoid.MoveDirection for keyboard inputs with the angular velocity or relative camera rotation for ShiftLock/First-Person modes to produce a normalized 'turn' value.	122	3	7	2026-01-03 16:23:12.113	2026-01-08 17:11:28.585177	{"views": 122, "content": " I’m making a sliding game where turning sharply will start a drift, I can already do that with this code. \\n  local MoveDirection = RootPart.CFrame:VectorToObjectSpace(Humanoid.MoveDirection) -- makes it relative to character\\nlocal MoveDirectionX = MoveDirection.X\\nif MoveDirectionX &gt;= 0.55 then -- Drift Right\\n\\t-- drift right code\\nelseif MoveDirectionX &lt;= -0.55 then -- Drift Left\\n\\t-- drift left code\\nend\\n  \\n Issue is, trying to use this code with first person/shiftlock will make the MoveDirectionX result in nothing being outputted (0). \\nI’ve tried ControlModule:GetMoveVector() as of now, is there a way to make the code above work with ShiftLock/First Person? \\nA and D inputs work just fine, it’s only moving and turning with shiftlock/first person that doesn’t get detected. ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2026-01-03T16:23:12.113Z"}
