320	devforum	4212848	HELPPP | URGENT Help Needed on a Universal Way to Detect NPC and Client Context For Special Moves	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212848	Scripting	Designing a universal context-detection system for combat finishers (downslam, uppercut, or normal attack) that functions for both players (via input/state) and NPCs (via state/AI logic).	\N	f	intermediate	{TweenService,ReplicatedStorage,Players,Humanoid,CFrame,Enum.EasingStyle}	{}	t	A coding agent could create a Context-Provider abstraction layer that checks the Humanoid's FloorMaterial for 'airborne' status and queries a shared StateManager or an 'InputBuffer' table to determine if the agent (NPC or Player) intended a Jump action during the attack sequence.	176	8	20	2026-01-03 18:59:44.513	2026-01-08 17:11:35.571755	{"views": 176, "content": " So I’m helping develop a battlegrounds game yes. As I’m not that of an experienced scripter, I’ve come across some issues with input tracking. I’m trying to make a system where on the last attack of the sequence (an M1), you are airborne, you perform a downslam. Similarly, if you were holding jump before the last attack sequence, you perform an uppercut. However, if you meet none of these requirements, then the normal attack will play. \\n For more context, different characters have different special moves and requirements to meet them, however, most of them relate to input and state changes. \\n Furthermore, I’ve been brainstorming ways to make this compatible with NPC’S and mobile players. Thank you in advance   \\n Here is my pre-existing code: \\n  --// Services //\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\nlocal TweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")   \\n\\n--// Folders //\\nlocal RepMods = ReplicatedStorage.Modules\\n\\tlocal Manage = RepMods.Management\\n\\tlocal RepUtils = RepMods.Utilities\\n\\t\\tlocal CoreRUtils = RepUtils.Core\\n\\tlocal CombatMods = RepMods.Combat\\n\\tlocal VelocityMods = RepMods.Velocity\\n\\t\\n\\t\\n--// Modules //\\nlocal Chrono = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"Chrono\\"))\\nlocal AnimationManager = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"AnimationManager\\"))\\nlocal StateManager = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"StateManager\\"))\\nlocal ComboManager = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"ComboManager\\"))\\nlocal CooldownManager = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"CooldownManager\\"))\\nlocal ValueManager = require(Manage:WaitForChild(\\"ValueManager\\"))\\n\\nlocal CombatUtility = require(CoreRUtils:WaitForChild(\\"CombatUtility\\"))\\n\\nlocal HitboxClass = require(CombatMods:WaitForChild(\\"HitboxClass\\"))\\nlocal HealthModule = require(CombatMods:WaitForChild(\\"HealthModule\\"))\\n\\nlocal RagdollModule = require(VelocityMods:WaitForChild(\\"RagdollModule\\"))\\nlocal VelocityModule = require(VelocityMods:WaitForChild(\\"VelocityModule\\"))\\n\\n--// Configs //\\nlocal highlightTween = Tween", "upvotes": 8, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 20, "created_at": "2026-01-03T18:59:44.513Z"}
