341	devforum	4153065	Whats the best way to make hitboxes?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4153065	Networking	Server-side hitbox delay and spatial misalignment due to network latency versus the security risks of client-side hitboxes in fast-paced combat.	Perform hitbox detection on the client side (using Spatial Query or Raycasting) to ensure responsiveness, then send the result to the server for validation (checking distance, cooldowns, and line-of-sight) to mitigate exploitation.	t	intermediate	{GetPartsinPart,WorldRoot:Raycast}	{}	t	A coding agent can generate a boilerplate system that uses a RemoteEvent to bridge a client-side hitbox detection (using GetPartsinPart) with a server-side validation script that checks the Magnitude between the attacker and victim.	218	2	8	2025-12-15 01:24:31.387	2026-01-08 17:11:57.558739	{"views": 218, "content": " I’m not bad at coding, but if there’s one thing I hate it’s 100% hitboxes. I know how to use GetPartsinPart and those functions, but my issue is, when create hitboxes on the server there’s delay due to ping like when you’re moving, or rotating, the hitbox will spawn not according to your current CFrame, which makes it behind you or in a previous position according to your ping. My original solution was to do it through the client, which handles creating the hitbox, target detection, and everything that doesn’t include changing values like damage. Doing it the client way is OBVIOUSLY unsafe because exploiters can hack it pretty easily, due to it being on the client. So what I’m asking is: \\nWhat’s the best way to make hitboxes, with as little delay as possible (or no delay at all), while also being safe from exploiters. Also if you could please lmk if your way is optimised. \\nI’m making a fighting game and this will be for combat, abilities and such. ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2025-12-15T01:24:31.387Z"}
