tats and leaderstats:FindFirstChild(\\"Seconds Ruled\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif kingSeconds then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tkingSeconds.Value += 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayersRewarded[player] = true\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayer:AddTag(\\"King\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t-- Remove King tag from players no longer on throne\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, player in pairs(game.Players:GetPlayers()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif player:HasTag(\\"King\\") and not playersRewarded[player] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplayer:RemoveTag(\\"King\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n (ignore it not counting anymore I had an error) ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-06T00:58:33.757Z"}
378	devforum	4219878	Single Remote Event & Function Networking	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4219878	Networking	Assessing the efficiency and best practices of using a centralized networking architecture with a single RemoteEvent and RemoteFunction versus multiple instances.	A single bridge is generally acceptable; however, for high-frequency traffic, developers should consider using multiple events and ensuring data packets are small and compact to minimize overhead.	t	intermediate	{RemoteEvent,RemoteFunction,RunService,ReplicatedStorage,FireClient,FireServer,InvokeServer}	{"ClientBind can only be called from client"}	t	An automated agent can generate this type of boilerplate networking wrapper or suggest optimized serialization techniques (like using buffers or bit-packing) to minimize the payload size of the single remote.	56	1	2	2026-01-05 23:23:50.625	2026-01-08 17:12:34.728253	{"views": 56, "content": " I have a question regarding networking in Roblox. Is it a good practice to handle all server–client and client–server communication through a single  RemoteEvent  and  RemoteFunction ? \\n Below is a custom networking module I created to handle interactions between client &amp; server &amp; server to client. \\n Both the server and clients can register  “binds” , which act as named route associated with callback functions. \\n For example, if a client registers a bind called  \\"UpdateXPVisuals\\" , the server can invoke it as follows: \\n  --Server \\nNetwork.Push(Player, \\"UpdateXPVisuals\\", {PlayerXPData}\\n\\n--Clients can react by doing--\\nNetwork.ClientBind(\\"UpdateXPVisuals\\", function(Data)\\n\\t\\t--some visual effect here--\\n\\tend)\\n\\n  \\n  local RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal Network = {}\\nNetwork.RATE_LIMIT = 20 --calls per route\\nNetwork.RATE_WINDOW = 1\\nNetwork.RATE_LIMITER = {}\\n\\nNetwork.Routes = { --server specific\\n\\t\\n}\\n\\nNetwork.ClientRoutes = {\\n\\t\\n}\\n\\n\\nlocal EventsFolder = ReplicatedStorage:FindFirstChild(\\"Events\\")\\n\\n\\n\\nlocal RemoteEvent = EventsFolder:FindFirstChild(\\"NetworkEvent\\")\\nlocal RemoteFunction = EventsFolder:FindFirstChild(\\"NetworkFunction\\")\\n\\n\\nif RunService:IsServer() then\\n\\tif not RemoteEvent then\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent.Name = \\"NetworkEvent\\"\\n\\t\\tRemoteEvent.Parent = EventsFolder\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tif not RemoteFunction then\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction = Instance.new(\\"RemoteFunction\\")\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction.Name = \\"NetworkFunction\\"\\n\\t\\tRemoteFunction.Parent = EventsFolder\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\n\\nNetwork.RemoteEvent = RemoteEvent\\nNetwork.RemoteFunction = RemoteFunction\\n\\n\\n\\n-- SERVER ONLY: bind a route \\n--where we define the routes/functionalities\\nfunction Network.ServerBind(name : string, callback )\\n\\tNetwork.Routes[name] = callback\\nend\\n\\n\\nfunction Network.ClientBind(name: string, callback)\\n\\tif RunService:IsServer() then\\n\\t\\terror(\\"ClientBind can only be called from client\\")\\n\\tend\\n\\tNetwork.ClientRoutes[name] = callback", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-05T23:23:50.625Z"}
