396	devforum	4212394	Server > client replication and re-replication help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212394	Networking	Selective client-side replication and memory management to optimize mobile performance by loading and unloading server-side objects (bases, maps, units) dynamically.	Use StreamingEnabled to allow the engine to automatically manage the loading and unloading of regions based on memory pressure and proximity, or implement a manual system using RemoteEvents to trigger client-side local instantiation while keeping logic on the server.	f	advanced	{StreamingEnabled}	{}	t	An agent could generate a framework that manages 'Object Pools' on the client, where the server sends data via RemoteEvents and the client instantiates/destroys high-detail assets while the server maintains low-detail hitboxes for verification.	77	0	2	2026-01-03 16:07:52.605	2026-01-08 17:12:56.129072	{"views": 77, "content": " I want to minimize the memory usage in my game for the client. Each client is going to have their own set of maps and a base, and I want each client to have 1 map and base in memory at a time. \\nThis means if client1 goes to the base of client2, then the memory of client1 base dissapears from client1’s memory. However, it stays on the server. \\nThen, once client1 goes back to his base, client1 gets rid of client2 base memory and re-replicates his base. \\nSame for the maps, monsters, units, etc. \\n If I don’t do this, then each client has to render and save in memory: 6 bases, 6 maps and 6 armies of enemies and units. Too much for mobile devices. \\n Other games manage to do things like Hide other’s units, or bee swarm simulator has a Hide other bees option, which works exactly how I need it to work. \\nHow is this done? \\n Yes, I looked for a solution, but I didn’t manage to find the solution. I have no idea how to approach this. \\nCreating things on the client would work, but then the server can’t verify if the client is not \\nexploiting. \\nI could create things on the server and then delete them for the clients that don’t need it, \\nbut once a client needs it that thing has to be recreated on the server, because I don’t think \\nthere’s a way to just re-replicate something from server &gt; client. \\n Keep in mind I don’t want a system that just hides things. That does not fix the memory issue. \\n Also, I’m not asking for an entire system or script. I just want to know how to approach this, then I can design and script everything myself. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-03T16:07:52.605Z"}
397	devforum	4217625	Delays and latency issues when trying to censor words live	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217625	Networking	High latency and performance overhead caused by frequent RemoteEvent firing and redundant TextService API calls during live text filtering.	Use GetNonChatStringForBroadcastAsync for live updates instead of per-user filtering, and implement rate limiting (throttling/debouncing) to prevent firing remotes on every single keystroke.	t	intermediate	{TextService,FilterStringAsync,GetNonChatStringForUserAsync,GetNonChatStringForBroadcastAsync,RemoteEvent,UserInputService}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the input handling logic to include a debounce variable or a timestamp-based check to limit RemoteEvent firing to a specific frequency (e.g., every 0.2 seconds).	81	3	3	2026-01-05 06:04:03.998	2026-01-08 17:12:56.24471	{"views": 81, "content": "  Heya, i’ve been working on game with a similar “word on screen system” to “Last Letter” or “Word Bomb” where one player is typing, while the others can see what they are typing live with filtration.  \\n  This has however lead to a LOT of lag and latency in my game. The problem is clearly that i’m sending way too much information between clients, but i don’t exactly know what way to fix it.  \\n  Local Script that handles the typing:  \\n  censorWordEvent2.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(word)\\n\\t\\n\\tprint(\\"Filtered word: \\"..word)\\n\\tfor i,v in pairs(wordFrame:GetChildren()) do\\n\\n\\t\\tif v:IsA(\\"TextLabel\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tv:Destroy()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tfor i = 1,string.len(word) do\\n\\n\\t\\tlocal templateClone = letterTemplate:Clone()\\n\\t\\ttemplateClone.Text = word:sub(i,i)\\n\\t\\ttemplateClone.Parent = script.Parent.Frame\\n\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n\\nfunction checkWord()\\n\\tcensorWordEvent:FireServer(currentWord)\\n\\t\\nend\\n\\nuserInputService.InputBegan:Connect(function(input)\\n\\t\\n\\tif plr.Character:FindFirstChild(\\"Guesser\\") and plr.Character:FindFirstChild(\\"Guesser\\").Value == true then\\n\\t\\tif (input.KeyCode).Name == \\"Backspace\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\tcurrentWord = currentWord:sub(1,-2)\\n\\t\\t\\tcheckWord()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif (input.KeyCode).Name == \\"Return\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\tcheckWord()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\tfor i,v in pairs(letterMap) do\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tif (input.KeyCode).Name == v then\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcurrentWord = currentWord..v\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcheckWord()\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\nend)\\n\\nshowLettersEvent2.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(word)\\n\\t\\n\\tcurrentWord = word\\n\\tcheckWord(true)\\n\\t\\nend)\\n  \\n  Game script that receives and sends back information:  \\n  showLettersEvent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(plr, currentWord)\\n\\t\\n\\tfor i,v in pairs(plrs) do\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif v ~= plr then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tshowLettersEvent2:FireClient(game.Players:FindFirstChild(v.Name), currentWord)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\nend)\\n\\ncensorWordEvent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(plr, word)\\n\\tlocal filterSuccess, filterResult = pcall(function()\\n\\t\\treturn textService:FilterStringAsync(word, plr.UserId)\\n\\tend)\\n\\n\\tif not filterSuccess then\\n\\t\\tprint(\\"Filtering failed\\")\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tloc", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-05T06:04:03.998Z"}
