do\\n\\tlocal s, m = pcall(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal mod = require(Module)\\n\\t\\tmod:Load()\\n\\tend)\\n\\n\\tif not s then\\n\\t\\twarn(`Error loading module {Module.Name}: {m}`)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n  The rate for this script rose to over 400,000/s and never stopped rising.  \\n The timing systems involve position roughly 150 parts around the track, that when a player touches them, it stores this in the user’s CarData. All car data is controlled in one module script, Data, whose structure looks like this: \\n  local Data = {\\n\\tCars = {},\\n\\t\\n\\tAuthorized = {\\n\\t\\t1382359571,\\n\\t\\t-1,\\n\\t\\t-2\\n\\t},\\n\\t\\n\\tCarTemplate = {\\n\\t\\tTeamName = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarClass = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarNumber = nil,\\n\\t\\tCarName = nil,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tCarModel = nil,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tDriving = nil,\\n\\t\\tSessionFinished = false,\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tMembers = {},\\n\\t\\tAvailableMembers = {},\\n\\t},\\n}\\n\\nlocal Utils = require(workspace.Systems.Utils)\\nlocal", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 12, "created_at": "2026-01-03T19:57:00.910Z"}
