414	devforum	4210353	RBXScriptSignal optimization help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4210353	Scripting	Optimizing signal connections by manually wrapping multiple callbacks into a single RBXScriptSignal:Connect listener to reduce perceived performance overhead.	Standard Roblox event connections are highly optimized and generally do not require manual multiplexing. Using a single connection to iterate through a table of callbacks is redundant unless a specific execution priority (sorting) is required. The use of task.spawn within the listener in the example is also likely unnecessary.	t	intermediate	{RBXScriptSignal,Humanoid.Died,task.spawn,Connect}	{}	t	An agent could provide a standardized signal management pattern or refactor redundant manual callback loops back into idiomatic RBXScriptSignal connections when optimization is not actually needed.	143	5	7	2026-01-03 00:30:40.841	2026-01-08 17:13:13.707356	{"views": 143, "content": " I am creating a singleton module for the player, where I am planning to make a single connection to execute several functions placed in a table, so that it is not necessary to make multiple connections. Would this be a good way to solve this problem? \\n Example: \\n  \\tself._internalPlayerConnections.HumanoidDied = self.Humanoid.Died:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, Callbacks in self.PlayerConnections.HumanoidDied do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tCallbacks()\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\tend)  \\n  ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2026-01-03T00:30:40.841Z"}
