424	devforum	4217768	Character jittering up and down when moving	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217768	Physics	Character jittering and vibrating up and down at high velocities when using VectorForce for movement, caused by collision-induced tilting and subsequent correction by AlignOrientation.	\N	f	advanced	{VectorForce,AlignOrientation,PreSimulation,Heartbeat}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest implementing a 'floating capsule' approach using Raycasts to maintain a specific height above the ground, preventing physical contact with the baseplate and avoiding the tilt-correction loop.	76	1	4	2026-01-05 07:46:55.893	2026-01-08 17:13:25.646404	{"views": 76, "content": " I am making my own character movement system, and I use  VectorForce  to apply force to the character. \\nWhen the character has lower velocities, like being under 16 studs/second, it moves smoothly. \\nBut once the velocity gets higher and reaches about 15, the character starts to vibrate/jitter up and down. \\nI’ve found out this happens because while moving the bottom part is in contact with the ground, which causes it to tilt slightly forward, and when that happens, its position gets slightly up on the Y axis, and to remove the tilting, I use  AlignOrientation  constraint with rigidity enabled. \\nThe problem with this approach is that  AlignOrientation  with rigidity enabled wont actually lock the rotation of the character but applies force in such a way that the object’s orientation matches the target orientation. \\n So this is what is happening, the contact with the ground slightly tilts the character forward causing its position to get incremented slightly upwards. Then the align orientation constraint makes its rotation back to by applying torque force. \\nBut as the position of the cylinder was incremented previously, the cylinder is slightly above the ground in the next frame, and in the next next frame it comes down, and this process repeats. \\n Isnt there another approach to this? Like in unity we can just tell the game engine to just lock the rotation of an object on a certain axis. \\n This is what i’ve tried so far: \\n \\n Setting the density of the character very high (increases mass) \\n Setting the friction of the character and baseplate to 0 \\n Applying the force on the bottom of the character \\n Forcing the CFrame of the character to have 0 rotation in both the  PreSimulation  and  Heartbeat  (After simulation of the frame is completed) events. \\n \\n All these methods have reduced the jittering by a lot but not completely. \\nHere’s the video, in the last part i show what happens when I disable  AlignOrientation  and as you can see it tilts in the direction of movement", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-05T07:46:55.893Z"}
427	devforum	4217904	What could be causing the strange behavior of the hit box?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4217904	Scripting	Inconsistent hitbox registration and latency issues when using .Touched events triggered by AnimationTrack:GetMarkerReachedSignal on the server.	\N	f	intermediate	{GetMarkerReachedSignal,Touched,WeldConstraint,TweenService,Debris,CFrame,LoadAnimation}	{}	t	Suggest replacing the .Touched logic with spatial query APIs like WorldRoot:GetPartBoundsInBox or WorldRoot:GetPartsInPart, and advise on handling animation markers on the client for visual responsiveness while validating on the server.	62	2	3	2026-01-05 09:27:11.092	2026-01-08 17:13:26.066278	{"views": 62, "content": "  Hello! What could be the reason for the hit box malfunction?  The hit box constantly captures the player with different delays, either later or earlier, even though the code is the same? \\n(Or is it a problem with weld?)   \\n The video clearly shows how it works \\n https://youtu.be/f83xpDOQvpc  \\n I don’t quite understand the reason for this, but it might be because the hitbox appears due to the Marker in the animation? \\n Here is a small part of the script \\n  Anim:GetMarkerReachedSignal(\\"Hit\\"):Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal function ReddLines(character)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal fine1 = Tool.VFX[\\"fine...1\\"]:Clone()\\n\\t\\t\\tfine1.Parent = workspace.Assets\\n\\t\\t\\tfine1.CFrame = character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame * CFrame.new(0,-1,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor i, particle in pairs(fine1:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif particle:IsA(\\"ParticleEmitter\\") and particle.Name ~= \\"constantowindo\\" and particle.Name ~= \\"smoksmokenable\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tspawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle:Emit(particle:GetAttribute(\\"EmitCount\\"))\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle.Enabled = true\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(0.3)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor i, particle in pairs(fine1:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif particle:IsA(\\"ParticleEmitter\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle.Enabled = false\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\tgame.Debris:AddItem(fine1, 2)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal function Smoke(character)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal fine1 = Tool.VFX[\\"fine...1\\"]:Clone()\\n\\t\\t\\tfine1.Parent = workspace.Assets\\n\\t\\t\\tfine1.CFrame = character.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame * CFrame.new(0,-1,0)\\n\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor i, particle in pairs(fine1:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif particle:IsA(\\"ParticleEmitter\\") and (particle.Name == \\"constantowindo\\" or particle.Name == \\"smoksmokenable\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tspawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle:Emit(particle:GetAttribute(\\"EmitCount\\"))\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle.Enabled = true\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(0.3)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor i, particle in pairs(fine1:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif particle:IsA(\\"ParticleEmitter\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tparticle.Enabled = false\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\tgame.Debris:AddItem(f", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-05T09:27:11.092Z"}
430	devforum	4215962	How do I filter a text box?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4215962	Scripting	How to filter user-inputted text from a TextBox to prevent profanity in a multiplayer environment	Use TextService:FilterStringAsync on the server. When a client submits text via a RemoteEvent, wrap the TextService call in a pcall for safety, then use GetChatForUserAsync on the returned FilterResult to obtain the cleaned string for display.	t	beginner	{TextService,TextService:FilterStringAsync,TextFilterResult:GetChatForUserAsync,RemoteEvent,ReplicatedStorage}	{"Error filtering text: "}	t	An agent can generate the standard boilerplate for server-side text filtering, including the required pcall handling and RemoteEvent listener setup.	176	6	18	2026-01-04 17:49:51.212	2026-01-08 17:13:30.460028	{"views": 176, "content": " I’ve been recently working on a system where players can write notes and place them on the ground. This works well but I’m unsure on how to filter the text so that people can’t cuss when writing. ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 18, "created_at": "2026-01-04T17:49:51.212Z"}
431	devforum	4216760	Speed / flying anti-cheat help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4216760	Scripting	Performance degradation in a 40-player server caused by high-frequency (60 FPS) per-player CFrame tracking and distance calculations for anti-cheat logic.	Reduce the sampling frequency from 60 times a second to a lower rate, such as 10 times a second, to decrease CPU load while still detecting movement anomalies over time.	t	intermediate	{CFrame}	{}	t	An agent can refactor high-frequency loops into throttled checks using task.wait() or RunService.Heartbeat with a modulus operator to perform logic every Nth frame.	191	3	13	2026-01-04 22:52:10.615	2026-01-08 17:13:30.828159	{"views": 191, "content": " Yo so I spent 13 hours creating an anti-cheat against exploiters who increase their speed or fly really fast. My goal isn’t to 100% eliminate speed exploiting, but to mostly reduce it. \\n Here’s my method: \\n \\n Tracking every player’s CFrame at 60 times a second for up to 2 seconds \\n Compare the distance between the latest and second latest CFrame \\n if movement detected is too fast, add it to a counter that resets every 9 seconds \\n Every 3 seconds check if that counter has reached 90 (because sometimes the system falsely thinks the player moving too fast) \\n Kick them \\n \\n The issue is, in a 40 player server, most players started noticing performance issues because each player who is playing a match is being tracked at 60 FPS. \\n What better ways can I go about this? Is 60 fps too fast? I appreciate all the help I can get. ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2026-01-04T22:52:10.615Z"}
432	devforum	4216658	Animation doesn't play on NPC with SimplePath	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4216658	Animation	Animations fail to play on an NPC because the Animate script is a LocalScript, which does not execute for non-player characters on the server.	Convert the Animate LocalScript into a server-side Script and remove client-only references such as LocalPlayer and Chat connections that cause errors on the server.	t	beginner	{SimplePath,Animate}	{}	t	A linter or plugin could detect LocalScripts placed inside NPC models in the workspace and suggest converting them to Scripts, or automatically provide a server-compatible boilerplate for the default Roblox Animate script.	41	2	3	2026-01-04 22:03:44.298	2026-01-08 17:13:31.234099	{"views": 41, "content": " I recently ran into a problem where the Animate script. Walking, running, and jumping animations do not play on NPCs with SimplePath, and it’s not just a problem with the Animate script — I just can’t get any animations to play on NPCs with SimplePath. \\nHere is my ai script: \\n ai.rbxm  (8,7 КБ) \\nAnd here is my Animate and SimplePath script: \\n Animate.rbxm  (8,5 КБ) \\n SimplePath.rbxm  (6,3 КБ) \\n          image  425×454 24.3 KB         \\n I dont know what to do ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-04T22:03:44.298Z"}
422	devforum	4211811	Help with CFrames	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4211811	Scripting	Incorrect calculation of world coordinates after rotating a relative point around a pivot, specifically failing to transform the relative CFrame back into world space after applying the rotation.	\N	f	intermediate	{CFrame.Angles,CFrame.new,ToObjectSpace,math.rad,math.round}	{}	t	A coding agent could identify that the current math `targetCFrame * originCFrame:ToObjectSpace(pointCFrame)` only calculates a rotated offset; it needs to be multiplied by the `originCFrame` on the left to return the point to world space, or use the formula: `originCFrame * targetCFrame * originCFrame:Inverse() * pointCFrame`.	73	0	1	2026-01-03 11:56:58.656	2026-01-08 17:13:20.688855	{"views": 73, "content": " I am working on an algorithm and as always, I have problems with CFrames, so: \\n  \\tlocal function rotatePiece(piece, turningPoint, rotation)\\n\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\tif rotation == 0 then return end\\n\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\tlocal newPoints = {}\\n\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\tfor i, point in piece.points do\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tif point == turningPoint then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tnewPoints[i] = point\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal targetCFrame = CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(rotation), 0)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal originCFrame = CFrame.new(turningPoint.x, 0, turningPoint.z)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal pointCFrame = CFrame.new(point.x, 0, point.z)\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal newCFrame = targetCFrame * originCFrame:ToObjectSpace(pointCFrame)\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"--\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\twarn(point.x, point.z)\\n\\t\\t\\twarn(newCFrame.X, newCFrame.Z)\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"--\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\t\\tnewPoints[i] = {x = math.round(newCFrame.Position.X), z = math.round(newCFrame.Position.Z)}\\n\\t\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t--\\n\\t\\tpiece.points = newPoints\\n\\t\\t--\\n\\tend\\n  \\n piece is a combination of points and each point is a table with a x and z value. \\nthe turningpoint is one of the points from the piece where the rotation is based of, in this case its the top left one. \\n This is what happens with 90 degrees: \\n         image  1038×532 30.8 KB         \\nThis is what normally happens with 0 degrees: \\n         image  1032×534 28.7 KB         \\n I can provide more things if needed, but I just wanted to keep it short. \\n Thank you for reading and any help would be much appreciated, have a great day or night! ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2026-01-03T11:56:58.656Z"}
423	devforum	4194905	Script plays only 1 audio when 2 should be played	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194905	Scripting	Logic error in selecting random children where non-Sound objects (like the script itself) or reverb-specific sound instances can be selected, leading to incorrect string concatenation and playback failure.	\N	f	beginner	{GetChildren,IsA,FindFirstChild,Play,Ended}	{}	t	Refactor the selection logic to first filter GetChildren() into a table containing only the base Sound objects (excluding scripts and sounds with the 'Reverb' suffix) before applying math.random.	199	3	6	2025-12-29 10:11:19.512	2026-01-08 17:13:22.122947	{"views": 199, "content": "  local songs = script.Parent\\n\\nwhile wait() do\\n\\tfor i, song in pairs(songs:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\tif song:IsA(\\"Sound\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal randomNo = math.random(1, #songs:GetChildren())\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal randomSong = songs:GetChildren()[randomNo]\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal randomSongMuffled = songs:FindFirstChild(randomSong.Name..\\"Reverb\\")\\n\\t\\t\\trandomSong:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\trandomSongMuffled:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\trandomSong.Ended:Wait()\\n\\t\\t\\trandomSongMuffled.Ended:Wait()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n Hi all, this is a script I have in which I want “randomSong” and “randomSongMuffled” to be played at the same time, however this doesn’t seem to work properly, only “randomSongMuffled” plays and “randomSong” does not. I don’t really script so I would appreciate if someone could help me with this. ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-12-29T10:11:19.512Z"}
425	devforum	4196104	How to code a phone like system in Roblox	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196104	Scripting	Optimizing a UI-based phone system architecture to minimize network traffic and server load in Roblox.	Shift the majority of the logic to the client side (LocalScripts) since the system is primarily UI-driven. Use RemoteEvents only for persistent data like PIN storage via DataStoreService or essential cross-player communication. Additionally, disable character spawning and clear the Workspace to reduce memory and CPU usage if the game is purely an emulator.	t	intermediate	{ReplicatedStorage,RemoteEvent,Players,DataStoreService,math.clamp,task.spawn,os.time}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the existing server-side messaging and battery logic into a client-side state management system, while setting up a standardized boilerplate for 'Apps' as modular UI components.	168	9	14	2025-12-29 18:36:43.688	2026-01-08 17:13:25.682389	{"views": 168, "content": " Hello members of the forum! \\n I recently saw a game on Roblox which is basically a phone system on Roblox where you can actually use a phone \\n Here is it: \\n \\n   \\n       \\n\\n       Roblox \\n   \\n\\n   \\n       \\n\\n  Phone OS [EMULATOR] [💵APP MAKER!]  \\n\\n   This is a single-player game that simulates an Android phone experience — you’re in full control of your virtual device\\n[This is an unofficial emulator/game]\\n\\nStart by powering on your phone, setting it up with a name and background, and then you're... \\n\\n\\n   \\n\\n   \\n    \\n    \\n   \\n\\n    \\n \\n\\n As the title states I want to know how to code a phone that is somewhat like this with things like functioning apps and notifications. \\n I did try making it but I wanted to know if there’s anything I need to add or if you would do something else. \\n My code: \\n  local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal PhoneFolder = ReplicatedStorage:FindFirstChild(\\"Phone\\")\\nif not PhoneFolder then\\n\\tPhoneFolder = Instance.new(\\"Folder\\")\\n\\tPhoneFolder.Name = \\"Phone\\"\\n\\tPhoneFolder.Parent = ReplicatedStorage\\nend\\n\\nlocal function makeRemote(name)\\n\\tlocal r = PhoneFolder:FindFirstChild(name)\\n\\tif not r then\\n\\t\\tr = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\n\\t\\tr.Name = name\\n\\t\\tr.Parent = PhoneFolder\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn r\\nend\\n\\nlocal SendMessage = makeRemote(\\"SendMessage\\")\\nlocal ReceiveMessage = makeRemote(\\"ReceiveMessage\\")\\nlocal BatteryUpdate = makeRemote(\\"BatteryUpdate\\")\\n\\nlocal Profiles = {}\\n\\nlocal function newProfile()\\n\\treturn {\\n\\t\\tBattery = 100,\\n\\t\\tMessages = {},\\n\\t\\tUnlocked = true\\n\\t}\\nend\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tProfiles[player] = newProfile()\\n\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\twhile player.Parent do\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(60)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal profile = Profiles[player]\\n\\t\\t\\tif profile then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tprofile.Battery = math.clamp(profile.Battery - 1, 0, 100)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tBatteryUpdate:FireClient(player, profile.Battery)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend)\\nend)\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tProfiles[player] = nil\\nend)\\n\\nSendMessage.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, targetUserId, text)\\n", "upvotes": 9, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 14, "created_at": "2025-12-29T18:36:43.688Z"}
426	devforum	2324460	HttpError: NetFail error	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/2324460	Networking	Intermittent 'HttpError: NetFail' when making HTTP requests from Roblox to an external Express.js server hosted on DigitalOcean, potentially related to DNS propagation or SSL certificate trust.	\N	f	intermediate	{HttpService}	{"HttpError: NetFail"}	t	A coding agent could implement a robust wrapper for HttpService that includes exponential backoff retry logic and diagnostic logging to identify if the failure correlates with specific DNS endpoints or certificate validation issues.	1234	0	3	2023-05-08 21:38:08.97	2026-01-08 17:13:25.943681	{"views": 1234, "content": " Hey all, \\n I currently host an express.js web server using DigitalOcean for database, bot, and leaderboard purposes. Recently my game went live, but randomly it’ll report this error. I’m not sure what this means, and no where on the Roblox website or documentation does it mention what exactly this is. The URL is purchased through namecheap, and I even purchased their “premium” DNS, so I’m confused what the deal is. \\n   \\n Interestingly enough, this same host/website is used as a proxy for sending my discord webhooks. So it’s failing on one endpoint, but working when sending the report? There’s no errors on the web server side, so what do I do? ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2023-05-08T21:38:08.970Z"}
428	devforum	4211145	What does an InputBinding with KeyCode set to `Unknown` do?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4211145	Scripting	Uncertainty regarding the behavior of Enum.KeyCode.Unknown when assigned to an InputBinding within the Roblox Input Action System (IAS), specifically whether it acts as an 'unbound' state or captures specific inputs.	\N	f	intermediate	{InputBinding,Enum.KeyCode.Unknown,UserInputService,InputObject,InputAction}	{}	t	A script could be written to programmatically create an InputBinding with KeyCode.Unknown and listen for triggers across all UserInputTypes to empirically determine if any input fires the associated action.	71	3	4	2026-01-03 06:11:47.333	2026-01-08 17:13:27.531038	{"views": 71, "content": " I’m trying to use more IAS in my projects, however I can’t find documentation on the specifics of how an InputBinding with KeyCode set to  Enum.KeyCode.Unknown  behaves. My assumption, in part because “Unknown” is the default value of KeyCode and this property is not allowed to be  nil , is that it renders the InputBinding inert -  whatever InputAction this InputBinding is a child of will not react whatsoever to any input ever . \\n I’m seeking clarification on this assumption because I’m wondering if “Unknown” is essentially equivalent to “unbound” / “not set” in the context of an in-experience settings menu that allows for user-modifiable bindings to various gameplay actions. If anyone is aware of any documentation, forum information, or personal experience that supports or contradicts my assumption, I’d appreciate it. Thanks! ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-03T06:11:47.333Z"}
429	devforum	4211267	Viewmodel sway that rotates with the camera, Sort of like bodycam	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4211267	Scripting	Implementing rotational viewmodel sway that mimics a bodycam effect, specifically rotating the viewmodel's CFrame based on camera movement rather than just translating its position.	\N	f	intermediate	{UserInputService,CFrame,Vector3,HumanoidRootPart}	{}	t	A coding agent could solve this by calculating a rotation offset using CFrame.Angles (typically using the X and Y mouse delta values passed through a spring) and multiplying it with the Viewmodel's base CFrame.	66	1	1	2026-01-03 07:12:34.598	2026-01-08 17:13:29.967572	{"views": 66, "content": " Hello, how would you create a Viewmodel sway that rotates with the camera if that makes sense. Sort of like in this video,  Sway demo  \\n Whenever they turn their camera, their viewmodel rotates and stays in that angle depending on where you are looking. Currently I’m using springs for the bobbing. \\n  if Springs.Bobbing and Springs.Sway and Root then\\n        \\n        local Bobble = Vector3.new(GetBobbing(6), GetBobbing(10), GetBobbing(1))\\n        \\n        local MouseDelta = UserInputService:GetMouseDelta()\\n        local MouseDeltaX = MouseDelta.X\\n        local MouseDeltaY = MouseDelta.Y\\n        \\n        -- Shove Springs --\\n        \\n        Springs.Bobbing:shove(Bobble / 5 * (Root.Velocity.Magnitude) / Bobbing_Division)\\n        Springs.Sway:shove(Vector3.new(-MouseDeltaX / Sway_Division, MouseDeltaY / Sway_Division, 0))\\t\\n        \\n        -- Springs Updater --\\n        \\n        local UpdatedBobbing = Springs.Bobbing:update(DT)\\n        local UpdatedSway = Springs.Sway:update(DT)\\n        local UpdatedFiring = Springs.Firing:update(DT)\\n        \\n        if Viewmodel.CurrentVM then\\n            \\n            -- Sway Updater --\\n            \\n            local SwayX = UpdatedSway.X\\n            local SwayY = UpdatedSway.Y\\n            \\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(SwayX, SwayY, 0)\\n            \\n            -- Bobbing Updater --\\n            \\n            local BobX = UpdatedBobbing.X\\n            local BobY = UpdatedBobbing.Y\\n\\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(BobX, BobY, 0)\\n            \\n            -- Firing Updater --\\n\\n            local FireX = UpdatedFiring.X\\n            local FireY = UpdatedFiring.Y\\n            local FireZ = UpdatedFiring.Z\\n\\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(FireX, FireY, FireZ)\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n  \\n Here’s the result of my code, it sways. But not in the way I want it to. \\n   \\n     ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2026-01-03T07:12:34.598Z"}
