444	devforum	4164412	Formatting issue	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4164412	UI	A TextLabel's Text property automatically reverts from a comma-formatted string to a plain numeric string after being set via script, despite no other scripts modifying the label.	\N	f	intermediate	{string.gsub,TextLabel.Text,TextLabel.AutoLocalize,task.wait}	{}	t	Debug by monitoring the TextLabel with GetPropertyChangedSignal to identify when and where the value is being reverted, and verify if Roblox's Automatic Localization or a bound Value object is overriding the script-assigned string.	75	1	4	2025-12-19 19:35:44.898	2026-01-08 17:13:43.75685	{"views": 75, "content": " So i was working on changing my money to showcase on the UI, and I decided to format it with commas, with a function that works. \\nHere is the function I used: \\n  function MathModule.formatWithCommas(number)\\n\\tlocal formatted = number\\n\\twhile true do  \\n\\t\\tformatted, k = string.gsub(formatted, \\"^(-?%d+)(%d%d%d)\\", '%1,%2')\\n\\t\\tif k == 0 then\\n\\t\\t\\tbreak\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn formatted\\nend\\n  \\n In my main script this is the problem, and I’ve gone through several print statements to figure it out. Here is what I obtained in the output: \\n5,000 \\n5,000 string \\nfalse \\n5,000​ 5,000 \\nfalse \\n5000 5,000 \\nfrom this code: \\n  local function updateCredits()\\n\\tlocal formatted = MathUtil.formatWithCommas(creditsValue.Value)\\n\\tprint(formatted)\\n\\tprint(tostring(formatted), type(formatted))\\n\\t\\n\\tcreditsLabel.Text = formatted\\n\\tprint(creditsLabel.AutoLocalize)\\n\\tprint(creditsLabel.Text, formatted)\\n\\ttask.wait(0.1)\\n\\tprint(creditsLabel.AutoLocalize)\\n\\tprint(creditsLabel.Text,formatted)\\nend\\n  \\n this made no sense to me as I figured it was autolocalize, or the type being a number, but all of it should be just fine. It changes the text directly to 5000 instead of 5,000 automatically even when I set it differently. I do not set it anywhere else in my code, this is the only script here that even references the creditsLabel. It’s happening to my other label as well though. I’m not sure if this is a studio bug, or something else that I just don’t know. ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-19T19:35:44.898Z"}
