469	devforum	4209547	Strange bug that I found in my DoorModule	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4209547	Scripting	TweenService:Create() is called but the resulting Tween object is never played with :Play(). Additionally, table.find is used on a dictionary instead of a direct key lookup, and a state variable (isOpen) is never toggled.	1. Append :Play() to the end of the TweenService:Create() call. 2. Use 'if doorBehaviours[behaviour] then' instead of table.find. 3. Update 'isOpen = not isOpen' inside the Triggered event connection.	f	beginner	{TweenService,CFrame,TweenInfo,ProximityPrompt}	{}	t	A linter or coding assistant can identify 'naked' Tween creations that are not assigned to a variable or followed by :Play(), and detect the misuse of table.find on tables containing non-numeric keys.	82	1	5	2026-01-02 19:46:16.884	2026-01-08 17:14:10.155026	{"views": 82, "content": " I have an issue with my door module I made in a test game, It doesn’t seem to work even though I don’t really see any errors at all. I tried debugging it, and it shown me no result. \\n The DoorModule code. \\n  local TweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\n\\nlocal DoorModule = {}\\n\\nfunction DoorModule.OpenDoor(model, angle, behaviour)\\n\\tlocal hinge = model.PrimaryPart\\n\\tlocal tweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0)\\n\\tlocal doorBehaviours = {\\n\\t\\t[\\"XRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(math.rad(angle), 0, 0),\\n\\t\\t[\\"YRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(angle), 0),\\n\\t\\t[\\"ZRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(0, 0, math.rad(angle))\\n\\t}\\n\\t\\n\\t\\n\\tif table.find(doorBehaviours, behaviour) then\\n\\t\\tTweenService:Create(hinge, tweenInfo, {[\\"CFrame\\"] = doorBehaviours[behaviour]})\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"Invalid door behaviour or an error occoured.\\")\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nfunction DoorModule.CloseDoor(model, behaviour)\\n\\tlocal hinge = model.PrimaryPart\\n\\tlocal tweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(0.5, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0)\\n\\tlocal doorBehaviours = {\\n\\t\\t[\\"XRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(math.rad(0), 0, 0),\\n\\t\\t[\\"YRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(0), 0),\\n\\t\\t[\\"ZRot\\"] = CFrame.Angles(0, 0, math.rad(0))\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tif table.find(doorBehaviours, behaviour) then\\n\\t\\tTweenService:Create(hinge, tweenInfo, {[\\"CFrame\\"] = doorBehaviours[behaviour]})\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"Invalid door behaviour or an error occoured.\\")\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nreturn DoorModule\\n  \\n The script requiring the DoorModule. \\n  local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal isOpen = false\\n\\nlocal doorModule = require(ReplicatedStorage.DoorModule)\\n\\nlocal prompt = script.Parent\\n\\nlocal doorModel = prompt.Parent.Parent\\n\\nprompt.Triggered:Connect(function()\\n\\tif not isOpen then\\n\\t\\tdoorModule.OpenDoor(doorModel, 90, \\"XRot\\")\\n\\telseif isOpen then\\n\\t\\tdoorModule.CloseDoor(doorModel, \\"XRot\\")\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  \\n I am geninuely clueless on how does the module not work, help is appriciated! \\n  \\n     ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-02T19:46:16.884Z"}
471	devforum	4209065	Smoothing animations with weight	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4209065	Animation	Difficulty implementing smooth animation transitions between idle, walk, and sprint states using manual weight adjustments via TweenService and NumberValues, leading to overlapping animations or lack of fading.	\N	f	intermediate	{TweenService,AnimationTrack:AdjustWeight,AnimationTrack:Play,AnimationTrack:Stop,Instance.new,GetPropertyChangedSignal}	{}	t	Replace the manual weight tweening logic with the built-in 'fadeTime' parameter of the AnimationTrack:Play() and AnimationTrack:Stop() methods, which natively handles weight transitions.	76	5	6	2026-01-02 16:59:38.409	2026-01-08 17:14:11.610847	{"views": 76, "content": " Hello! I’m trying to make walking, idle, and sprint animations blend into each other but just can’t get it right for the life of me. \\n Either no animations play when I move, they bug out and overlap, or just don’t fade. If anyone has any techniques or a way to fix my function, please let me know. \\n  local function PlayAnimation(anim)\\n\\t\\n\\tfor i, animation in pairs({IdleAnim,WalkAnim,SprintAnim}) do\\n\\t\\t\\tif animation.IsPlaying then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal TargetWeight = Instance.new(\\"NumberValue\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tTargetWeight.Value = 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal Tween = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\"):Create(TargetWeight, TweenInfo.new(0.25, Enum.EasingStyle.Exponential), {Value = 0}):Play()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tTargetWeight:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\\"Value\\"):Connect(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tanimation:AdjustWeight(TargetWeight.Value)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif TargetWeight.Value &lt;= 0.05 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tanimation:Stop()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tanim:Play(0 ,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal TargetWeight = Instance.new(\\"NumberValue\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tTargetWeight.Value = 1\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Tween = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\"):Create(TargetWeight, TweenInfo.new(0.25, Enum.EasingStyle.Exponential), {Value = 1}):Play()\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tTargetWeight:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\\"Value\\"):Connect(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tanimation:AdjustWeight(TargetWeight.Value)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\t\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2026-01-02T16:59:38.409Z"}
483	devforum	4199045	Critical server delay	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4199045	Networking	Latency-induced hit registration failure where server-side raycast validation misses targets that have moved since the client-side hit was recorded.	Implement lag compensation (server-side rewind) by sending client timestamps with hit data and checking raycasts against the target's historical positions instead of their current state.	t	advanced	{Raycast}	{}	t	Create a server-side module that maintains a sliding buffer of player CFrames and timestamps, allowing hit verification logic to interpolate a target's position back in time.	116	3	6	2025-12-30 16:57:15.696	2026-01-08 17:14:25.539524	{"views": 116, "content": " I’ve been making weapon system for a while, until i got a problem - exploiters can just send some packets with information about “hit” and it will work, because packets contained info about parts that was “hit” with a bullet. I decided to fix this and make a new communication system: \\n Client is doing the first raycast, and if it’s successful, it waits raycast1.Distance/bulletSpeed and fires another raycast that finally shows a hitmarker, makes bullet hole and sends info (position and direction) to server, where it fires ANOTHER raycast and only then it deals damage or creates an explosion. So yeah, this might work, but… target may move to the side and avoid server raycast because of the client-server delay. That’s very annoying, because 80% of all bullets just don’t deal any damage, but there’s a hitmarker and blood particles. I may perform raycasting from a server and then get the result on client and do hitmarker or bullet hole, but the client will get too much delayed information (Very critical to ingame experience). \\n  Is there a way to make such system that will be protected from exploiters, but also register bullets normally?  \\n  ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-12-30T16:57:15.696Z"}
1069	devforum	2275805	How can I make a Global Leaderboard like this?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/2275805	DataStore	Creating a consolidated global leaderboard that displays multiple player statistics within a single UI component using OrderedDataStore.	Use OrderedDataStore to store and retrieve player rankings for specific stats, as detailed in the linked community tutorial. Note that PointsService is deprecated and should be avoided in favor of custom DataStore implementations.	t	intermediate	{OrderedDataStore,PointsService,DataStoreService}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a standard Lua script that iterates through a list of player stats, updates their respective OrderedDataStores, and provides a function to refresh the UI with the top results.	3470	0	15	2023-04-07 01:43:13.142	2026-01-08 17:30:00.689596	{"url": "https://devforum.roblox.com/t/2275805", "title": "How can I make a Global Leaderboard like this?", "views": 3470, "source": "devforum", "replies": 15, "analysis": {"solved": true, "problem": "Creating a consolidated global leaderboard that displays multiple player statistics within a single UI component using OrderedDataStore.", "category": "DataStore", "solution": "Use OrderedDataStore to store and retrieve player rankings for specific stats, as detailed in the linked community tutorial. Note that PointsService is deprecated and should be avoided in favor of custom DataStore implementations.", "difficulty": "intermediate", "automatable": true, "apis_mentioned": ["OrderedDataStore", "PointsService", "DataStoreService"], "error_messages": [], "automation_hint": "A coding agent could generate a standard Lua script that iterates through a list of player stats, updates their respective OrderedDataStores, and provides a function to refresh the UI with the top results."}, "category": "scripting-support", "source_id": "2275805", "worker_id": "devforum-1", "created_at": "2023-04-07T01:43:13.142Z", "scraped_at": "2026-01-09T01:29:54.515558"}
470	devforum	4174701	How Lag Compensation Of Projectiles Should Be Handled With Server-Auth?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4174701	Networking	Implementing server-authoritative lag compensation specifically for projectiles (non-hitscan) using rewind and fast-forward logic to synchronize server and client simulations without excessive server overhead.	\N	f	advanced	{"Server Authority"}	{}	t	An AI could generate a framework for projectile hit validation that utilizes a history buffer of player positions, allowing the server to 'rewind' the world state to the exact timestamp a projectile was fired based on client latency.	321	5	11	2025-12-22 22:25:46.499	2026-01-08 17:14:10.995796	{"views": 321, "content": " First of all i want to mention i really searched so much but i just find out limited sources/articles about lag compensation for projectiles, and it made me create this post \\n With Robloxs  server auth  system i guess things are deterministic and it should be possible to process rollback/rewind type lag compensations \\n When u want to create a server auth projectiles probably u would look logic of libraries like  SecureCast  and  Chickynoid  then u apply same logic to ur game with robloxs new server auth system everything should be fine right? \\n         image  1011×347 13.9 KB         \\nThere is how networking of that logic would look like, it is possible to reduce delay 2x at end for hit info packet server to shooter client. When u apply this logic at the moment server receives first request it calculates the latency and rewinds the time but there is no fast forward, simulation of server and shooters client never get synced its reason of the problem on that schema \\n This is whats my solution to it: \\n         image  858×419 18.9 KB         \\nThe server processes the  all of snapshots got affected by latency  at the frame receives packet and i guess this would be expensive for server. \\n So why i created this post; i inspired that fast forward logic just by one not solved unity forum post i dont even know this logic exist in real games applying lag compensation for projectiles like overwatch and etc. \\n So whats correct way to implementation of rewind lag compensation for projectiles? ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2025-12-22T22:25:46.499Z"}
