521	devforum	4184480	How do you make it so a client script can detect a part that was created from serverScript?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4184480	Networking	Client script cannot reference a server-created Instance passed via RemoteEvent or ObjectValue immediately after creation due to replication latency.	\N	f	intermediate	{ReplicatedStorage,RemoteEvent,ObjectValue,SetNetworkOwner,Debris,ApplyImpulse,OnServerEvent,FireClient,OnClientEvent}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest using WaitForChild on the client to wait for the replicated part or explain that passing an ObjectValue created on the server might not be visible to the client immediately.	107	0	4	2025-12-26 02:24:10.998	2026-01-08 17:15:05.004636	{"views": 107, "content": " I’m having issues with my client script not picking up on a part named “Bullet” that was replicated and parented to workspace by a serverscript and then passed onto the client as a objValue. \\n I tried just passing the part as a value and not wrapped in a objvalue, well that failed, so then I tried passing it as a object value and that also failed, the client never seems to recognize the part exists no matter what. \\n Server Script \\n  game.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, mousePosition, Hull, Barrel)\\n\\n\\tlocal bullet = game.ReplicatedStorage.Bullet:Clone()\\n\\tbullet.Parent = workspace\\n\\tbullet.CanCollide = false\\n\\tbullet.CFrame = Barrel.Attachment.WorldCFrame\\n\\n\\ttask.wait()\\n\\tbullet:SetNetworkOwner(player)\\n\\t\\n\\tgame.Debris:AddItem(bullet, 10)\\n\\tlocal objvalue = Instance.new(\\"ObjectValue\\")\\n\\tobjvalue.Value = bullet\\n\\t\\n\\tgame.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired:FireClient(player, objvalue)\\n\\t\\nend)\\n  \\n Local Script \\n  game.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(objValue)\\n\\tlocal bullet = objValue.Value\\n\\tbullet:ApplyImpulse(bullet.CFrame.LookVector * bullet.AssemblyMass * 500)\\nend)\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-suppo