516	devforum	4212427	Detect turning with ShiftLock enabled	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212427	Scripting	Humanoid.MoveDirection remains 0 when turning in ShiftLock or First Person mode, preventing the detection of player rotation for a drifting mechanic.	Calculate the camera's LookVector relative to the character's RootPart CFrame using VectorToObjectSpace to determine a turnAmount independent of MoveDirection.	t	intermediate	{Humanoid.MoveDirection,CFrame.VectorToObjectSpace,Camera.CFrame,BasePart.CFrame,Vector3.LookVector}	{}	t	Create a wrapper function that combines MoveDirection and Camera-RootPart angular delta to provide a unified 'turn intensity' value regardless of input method.	122	3	7	2026-01-03 16:23:12.113	2026-01-08 17:15:02.725551	{"views": 122, "content": " I’m making a sliding game where turning sharply will start a drift, I can already do that with this code. \\n  local MoveDirection = RootPart.CFrame:VectorToObjectSpace(Humanoid.MoveDirection) -- makes it relative to character\\nlocal MoveDirectionX = MoveDirection.X\\nif MoveDirectionX &gt;= 0.55 then -- Drift Right\\n\\t-- drift right code\\nelseif MoveDirectionX &lt;= -0.55 then -- Drift Left\\n\\t-- drift left code\\nend\\n  \\n Issue is, trying to use this code with first person/shiftlock will make the MoveDirectionX result in nothing being outputted (0). \\nI’ve tried ControlModule:GetMoveVector() as of now, is there a way to make the code above work with ShiftLock/First Person? \\nA and D inputs work just fine, it’s only moving and turning with shiftlock/first person that doesn’t get detected. ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2026-01-03T16:23:12.113Z"}
