529	devforum	4207394	Don't Know How to Make Hitbox System Account for Player Velocity	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4207394	Scripting	Hitboxes lag behind or become disjointed when a player moves or rotates because they are anchored and positioned only once upon creation, failing to follow the character's movement.	Instead of using velocity-based math to predict positioning, continuously update the hitbox's CFrame relative to the HumanoidRootPart every frame using RunService.Heartbeat or use a WeldConstraint to attach the hitbox to the player.	t	intermediate	{GetNetworkPing,VectorToObjectSpace,AssemblyLinearVelocity,CFrame,GetPartBoundsInBox,Heartbeat,OnServerEvent}	{}	t	Refactor the hitbox creation script to utilize RunService.Heartbeat to update the hitbox CFrame relative to the character or implement a Weld/WeldConstraint to handle the offset automatically via the physics engine.	177	6	6	2026-01-02 04:35:10.49	2026-01-08 17:15:23.663853	{"views": 177, "content": " For my asymmetrical game (how original I know) I want to have hitboxes similar to that of Forsaken’s or like Pwned By 14:00, with how multiple hitboxes are spawned with one swing, and the code that I have so gracefully borrowed from DoomHammerYT does this correctly. However the system doesn’t account for velocity, which is the main issue, as the hitboxes lags behind the player while moving and the hitboxes get thrown if the player turns too fast. \\n The 3 lines of code above from Adi_DK is a solution that works for forsaken, but attempting to insert the code into the hitbox script doesn’t work, as I believe that the way the createHitbox function actually creates the hitboxes, attempting to combine the lines on top, is more difficult than I thought it would be. \\n Is there a simpler way to either make the hitboxes’s offset value adapt to velocity, or a way to combine the code? \\n The solution that I currently have is just an extremely simple and quite terrible, increasing the offset when a certain speed is reached, which still produces the issue of the hitboxes getting thrown when turning, and the hitboxes generally being disjointed \\n  \\nlocal pingOffset = 6.5 - 10 * math.clamp(player:GetNetworkPing(), 0, 0.3)\\n\\nlocal velocityOffset = hitboxPart.CFrame:VectorToObjectSpace(primaryPart.AssemblyLinearVelocity)\\n\\nhitboxPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(velocityOffset / pingOffset)\\n\\n-- the code i have no idea how to implement above \\n\\n-- above code by Adi_DK\\n\\n-- beneath code by DoomHammerYT\\n\\nlocal function createHitbox(damage, size, offset, hrp, hitboxes, touchedTable)\\n\\tlocal hitbox = Instance.new(\\"Part\\")\\n\\thitbox.CanCollide = false\\n\\thitbox.Transparency = 0.75\\n\\thitbox.Size = size\\n\\thitbox.Parent = workspace\\n\\thitbox.CFrame = hrp.CFrame * CFrame.new(offset)\\n\\thitbox.Anchored = true\\n\\t\\n\\ttable.insert(hitboxes, hitbox)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal touchedParts = workspace:GetPartBoundsInBox(hitbox.CFrame, hitbox.Size)\\n\\tfor i, part in touchedParts do\\n\\t\\ttable.insert(touchedTable, part)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nm1Event.OnServerEven", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2026-01-02T04:35:10.490Z"}
