536	devforum	4213714	ShapeCast Passes Through Corners	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4213714	Physics	Shapecast (Blockcast) fails to detect collisions and passes through geometry when hitting corners or intersections where multiple surfaces meet.	\N	f	intermediate	{workspace:Blockcast,RaycastParams,OverlapParams,workspace:GetPartsInPart,CFrame,Vector3,Instance.new,Debris}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest implementing a recursive casting algorithm that performs secondary checks if a hit is detected near a corner, or apply a small 'epsilon' offset to the reflection position to prevent the projectile from being initialized inside a wall on the next frame.	50	3	2	2026-01-04 00:41:38.751	2026-01-08 17:15:32.227449	{"views": 50, "content": " Explanation: I am currently coding a bouncing projectile that uses Shapecast to detect surfaces and bounce off them. The issue I am encountering is that when the projectile is thrown into a corner-like shape (as shown in the video), it passes straight through the surface instead of bouncing. This only seems to happen when the projectile hits multiple surfaces at once (for example, a corner or tight angle). In normal, flat surface collisions, the bouncing works as expected. What would be the correct way to handle this scenario? Is there a known limitation with Shapecast in corner collisions, or am I missing an additional check or calculation? \\n   \\n     \\n Module: \\n  local projectile = {}\\nlocal Debris = game:GetService(\\"Debris\\")\\nprojectile.__index = projectile\\n\\nlocal function newCube(pos,propertie)\\n\\tlocal cube = Instance.new(\\"Part\\")\\n\\tcube.Size = Vector3.new(0.5,0.5,0.5)\\n\\tcube.Anchored = true\\n\\tcube.CanCollide = false\\n\\tcube.Transparency = 0.5\\n\\tcube.Parent = workspace\\n\\tcube.Position = pos\\n\\tcube.Color = Color3.new(1, 0, 0)\\n\\tcube.Material = Enum.Material.Neon\\n\\t--cube.Shape = Enum.PartType.Ball\\n\\tfor i,v in pairs(propertie or {}) do\\n\\t\\tcube[i] = v\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn cube\\nend\\n\\nfunction projectile:initStep(donteat:boolean)\\n\\tlocal instance = self.CastSettings.Hitbox or self.Instance\\n\\tlocal scanner = (instance or newCube(Vector3.new(0,0,0),{Transparency = 1})):Clone()\\n\\tscanner.CFrame = CFrame.new(self.pos)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal params = OverlapParams.new()\\n\\tparams.FilterType = Enum.RaycastFilterType.Exclude\\n\\tparams.FilterDescendantsInstances = {scanner,table.unpack(self.CastSettings.FilterDescendantsInstances)}\\n\\tlocal res = workspace:GetPartsInPart(scanner,params)\\n\\tif res and #res &gt; 0 then\\n\\t\\tif donteat then\\n\\t\\t\\tself:Eat()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\treturn false\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn true\\nend\\n\\nfunction projectile:Render()\\n\\tlocal cube = self.Instance or newCube(self.pos)\\n\\t--cube.Position = self.pos\\n\\tcube.CFrame = CFrame.new(self.pos, self.pos + self.vel.Unit)\\n\\t--Debris:addItem(cube,self.LifeTime)\\nend\\n\\nfunction projectile:Eat(", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-04T00:41:38.751Z"}
