542	devforum	4213098	How to make a player stick to a tweened part?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4213098	Physics	Characters do not automatically move with a platform that is being moved via TweenService because the movement is kinematic/CFrame-based rather than physics-based.	Calculate and update the platform's AssemblyLinearVelocity manually by measuring the DeltaPosition between frames within a RunService.Heartbeat loop, or utilize physics constraints like AlignPosition.	t	intermediate	{TweenService,TweenInfo,AlignPosition,RunService.Heartbeat,AssemblyLinearVelocity}	{}	t	An AI agent could provide a standardized 'MovingPlatform' module that handles the Heartbeat connection and AssemblyLinearVelocity calculation for any anchored part being tweened.	97	0	11	2026-01-03 20:40:00.176	2026-01-08 17:15:37.300316	{"views": 97, "content": " It sounded simple to me, but I couldent understand it. I want to make a player move along with a moving part whenever the player is ontop of it. \\n I looked at other solutions, but it looks like theres just so many solutions for diffrent purposes, and it looks very complex. Im very stuck on where to even start. \\n I only want the player to stick on the part while standing on it, when they jump they should stop sticking \\n If anyone wonders what my current script is,  its just a basic moving script with waypoints: \\n  local t=script.Parent.Time.Value\\nlocal Tween_Settings = TweenInfo.new(t,Enum.EasingStyle.Sine,Enum.EasingDirection.Out,-1,true)\\nlocal WP1 = script.Parent:WaitForChild(\\"Waypoint1\\")\\nlocal WP2 = script.Parent:WaitForChild(\\"Waypoint2\\")\\nlocal MP = script.Parent:WaitForChild(\\"Moving\\")\\nWP1.Transparency = 1\\nWP2.Transparency = 1\\nMP.Position = WP1.Position\\nlocal TS = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\nTS:Create(MP,Tween_Settings,{Position=WP2.Position}):Play()\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2026-01-03T20:40:00.176Z"}
