547	devforum	4192764	What is the best way to create realistic pillars in Roblox Studio?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4192764	3D Modeling	How to create high-detail, realistic Greek-style pillars for Roblox Studio buildings efficiently.	Use Blender instead of Roblox Studio. Import a reference image, use a cylinder as the base mesh, and apply the Mirror modifier across the X and Y axes to synchronize edits across four quadrants simultaneously.	t	intermediate	{}	{}	t	A Blender Python script could be developed to procedurally generate fluted pillars by taking parameters like height, diameter, and flute count, automatically setting up the Mirror modifiers and UV mapping.	100	4	6	2025-12-28 17:41:42.286	2026-01-08 17:15:41.778293	{"views": 100, "content": " Hey everyone! \\n I’m planning to make a realistic replica of the Australian City of Canberra with government buildings and I wanted to create realistic pillars for them but I don’t know how to? Does anyone know how to? \\n .  What do you want to achieve?  \\nI saw these pillars on the Devforum and I think they are Greek and I wanted to create a replica of them here’s the post and what I wanna make:  \\n   \\n      \\n     \\n     Feedback on Greek-style wall thingy     Creations Feedback   \\n   \\n   \\n    Yeah the blocks are definitely bright. \\nWhen you’re doing something in the Ancient genre, things will be more pristine. So the marble (I’m presuming the wall is made of marble) would be more white. Pictures you see now of temples like the Parthenon is just from centuries of weathering, dirt, ect. \\nI didn’t make this but I think this is accurate \\n  [image]  \\nOr, if its another material like sandstone then i’d make it a little more reddish and darker. \\nHowever if this is the modern era and its just …\\n   \\n \\n          image  493×500 284 KB         \\n . **What is the issue? \\nWhile I found the post I’m not sure how to make a pillar that looks similar to it. I tried to recreate it but it didn’t look as