552	devforum	3059804	Is it possible to create a search function in the datastore?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/3059804	DataStore	Implementing a performant search and querying function for large datasets in Roblox, given that DataStoreService lacks native complex querying and indexing capabilities.	Use an external database (such as MySQL, MongoDB, or Elasticsearch) paired with a backend server (Node.js, Python) to handle advanced queries, communicating via Roblox's HttpService. While technically possible in DataStore by manually iterating through data in Lua, it is discouraged due to rate limits and performance bottlenecks.	t	advanced	{DataStoreService,HttpService}	{}	t	An agent can generate a boilerplate backend API in Node.js or Python to interface with a database and provide the corresponding Roblox Lua script for making HTTP requests and handling the JSON response.	571	3	4	2024-07-09 06:54:24.419	2026-01-08 17:15:46.910248	{"views": 571, "content": " \\n CatWeb \\n \\n I saw a search function implementation in this game. \\nWas it possible to implement the search function with datastore? Or is this an external database? ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2024-07-09T06:54:24.419Z"}
555	devforum	4213195	Module code did not return exactly one value	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4213195	Scripting	Roblox ModuleScript failing to load with the error 'Module code did not return exactly one value', caused by invalid ModuleScript structure or content after the return statement.	Ensure every ModuleScript returns exactly one value (typically a table or function) and that no code exists after the final 'return' statement. The user's snippet showed two separate module definitions combined in what appears to be a single file or code block, which violates the requirement that a ModuleScript must return only one value.	t	beginner	{require,RunService,GetDescendants,IsA,GetService,WaitForChild}	{"Module code did not return exactly one value"}	t	A coding agent or linter can statically analyze ModuleScripts to verify they contain exactly one return statement and that no logic or variable declarations follow the primary return statement.	75	0	4	2026-01-03 21:17:56.189	2026-01-08 17:15:50.682851	{"views": 75, "content": " Hey guys, today while reorganizing my game I decided to implement a module loader I had found awhile ago, but am having trouble getting it to work. Currently, the way I intend for it to work is to loop through two folders which contain nested module scripts, and run the defined functions inside. But I’m only receiving this error message,  Module code did not return exactly one value  instead. Is it possibly due to the number of module scripts it would have to comb through, or is there another way to get require to work on an table containing module scripts? Below will be pasted the current code I’m using. Any help figuring this out will be greatly appreciated! &lt;3 \\n  -- Services\\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\n\\n-- Functions\\nfunction Loader.LoadAll()\\n\\t-- Get ReplicatedStorage scripts\\n\\tlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\tlocal Shared = ReplicatedStorage.Shared\\n\\tlocal RSScripts = Shared:WaitForChild(\\"Scripts\\")\\n\\n\\tlocal serverOrLocalScripts = nil\\n\\n\\t-- Get if server or local\\n\\tif RunService:IsServer() then\\n\\t\\tlocal ServerScriptService = game:GetService(\\"ServerScriptService\\")\\n\\t\\tlocal server = ServerScriptService.Server\\n\\t\\tlocal SSSScripts = server:WaitForChild(\\"Scripts\\")\\n\\t\\tserverOrLocalScripts = SSSScripts\\n\\telseif RunService:IsClient() then\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\t-- Initialize ReplicatedStorage modules\\n\\tfor i, moduleScript in pairs(RSScripts:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\tif moduleScript:IsA(\\"ModuleScript\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tmoduleScript = require(moduleScript)\\n\\t\\t\\tif moduleScript[\\"Init\\"] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tmoduleScript.Init()\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\t-- Start ReplicatedStorage modules\\n\\tfor i, moduleScript in pairs(RSScripts:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\tif moduleScript:IsA(\\"ModuleScript\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tmoduleScript = require(moduleScript)\\n\\t\\t\\tif moduleScript[\\"Start\\"] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tmoduleScript.Start()\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\t-- Initialize server or local modules\\n\\tfor i, moduleScript in pairs(serverOrLocalScripts:GetDescendants()) do\\n\\t\\tif moduleScript:IsA(\\"ModuleScript\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tmoduleScript", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-03T21:17:56.189Z"}
557	devforum	4213075	Bullet casings phasing through the floor	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4213075	Scripting	Custom bullet casing physics using raycasting are phasing through objects due to insufficient collision detection logic in the Heartbeat loop.	Use the FastCast module for projectile physics, move the bullet along a kinematic parabola, and implement Object Pooling for optimization.	f	intermediate	{RunService.Heartbeat,WorldRoot:Raycast,TweenService,Debris,RaycastParams}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the loop to ensure the raycast distance covers the full delta between frames (current position to next predicted position) and implement a recursive or iterative bounce logic to handle collisions within a single frame.	39	0	2	2026-01-03 20:33:07.097	2026-01-08 17:15:51.798454	{"views": 39, "content": " i’m trying to make a bullet casing system that doesn’t rely on roblox’s physics, but most of the time they just phase through objects \\n   \\n     \\n  function module.casing(pos:Vector3, mdl:BasePart, shotgun:boolean)\\n\\tlocal casing = mdl:Clone()\\n\\tlocal firstbounce = false\\n\\tlocal bounces = math.random(1,4)\\n\\tlocal folder\\n\\tif shotgun then\\n\\t\\tfolder = script.casingsounds.shotgun\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tfolder = script.casingsounds.metal\\n\\tend\\n\\tcasing.Anchored = true\\n\\tcasing.Position = pos\\n\\tcasing.CanCollide = false; casing.CanQuery = false; casing.CanTouch = false\\n\\tcasing.Parent = workspace\\n\\tlocal initvel = Vector3.new(math.random(-40,40)/100, math.random(50,70)/100, math.random(-40,40)/100)\\n\\tlocal vel = initvel\\n\\tlocal filter = RaycastParams.new()\\n\\tfilter.RespectCanCollide = true\\n\\tfor i,v in pairs(workspace:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\tif v:IsA(\\"Model\\") and v:FindFirstChildOfClass(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tfilter:AddToFilter(v:GetDescendants())\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\tlocal poop\\n\\tgame:GetService(\\"TweenService\\"):Create(casing, TweenInfo.new(6, Enum.EasingStyle.Linear, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 2), {Transparency = 1}):Play()\\n\\tgame:GetService(\\"Debris\\"):AddItem(casing, 8)\\n\\tpoop = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\").Heartbeat:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal ray = workspace:Raycast(casing.Position, vel, filter)\\n\\t\\tif ray then\\n\\t\\t\\tif bounces &gt;= 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tbounces -= 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcasing.Position = ray.Position\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcasing.CFrame = CFrame.new(casing.Position, ray.Position + ray.Normal) * CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tvel = Vector3.new(ray.Normal.X, -vel.Y, ray.Normal.Z)*math.random(-100,100)/100\\n\\t\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tpoop:Disconnect()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcasing.CFrame = CFrame.new(ray.Position, ray.Position + ray.Normal) * CFrame.Angles(math.rad(90),0,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tvel = Vector3.one*0\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tvel += Vector3.new(0, -.05, 0)\\n\\t\\tcasing.Position += vel\\n\\tend)\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-03T20:33:07.097Z"}
