565	devforum	4151404	Adaptive Animations BREAKS R6 rigs entirely when enabled │ End of R6?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4151404	Animation	The 'Adaptive Animations' Studio Beta feature prevents R6 rigs from rotating or moving their Torso joint during animations, whereas R15 rigs remain unaffected.	Roblox staff acknowledged the bug and confirmed it will be fixed before the feature is fully rolled out; users are advised to disable the 'Adaptive Animations' beta feature until the fix is deployed.	t	intermediate	{}	{}	f	An automation tool could check for the presence of R6 rigs in a place and verify if the 'Adaptive Animations' beta setting is toggled, warning the developer of potential torso movement issues.	244	10	2	2025-12-14 11:54:34.925	2026-01-08 17:16:00.052649	{"views": 244, "content": " Today, I enabled the Studio Beta “Adaptive Animations” feature, more on the topic of this feature can be found here: \\n  Adaptive Animations  \\n I typically enable all beta features as soon as they come out to get an early feel with them before they’re fully released. However, this one is the most dangerous as enabling it removes all access to rotate and move an R6 rig’s torso completely as seen below,  where an R6 cannot have its torso moved on the main roblox animation engine VS. an R15 rig which can:  \\n  \\n     \\n Now we know Roblox is slowly and secretly trying to move away from R6 by slowly limiting it more and more but if this issue remains, and the feature rolls out fully for all games,  then ALL R6 GAMES will have non-functioning torso movement on all their R6 animations.  \\n As of right now I am forced to disable it, hoping it gets fixed by the time it gets fully rolled out, otherwise my game which supports both R6 and R15 along with other games that include R6 will be forced to reanimate their entire game with a new rig system, effectively destroying the platform as a whole. \\n Now I might be overreacting and I don’t post here much but I never seen something so