577	devforum	4212893	Parallel Luau Help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4212893	Scripting	Performance optimization for a light management system using Parallel Luau within the RenderStepped event, specifically dealing with synchronization overhead and engine limitations.	Stay in serial execution and optimize calculations using pure Luau math to leverage native codegen, while batching DataModel changes and raycasting at the end of the frame to minimize overhead.	t	advanced	{task.desynchronize,task.synchronize,RenderStepped,Raycasting,Actor}	{}	f	A coding agent could assist by refactoring distributed Actor logic into a centralized serial manager and identifying sections of pure math that could benefit from the --!native attribute.	72	2	5	2026-01-03 19:23:22.389	2026-01-08 17:16:12.569208	{"views": 72, "content": " So I wrote a system that manages every light with a tag. It adds lens flares, volumetric beam and stuff. Everything works perfectly fine but I’m worried when I increase number of lights it’s gonna affect performance heavily. That’s why I decided to use Parallel Luau. I have a script that listens for new light sources, when added it clones an actor with a runner script in it and assigns that actor to that light source. I run this logic (skeleton) every frame in RenderStepped event: \\n  function RenderStepped(dt)\\n    task.desynchronize()\\n    -- heavy math, raycasting etc in parallel\\n    task.synchronize()\\n    -- updating state of every flare in serial\\nend\\n  \\n but the thing is I have just learned that it doesn’t work as expected. I mean it works fine but it’s not real parallel since it doesn’t work in RenderStepped (I’ve been mistaken for a long time). \\n So my question is - how to make it so it really runs in parallel? \\n I used RenderStepped because this system is everything about rendering (rendering flares, beams, lens flares) ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-03T19:23:22.389Z"}
