626	devforum	4174090	How Small can I make my texture size?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4174090	3D Modeling	Roblox automatically applies linear resampling/interpolation to very low-resolution textures (e.g., 6x6 pixels), causing them to appear blurred on 3D models rather than maintaining sharp pixel edges.	Roblox maintains the original low-resolution file size (e.g., 6x6) without forced upscaling of the asset itself, but the engine visually resamples it. To achieve a sharp pixelated look, SurfaceGuis can be used as a workaround, though they may have different performance implications compared to standard textures.	t	beginner	{SurfaceGui}	{}	f	An automation tool could batch-check texture asset resolutions and flag those below a certain threshold (e.g., 16x16) that might suffer from unintended blurring or suggest standard power-of-two optimizations.	94	3	4	2025-12-22 19:00:02.686	2026-01-08 17:17:03.694949	{"views": 94, "content": " I’m trying to optimize by reducing image texture sizes since my models use fairly simple base colors I made a 6 x 6 pixel image with different colored pixels on them \\n  \\n I’m just wondering if this actually is supported? Or like does roblox have a minimum image size limit that upscales mine when uploaded? Or if it even helps that much compared to just a 64x64 or 256x256. \\n Any answer appreciated   ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "building-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-22T19:00:02.686Z"}
