628	devforum	4211267	Viewmodel sway that rotates with the camera, Sort of like bodycam	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4211267	Scripting	Implementing rotational viewmodel sway that follows camera movement (bodycam style) rather than just translational position offset.	\N	f	intermediate	{UserInputService,CFrame,Vector3,GetMouseDelta}	{}	t	An agent could assist by modifying the CFrame logic to apply rotational offsets using CFrame.Angles based on the MouseDelta values, rather than just using CFrame.new for positional offsets.	66	1	1	2026-01-03 07:12:34.598	2026-01-08 17:17:06.636294	{"views": 66, "content": " Hello, how would you create a Viewmodel sway that rotates with the camera if that makes sense. Sort of like in this video,  Sway demo  \\n Whenever they turn their camera, their viewmodel rotates and stays in that angle depending on where you are looking. Currently I’m using springs for the bobbing. \\n  if Springs.Bobbing and Springs.Sway and Root then\\n        \\n        local Bobble = Vector3.new(GetBobbing(6), GetBobbing(10), GetBobbing(1))\\n        \\n        local MouseDelta = UserInputService:GetMouseDelta()\\n        local MouseDeltaX = MouseDelta.X\\n        local MouseDeltaY = MouseDelta.Y\\n        \\n        -- Shove Springs --\\n        \\n        Springs.Bobbing:shove(Bobble / 5 * (Root.Velocity.Magnitude) / Bobbing_Division)\\n        Springs.Sway:shove(Vector3.new(-MouseDeltaX / Sway_Division, MouseDeltaY / Sway_Division, 0))\\t\\n        \\n        -- Springs Updater --\\n        \\n        local UpdatedBobbing = Springs.Bobbing:update(DT)\\n        local UpdatedSway = Springs.Sway:update(DT)\\n        local UpdatedFiring = Springs.Firing:update(DT)\\n        \\n        if Viewmodel.CurrentVM then\\n            \\n            -- Sway Updater --\\n            \\n            local SwayX = UpdatedSway.X\\n            local SwayY = UpdatedSway.Y\\n            \\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(SwayX, SwayY, 0)\\n            \\n            -- Bobbing Updater --\\n            \\n            local BobX = UpdatedBobbing.X\\n            local BobY = UpdatedBobbing.Y\\n\\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(BobX, BobY, 0)\\n            \\n            -- Firing Updater --\\n\\n            local FireX = UpdatedFiring.X\\n            local FireY = UpdatedFiring.Y\\n            local FireZ = UpdatedFiring.Z\\n\\n            Viewmodel.CurrentVM.HumanoidRootPart.CFrame *= CFrame.new(FireX, FireY, FireZ)\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n  \\n Here’s the result of my code, it sways. But not in the way I want it to. \\n   \\n     ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2026-01-03T07:12:34.598Z"}
632	devforum	4203532	Text not updating on SurfaceGUI	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4203532	Scripting	Text and Value objects inside a SurfaceGUI are not updating when a RemoteEvent is fired, likely because a LocalScript is being used in a container where it cannot execute (Workspace).	\N	f	beginner	{Touched,FireAllClients,OnClientEvent,RemoteEvent,SurfaceGui,TextLabel}	{}	t	Check the parent of the script; LocalScripts do not run in the Workspace unless they are parented to the local player's character. Recommend moving logic to a ServerScript if global visibility is intended, or moving the LocalScript to StarterGui/PlayerGui.	168	1	7	2026-01-01 01:27:26.039	2026-01-08 17:17:09.045049	{"views": 168, "content": " I’m a rookie at scripting, and I’m trying to make it so that when the event is triggered, it adds 1 to the value and changes the text to the value, but for some reason, the text and value remain the same. \\n  local triggerPart = script.Parent\\nlocal events = game.ReplicatedStorage.Events\\nlocal event = events.Smoked\\n\\n\\ntriggerPart.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\\n    if hit.Parent.Name == \\"elg\\" or hit.Parent.Name == \\"elk\\" then\\n\\t\\tevent:FireAllClients(\\"smoked\\")\\n\\t\\thit:Destroy()\\n\\t\\tprint(\\"smoked meat\\")\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  \\n and \\n  local events = game.ReplicatedStorage.Events\\nlocal event = events.Smoked\\nlocal value = script.Parent.count\\nlocal text = script.Parent.Count\\n\\nevent.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(action)\\n\\tif action == \\"smoked\\" then\\n\\t\\tvalue.Value = value.Value + 1\\n\\t\\ttext.Text = tostring(value.Value)\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2026-01-01T01:27:26.039Z"}
633	devforum	4208719	How do they make entities like Eyes from Doors with respect to the client-server system?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4208719	Networking	Determining the optimal client-server architecture for a gaze-based damage mechanic (damaging the player when they look at an entity) to balance network latency and exploit prevention.	Use a client-side approach for responsiveness using Vector3:Dot() to check the look-at angle and WorldRoot:Raycast to check for line-of-sight obstructions. The server should receive a signal from the client, as the mechanic primarily impacts the local player and is less critical to secure than competitive mechanics.	t	intermediate	{Vector3:Dot,WorldRoot:Raycast}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a boilerplate script using a RunService Heartbeat loop on the client to calculate the Dot product between the Camera's LookVector and the vector to the entity, combined with a raycast for visibility checking.	129	6	8	2026-01-02 14:59:01.579	2026-01-08 17:17:11.229965	{"views": 129, "content": " (Hopefully a similar thing hasn’t already been asked since I couldn’t find any) \\n So I’m making a horror game, and I want to make an entity that has similar mechanics with Eyes from the game Doors. I already have some ways to make it in my mind, but I’m unsure about the server-client issues. \\n I mainly concern about how should I make the mechanic with respect to the client-server system. Such as following: \\n   Make it server-based: \\n \\n Secure. \\n Unlikely able to be exploited. \\n Can lead to unwanted outcomes due to network latency. \\n \\n   Make it client-based: \\n \\n Devoid of network issues. \\n CAN be exploited. \\n \\n Should I make it in another way? ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2026-01-02T14:59:01.579Z"}
635	devforum	4210888	How do I filter messages in a custom chat in 2026?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4210888	Scripting	Finding the modern equivalent for TextService:GetChatForUserAsync() to filter strings in a custom chat system, as the documentation for the deprecated method incorrectly points to TextChatService which lacks a direct filtering equivalent.	Use TextService:FilterStringAsync() to obtain a TextFilterResult object, which can then be used to filter text for specific users or all users. TextService:GetChatForUserAsync() is deprecated, but FilterStringAsync remains the standard for custom systems.	t	intermediate	{TextService,TextChatService,GetChatForUserAsync,FilterStringAsync,MessageReceived,Player.Chatted,Chat}	{}	t	A coding agent could identify deprecated chat filtering methods like GetChatForUserAsync or Chat:FilterStringAsync and replace them with TextService:FilterStringAsync wrapped in a pcall for robustness.	162	5	8	2026-01-03 04:09:44.182	2026-01-08 17:17:12.023256	{"views": 162, "content": " I’ve been playing around with and making custom chat systems for over 10 years now, but ROBLOX seems to change the chat every once in a while and it’s a little annoying. \\n Previously, I would use  GetChatForUserAsync()  via  TextService , but now the Create Hub says it’s deprecated and says to use TextChatService instead. However, I cannot see an equivalent under  TextChatService . \\n \\n If possible, how do I filter messages for my custom chat? \\n I’m getting player messages now via  .MessageReceived  from  TextChatService  instead of using  Player.Chatted  like I used to. Is the result I get from  .MessageReceived  automatically filtered? \\n \\n My main concern is my game getting moderated because I failed to comply to ROBLOX’s current policies and guidelines because I did not make and/or filter my custom chat correctly. ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2026-01-03T04:09:44.182Z"}
637	devforum	4210379	Plot System not spawning players to the correct plot	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4210379	Scripting	Incorrect plot assignment and teleportation due to FindFirstChild being called with an integer instead of a string, which can lead to index-based retrieval rather than name-based matching.	Convert the integer plot number to a string using tostring() when calling FindFirstChild, e.g., FindFirstChild(tostring(PlotNumber.Value)).	t	beginner	{Instance:FindFirstChild,PVInstance:PivotTo,Players.PlayerAdded,Players:GetUserThumbnailAsync,Player.CharacterAdded}	{}	t	A coding agent could perform static analysis to check if FindFirstChild is being passed a numerical type (like an IntValue's .Value) and suggest wrapping it in tostring() to ensure name-based lookup.	81	0	3	2026-01-03 00:42:03.527	2026-01-08 17:17:15.28851	{"views": 81, "content": " Hi, \\n I’m working on a plot system where each player gets a numbered plot (1–4) and is teleported there. The problem is that players sometimes spawn at the wrong plot, like player 2 spawns at plot 4. For some reason, it’s mainly been those two being mixed up. \\n I’m using FindFirstChild(PlotNumber.Value) to get the plot. So I’m not sure what’s causing this issue. Anyone who could give some advice? Thanks!   \\n ServerScriptServer (script) \\n  local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal Players = game:GetService('Players')\\n\\nlocal PlotHolders = Instance.new(\\"Folder\\")\\nPlotHolders.Parent = ReplicatedStorage\\nPlotHolders.Name = \\"PlotHolders\\"\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal PlotNumber = Instance.new(\\"IntValue\\")\\n\\tPlotNumber.Name = \\"PlotNumber\\"\\n\\tPlotNumber.Parent = player\\n\\tfor i = 1, 4 do\\n\\t\\tif PlotHolders:FindFirstChild(i) then\\n\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal ClaimPlot = Instance.new(\\"ObjectValue\\")\\n\\t\\tClaimPlot.Parent = PlotHolders\\n\\t\\tClaimPlot.Name = i\\n\\t\\tClaimPlot.Value = player\\n\\n\\t\\tPlotNumber.Value = i\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tbreak\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tif PlotNumber.Value == 0 then\\n\\t\\tplayer:kill(\\"Server Full\\")\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal plotFolder = workspace.Map.Plots:FindFirstChild(PlotNumber.Value)\\n\\tplayer.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(character)\\n\\t\\tlocal teleportPart = plotFolder.teleport\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tcharacter:PivotTo(teleportPart.CFrame)\\n\\tend)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal sign = plotFolder.Sign\\n\\tsign.PlayerDisplay.SurfaceGui.PlayerName.Text = player.Name ..\\"'s Plot\\"\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal thumbnailType = Enum.ThumbnailType.HeadShot\\n\\tlocal thumbnailSize = Enum.ThumbnailSize.Size420x420\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal playerIcon, isReady = Players:GetUserThumbnailAsync(player.UserId, thumbnailType, thumbnailSize)\\n\\t\\n\\tsign.PlayerDisplay.SurfaceGui.PlayerIcon.Image = playerIcon\\n\\t\\n\\tsign.PlayerDisplay.SurfaceGui.Enabled = true\\nend)\\n\\nPlayers.PlayerRemoving:Connect(function(player)\\n\\tlocal plotNumber = player.PlotNumber.Value\\n\\tlocal plotClaimed = PlotHolders:FindFirstChild(plotNumber)\\n\\tplotClaimed:Destroy()\\n\\tlocal playerPlot = workspace.Map.Pl", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-03T00:42:03.527Z"}
