636	devforum	4168166	What is the best way to color models? (Studio VS Blender)	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4168166	3D Modeling	Determining the most efficient workflow for coloring 3D models for Roblox, specifically choosing between mesh separation, vertex painting, or color palette texturing.	The most efficient method is using a small color palette texture (e.g., 128x128). Instead of standard unwrapping, scale the UV islands for specific faces down to a single point and move that point onto the corresponding color on the palette. Alternatively, vertex painting can be used to color faces without requiring UV maps.	t	intermediate	{"Emissive Map"}	{}	f	While the creative process is manual, a Blender Python script could be used to automate the 'scale to zero and snap to grid' process for UV points based on selected face colors.	80	0	3	2025-12-20 23:40:25.93	2026-01-08 17:17:13.774188	{"views": 80, "content": " I would like to learn about the workflow of more professional modellers.   \\n The simple question is wether you would take the compromise to seperate whatever faces or parts of the model you wanna color differently,  or  unwrap the model and use a color palette to texture the model. What is the most efficient way to solve this? \\n Reference  \\n         firefox_TjXMbldO4J  386×158 101 KB         \\n My Model  \\n         blender_x9uVBiY8XD  1008×508 113 KB         ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "building-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-20T23:40:25.930Z"}
