d\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-02T22:00:13.607Z"}
650	devforum	3988271	Unknown source of malicious backdoor code: need help identifying where it came from	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/3988271	Scripting	Recurring malicious backdoor script named 'Event' automatically appearing in ServerScriptService, suspected to be caused by a malicious plugin or infected asset.	\N	f	intermediate	{game:GetService,ReplicatedStorage,ServerScriptService,ReplicatedFirst,GetAttribute,GetChildren,FindFirstChild}	{}	t	A script or plugin can be used to scan the entire DataModel for objects named 'Event', search for specific code patterns (like the unique comments or string-to-byte conversion logic), and audit installed plugins for known malicious IDs.	225	5	3	2025-10-11 01:11:06.078	2026-01-08 17:17:28.884363	{"views": 225, "content": " Hi, I don’t know if this is the right topic, but lately, whenever I join a studio session in a specifiic game (with TC, it was made in a group) A malicious piece of code pops up in ServerScriptService, named ''Event\\" \\n I don’t know where this code comes from, our team has experienced it for more than a week, and it’s probably from plugins or whatnot, just hoping somebody here could (maybe?) help where this could possibly come from \\n  --[[\\n    Roblox Lua Script: Event Setup &amp; Filtering\\n\\n    This script is responsible for managing Event-related functionality within a Roblox game.\\n    It utilizes the ReplicatedStorage service to locate and work with a module named EventMain,\\n    which is assumed to contain core logic for detecting and processing hit collisions between game objects.\\n\\n    The primary responsibilities of this script include:\\n    - Retrieving and referencing the EventMain module safely.\\n    - Setting up utility functions to support Event operations.\\n    - Providing filtering mechanisms to ensure Eventes only interact with valid targets.\\n    - Enhancing game performance and accuracy by avoiding unnecessary collision checks.\\n    - Ensuring modularity and reusability through centralized Event handling.\\n\\n    Eventes are commonly used in combat systems, interaction mechanics, or any system requiring spatial detection,\\n    and this script aims to provide a robust foundation for such systems.\\n\\n    It is important that all developers using or modifying this script understand the structure of the EventMain module,\\n    as well as the general design philosophy behind Event-based detection systems.\\n\\n    Dependencies:\\n    - ReplicatedStorage: Used to store and access the EventMain module globally.\\n    - EventMain ModuleScript: Should expose functions to manage and evaluate hit collisions.\\n\\n    Author: Darwin\\n    Date: 24/05/2018\\n--]]\\n\\n\\n-- Services\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage, script = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\"), script\\nlocal ReplicatedFirst = game:GetService", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-10-11T01:11:06.078Z"}
