\\tlocal Tween = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\"):Create(TargetWeight, TweenInfo.new(0.25, Enum.EasingStyle.Exponential), {Value = 1}):Play()\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tTargetWeight:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\\"Value\\"):Connect(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tanimation:AdjustWeight(TargetWeight.Value)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\t\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2026-01-02T16:59:38.409Z"}
671	devforum	4208595	Network ownership messes up NPC ragdolls	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4208595	Networking	NPC ragdoll behavior breaks when network ownership automatically shifts to nearby players, and calling SetNetworkOwner(nil) is being reverted or ignored.	\N	f	intermediate	{SetNetworkOwner,Humanoid.AutomaticScalingEnabled,BallSocketConstraint,Motor6D,Humanoid:ChangeState,HumanoidStateType.Physics,HumanoidStateType.GettingUp}	{}	t	A script could be provided to ensure network ownership is locked to the server by calling SetNetworkOwner(nil) on the character's RootPart specifically, rather than looping through all parts, and ensuring this occurs before changing the Humanoid state to Physics.	75	0	2	2026-01-02 14:12:47.019	2026-01-08 17:17:51.543831	{"views": 75, "content": " Ive found plenty of posts on this but none of them seem to fix it. But what ive been trying to do is make a ragdoll script that can be called by anyscript via a module script \\n I made the inside of a module script so that it can be required by anyscript to ragdoll something which works fine if the server owns the NPC but if the player gets too close it breaks them, ive tried setting networkowner to nil but it imidietly changes back to the player. \\n ive tried disabling  humanoid.AutomaticScalingEnabled  which hasnt worked either \\n  local charEvents = {}\\n\\n--Ragdolls the given player\\nfunction charEvents.Ragdoll(char: Model?,stunTime: number?)\\n\\tlocal hum: Humanoid = char.Humanoid\\n\\thum.RequiresNeck = false\\n\\tprint(hum)\\n\\tfor i,v in char.Torso:GetChildren() do\\n\\t\\tif v:IsA(\\"Motor6D\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal ballConstraint = Instance.new(\\"BallSocketConstraint\\",char.Torso)\\n\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Name = v.Name\\n\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.LimitsEnabled = true\\n\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.TwistLimitsEnabled = true\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal att0 = Instance.new(\\"Attachment\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal att1 = Instance.new(\\"Attachment\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tif string.find(v.Part1.Name,\\"Leg\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Name = \\"ragAtt0\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Parent = v.Part1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Position += Vector3.new(0,1,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Name = \\"ragAtt1\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Parent = char.Torso\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.WorldPosition = att0.WorldPosition\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Parent = char.Torso\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Attachment0 = att0\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Attachment1 = att1\\n\\t\\t\\telseif string.find(v.Part1.Name,\\"Arm\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Name = \\"ragAtt0\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Parent = v.Part1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Position += Vector3.new(0,1,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Name = \\"ragAtt1\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Parent = char.Torso\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.WorldPosition = att0.WorldPosition\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Parent = char.Torso\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Attachment0 = att0\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tballConstraint.Attachment1 = att1\\n\\t\\t\\telseif v.Name == \\"Neck\\" then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Name = \\"ragAtt0\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Parent = v.Part1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt0.Position -= Vector3.new(0,0.5,0)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Name = \\"ragAtt1\\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.Parent = char.Torso\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tatt1.WorldPosition = att0.WorldPosition\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tbal", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-02T14:12:47.019Z"}
