675	devforum	4207996	How do i make it check if the attribute is true	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4207996	Scripting	The NPC pathfinding script calculates a path to a destination before checking its 'occupied' attribute, and attempts to re-select a destination inside the waypoint loop without re-computing the path.	\N	f	beginner	{PathfindingService,Humanoid,GetAttribute,ComputeAsync,MoveTo}	{}	t	Refactor the logic to select an unoccupied destination using a loop or filter before calling ComputeAsync, rather than checking the attribute during the waypoint iteration.	157	1	17	2026-01-02 09:32:07.221	2026-01-08 17:17:56.007917	{"views": 157, "content": " So i have these npcs when it spawns to go to a spot, and if they touch that spot that area “occupied” attribute is turned true, i got everything else working except it doesnt check it if its already occupied and then finds another spot that isnt occupied. \\n  local pfs = game:GetService(\\"PathfindingService\\")\\nlocal NPC = script.Parent\\nlocal debri = game:GetService(\\"Debris\\")\\n\\nlocal waitpoints = workspace:WaitForChild(\\"Areas\\"):GetChildren()\\nlocal randomdes = waitpoints[math.random(1, #waitpoints)]\\n \\n\\n\\n -- Change Destination1 to the name of your destination part and delete this message if you want\\n\\nlocal path = pfs:CreatePath()\\ntask.wait(0.5)\\npath:ComputeAsync(NPC.HumanoidRootPart.Position,randomdes.Position)\\n\\nfor _, waypoint in pairs(path:GetWaypoints()) do\\n\\tif randomdes:GetAttribute(\\"occupied\\") == true then\\n\\t\\trandomdes = waitpoints[math.random(1, #waitpoints)]\\n\\t\\t\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tNPC.Humanoid:MoveTo(waypoint.Position)\\n\\t\\tNPC.Humanoid.MoveToFinished:Wait()\\n\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 17, "created_at": "2026-01-02T09:32:07.221Z"}
678	devforum	4208858	Moving a part attached to the player?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4208858	Physics	Implementing a physics-enabled player limb that can extend forward and bounce off walls while being restricted to the X and Z axes, avoiding the limitations of Motor6D-based animations.	\N	f	intermediate	{Motor6D,RemoteEvent,Instance:Clone,Instance:WaitForChild,Instance:GetChildren}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a script that clones the player's arm, disables the associated Motor6D, and applies physics constraints such as LinearVelocity or AlignPosition to manage movement while locking the Y-axis.	64	2	2	2026-01-02 15:49:18.939	2026-01-08 17:17:58.249197	{"views": 64, "content": " Hello, I’m trying to create a server script that will move the players right arm far in front of them and allow it to bounce off walls, but it should not be able to move on the Y axis, somewhat similar to the video seen below: \\n  \\n    \\nI am aware that this was done through motor6ds and animation, however that would not work for the functionality I’m going for, as ill need it to bounce off walls.  \\n I am unsure of how to go about something like this, as I’ve never done something like it before, and from my experience trying to manipulate a part attached with a motor6d tends to break it or make physics act really wonky. Anyways, I could not find any current post on the dev forum trying to do something similar, but if you know of one I would appreciate if you linked it. Otherwise, any help is appreciated! ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-02T15:49:18.939Z"}
680	devforum	4205361	Third Person Camera Glitching	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4205361	Scripting	Character jitter and glitchy orientation movement when manually setting HumanoidRootPart CFrame to match camera direction without disabling Humanoid.AutoRotate and lack of interpolation.	Disable 'Humanoid.AutoRotate' to prevent the physics engine from fighting the script, and use 'Lerp' or a similar interpolation method within 'RunService:BindToRenderStep' to smooth the character's rotation toward the camera's target direction.	t	intermediate	{RunService,UserInputService,TweenService,CFrame,Humanoid,Humanoid.AutoRotate,Humanoid.CameraOffset,Camera,BindToRenderStep,RaycastParams}	{}	t	An AI agent can identify when a script attempts to rotate a character manually and automatically suggest disabling 'AutoRotate' while providing a boilerplate for CFrame lerping or spring-based smoothing.	88	3	3	2026-01-01 16:53:26.171	2026-01-08 17:17:59.578371	{"views": 88, "content": " I am making a third person, over the shoulder, camera for my game, but how my script is rotating the character is pretty buggy. \\n  \\n    \\nAs you can see and if you try the code out yourself, the character is glitching out when moving in different directions and rotating around, especially when you move backwards.  \\n I want the camera and character to be more smooth and prevent this laggy type of movement. \\n Here is my code: \\n  local Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\nlocal UserInputService = game:GetService(\\"UserInputService\\")\\nlocal TweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\n\\nlocal connection = nil\\nlocal enabled = false\\n\\nlocal player = Players.LocalPlayer\\n\\nlocal character = player.Character or player.CharacterAdded:Wait()\\nlocal camera = workspace.CurrentCamera\\n\\nlocal root = character.PrimaryPart\\n\\nlocal function RotateCharacter()\\n\\n\\tlocal lookVector = camera.CFrame.LookVector\\n\\tlocal flatVector = Vector3.new(lookVector.X, 0, lookVector.Z).Unit\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal targetCFrame = CFrame.new(root.Position, root.Position + flatVector)\\n\\t\\n\\troot.CFrame = targetCFrame\\nend\\n\\nlocal tweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(0.2, Enum.EasingStyle.Quint, Enum.EasingDirection.Out)\\n\\nlocal function TweenOffset(bool)\\n\\t\\n\\tif bool then\\n\\n\\t\\tUserInputService.MouseBehavior = Enum.MouseBehavior.LockCenter\\n\\n\\t\\tlocal tween = TweenService:Create(character.Humanoid, tweenInfo, {CameraOffset = Vector3.new(2, 0.25, 0)})\\n\\t\\ttween:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif connection then connection:Disconnect() end \\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tconnection = RunService.PreRender:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tRotateCharacter()\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tUserInputService.MouseBehavior = Enum.MouseBehavior.Default\\n\\n\\t\\tlocal tween = TweenService:Create(character.Humanoid, tweenInfo, {CameraOffset = Vector3.new(0, 0, 0)})\\n\\t\\ttween:Play()\\n\\n\\t\\tif connection then connection:Disconnect() end \\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nUserInputService.InputBegan:Connect(function(input, processed)\\n\\t\\n\\tif processed then return end\\n\\n\\tif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.Z then\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tenabled = ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-01T16:53:26.171Z"}
681	devforum	4199045	Critical server delay	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4199045	Networking	Server-side hit registration failing for moving targets due to network latency when validating client-side raycasts.	Implement lag compensation by sending timestamps with hit data and performing server-side validation against historical character positions rather than current ones.	t	advanced	{Raycast}	{}	t	A coding agent could implement a server-side position history buffer for players and create a function to interpolate and retrieve player positions at specific past timestamps for hit validation.	116	3	6	2025-12-30 16:57:15.696	2026-01-08 17:18:01.45025	{"views": 116, "content": " I’ve been making weapon system for a while, until i got a problem - exploiters can just send some packets with information about “hit” and it will work, because packets contained info about parts that was “hit” with a bullet. I decided to fix this and make a new communication system: \\n Client is doing the first raycast, and if it’s successful, it waits raycast1.Distance/bulletSpeed and fires another raycast that finally shows a hitmarker, makes bullet hole and sends info (position and direction) to server, where it fires ANOTHER raycast and only then it deals damage or creates an explosion. So yeah, this might work, but… target may move to the side and avoid server raycast because of the client-server delay. That’s very annoying, because 80% of all bullets just don’t deal any damage, but there’s a hitmarker and blood particles. I may perform raycasting from a server and then get the result on client and do hitmarker or bullet hole, but the client will get too much delayed information (Very critical to ingame experience). \\n  Is there a way to make such system that will be protected from exploiters, but also register bullets normally?  \\n  ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-12-30T16:57:15.696Z"}
