710	devforum	4116661	How Can I Efficiently Convert MeshParts to regular Parts?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4116661	3D Modeling	MeshParts with baked-in geometric transformations display (0, 0, 0) Orientation despite being visually rotated, preventing accurate automated replacement with regular Parts.	\N	f	advanced	{}	{}	t	A script could iterate through MeshParts to attempt to extract the CFrame; however, if the rotation is baked into the mesh data itself, an external tool like a GLB optimizer or a custom vertex-data API would be needed to reconstruct the geometry.	118	2	4	2025-12-05 03:09:07.741	2026-01-08 17:18:31.106353	{"views": 118, "content": " I’ve asked a similar question in the past and am asking again in hopes that a possible solution can be made… \\n What I’ve done: \\nI imported a 1:1 model of every Manhattan building into Roblox Studio. \\n          image  1233×610 33.8 KB         \\n The problem: \\nThere are over 40,000 buildings, each as a MeshPart with a unique MeshID. Even the simple, “undetailed” buildings that appear as a regular Part use different MeshIDs, so every one must be downloaded separately. \\n Goal: \\nLoop through all “undetailed” MeshParts and replace them with regular Parts while preserving their size, position, and orientation. \\n The issue: \\nAlthough the MeshParts are visibly rotated, their Orientation property is always (0, 0, 0), so the replacement Parts don’t match their actual rotation. However, Roblox correctly detects their rotation when dragging another part over them. \\n Is there a way to automate converting these MeshParts into regular Parts instead of manually tracing each building with a new Part? ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "building-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-05T03:09:07.741Z"}
