715	devforum	4112858	Decal overlapping on solid part	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4112858	3D Modeling	Z-fighting and rendering artifacts where a transparent texture on a lower part overlaps an opaque part at specific camera distances and angles.	Increase the thickness of the solid part or reposition the parts so that they are adjacent rather than layered on top of one another to prevent rendering conflicts.	t	beginner	{}	{}	f	A plugin could potentially detect coplanar surfaces or surfaces with very small offsets that are likely to cause Z-fighting and highlight them for the builder.	88	0	4	2025-12-03 11:26:28.797	2026-01-08 17:18:36.394213	{"views": 88, "content": " Hello, \\n I am building a country road and I decided to simply use a solid, non-transparent asphalt part and under it a transparent part, with a gravel-like texture. \\n The problem is that when you look at it from above or from specific angles, the gravel texture overlaps the solid asphalt part, while this does not happen when you are “on the road”. \\n Here is some pictures to demonstrate it: \\n         image  742×568 24.9 KB         \\n         image  368×445 28.6 KB         \\n         image  850×633 21.4 KB         \\n I know there is some problems with two or more transparent decals overlapping, but this is just one decal and one solid part so it’s a bit weird. \\n Is there any way to fix this? \\nThanks ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "building-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-03T11:26:28.797Z"}
746	devforum	4071636	Assembly just flies off if you jump on it	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4071636	Physics	Assemblies using VectorForce to counteract gravity fly away at high velocities when interacted with by a player character, specifically when jumping or rubbing against welded parts.	Replace the VectorForce constraint with a LinearVelocity or BodyVelocity constraint to stabilize the assembly's movement, though this alters the physical response to external forces.	t	intermediate	{VectorForce,LinearVelocity,BodyVelocity,AssemblyMass,workspace.Gravity}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a script to dynamically swap VectorForce for a LinearVelocity constraint with a high MaxForce, or implement a script that adjusts the assembly's properties to ignore character-induced impulses while maintaining responsiveness to other physical objects.	68	1	3	2025-11-15 03:59:11.274	2026-01-08 17:19:07.914029	{"views": 68, "content": "   Video of the issue \\n   \\n     \\n   Assembly setup \\n          image  1993×888 248 KB         \\nLike in the image, when I set up an assembly so that: \\n \\n One part is vertical, a wall \\n One part is horizontal, a floor \\n Both welded together \\n VectorForce set so the assembly isnt affected by gravity (workspace.Gravity * part.AssemblyMass) \\n \\n Then whenever I jump on it, it just randomly goes flying? \\nThe  material is metal , so the assembly should be several hundred times heavier than the character \\nEven if I add a LinearVelocity constraint to try resist this cursed phenomenon, I need to set the magnitude really high which sucks since I still want it to be pushable by parts that are actually similar in mass \\n The goal is so that it  doesn’t  do this, would be cool if I can know why this happens \\n Reproduce: \\n spaceshipbug.rbxl  (60.5 KB) \\n \\n Play \\n Jump onto the green part \\n Start jumping while rubbing against the grey part \\n You’ll probably initiate takeoff \\n ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "building-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-11-15T03:59:11.274Z"}
712	devforum	4206746	Simple for loop Not Working	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4206746	Scripting	Using a LocalScript to handle ProximityPrompt events and modify the player's Backpack, which prevents server-side replication and proper tool functionality.	Refactor the logic to use a Server Script for handling ProximityPrompt triggers and inventory management, or use a RemoteEvent to communicate from the client to the server.	t	beginner	{game:GetService,WaitForChild,GetChildren,ProximityPrompt.Triggered,FindFirstChild,Clone}	{}	t	A linter or coding assistant could detect the use of LocalPlayer and Backpack modification within a LocalScript and suggest moving the logic to a Script (server-side) to ensure replication.	75	5	11	2026-01-02 00:20:12.548	2026-01-08 17:18:32.315676	{"views": 75, "content": " Ok this has to be an easy fix and I just do not know why it is not working. If anyone can help me and tell me why I am being so dumb right now I would love it.   \\n  --Give the player ingredients on click\\nlocal RS = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal player = game.Players.LocalPlayer\\n\\nlocal backpack = player.Backpack\\n\\nlocal ingredientsFolder = game.Workspace:WaitForChild(\\"IngredientsGivers\\")\\nlocal potionModelFolder = RS:WaitForChild(\\"PotionModels\\")\\n\\nprint(\\"This works\\")\\n\\nfor _, ingredient in pairs(ingredientsFolder:GetChildren()) do\\n\\tlocal prompt = ingredient:WaitForChild(\\"ProximityPrompt\\")\\n\\tprompt.Triggered:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tlocal clone = potionModelFolder:FindFirstChild(ingredient.Name):Clone()\\n\\t\\tclone.Parent = backpack\\n\\t\\tprint(\\"This works\\")\\n\\tend)\\nend\\n  \\n I don’t know what is wrong here.    I am having a brain fart   ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2026-01-02T00:20:12.548Z"}
