716	devforum	4206673	Remove notifications, reset button, and more	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4206673	Scripting	Race condition errors when calling SetCore before CoreScripts are initialized and passing invalid arguments to CoreScript methods.	Wrap SetCore calls in a retry loop using pcall to wait for the CoreScripts to register the callbacks, and ensure valid arguments are passed to methods like ResetButtonCallback (which accepts a boolean or BindableEvent).	t	beginner	{StarterGui,SetCore,SetCoreGuiEnabled,ResetButtonCallback,PromptSendFriendRequest,PromptUnfriend,PromptBlockPlayer,PromptUnblockPlayer}	{"SetCore: ResetButtonCallback has not been registered by the CoreScripts","Invalid argument to PromptSendFriendRequest","Invalid argument to PromptUnfriend","Invalid argument to PromptBlockPlayer"}	t	An agent could provide a standardized utility function that handles the pcall retry logic for SetCore and provide documentation warnings that 'Prompt' methods in SetCore expect Player objects or specific arguments rather than booleans used for disabling UI.	100	7	12	2026-01-01 23:55:57.412	2026-01-08 17:18:36.682084	{"views": 100, "content": " Hello, \\n I’m trying to remove the reset button from roblox UIs using SetCore from StarterGui service but… getting this error : \\n   00:53:32.278  CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt:215: Invalid argument to PromptSendFriendRequest  -  Client\\n  00:53:32.278  Stack Begin  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.278  Script 'CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt', Line 215 - function PromptRequestFriendPlayer  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  Stack End  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  SetCore: Unexpected error while invoking callback: CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt:215: Invalid argument to PromptSendFriendRequest  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt:308: Invalid argument to PromptUnfriend  -  Client\\n  00:53:32.279  Stack Begin  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  Script 'CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt', Line 308 - function PromptUnfriendPlayer  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  Stack End  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  SetCore: Unexpected error while invoking callback: CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/FriendPlayerPrompt:308: Invalid argument to PromptUnfriend  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/BlockPlayerPrompt:107: Invalid argument to PromptBlockPlayer  -  Client\\n  00:53:32.279  Stack Begin  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  Script 'CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/BlockPlayerPrompt', Line 107 - function PromptBlockPlayer  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  Stack End  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.279  SetCore: Unexpected error while invoking callback: CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/BlockPlayerPrompt:107: Invalid argument to PromptBlockPlayer  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.280  CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/BlockPlayerPrompt:167: Invalid argument to PromptUnblockPlayer  -  Client\\n  00:53:32.280  Stack Begin  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.280  Script 'CoreGui.RobloxGui.CoreScripts/BlockPlayerPrompt', Line 167 - function PromptUnblockPlayer  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.280  Stack End  -  Studio\\n  00:53:32.280  SetCore: Unexpected error while invoking callback: C", "upvotes": 7, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 12, "created_at": "2026-01-01T23:55:57.412Z"}
717	devforum	4206008	Character being sent to the void after a stun?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4206008	Physics	Roblox character flung to the void when BodyVelocity is applied during a network-ownership-based grab move, likely due to physics instability or NaN vectors.	\N	f	intermediate	{BodyVelocity,MaxForce,Vector3.Unit}	{}	t	Check code for vector normalization (Vector3.Unit) without checking if magnitude is greater than zero, and suggest migrating from deprecated BodyMovers to modern Mover Constraints like LinearVelocity.	64	2	5	2026-01-01 20:26:59.058	2026-01-08 17:18:36.938714	{"views": 64, "content": " In my game, stun for killers is handled via a strong body velocity on the character (MaxForce = 400000,0,400000). A specific character has a move that lets him grab a survivor, holding him in place via network ownership and a bodymover (no weld). They automatically drop the survivor when they get stunned during this move. \\n For some reason, there is a very rare chance that the killer gets sent to the void immediately upon getting stunned out of their grab. I assume this is some sort of roblox physics engine bug with the very high values set to the bodyvelocities maxforce, but are there any work-arounds to ensure this doesn’t happen? It’s rare but its game ruining for players when it does happen. ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-01T20:26:59.058Z"}
