718	devforum	4114372	Pointlights acting weird when moved/rotated	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4114372	Other	PointLight appearance and behavior changing inconsistently when the parent model (shelf and candles) is moved or rotated in the workspace.	Ensure that the PointLights are parented to Parts or Attachments that are correctly grouped within the model hierarchy to maintain relative positioning during movement.	f	beginner	{PointLight,Attachment}	{}	t	A script could be used to validate that all lighting objects within a model are children of a physical Part or Attachment rather than the Model object itself, which can cause offset issues.	59	1	5	2025-12-04 00:49:53.787	2026-01-08 17:18:40.572353	{"views": 59, "content": " \\n  What do you want to achieve?  On a shelf I made, I want to have candles. \\n  What is the issue?  I built it and used pointlights for the candles, but now when I move it to the place I’d like it to be the lighting changes. \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  I looked for solutions and tried doing things like changing the brightness in the lighting tab, moving the pointlight itself into a different part, and changing settings in the candles like CastShadow. \\n \\n          Screenshot 2025-12-03 174344  534×357 137 KB         \\n         Screenshot 2025-12-03 174350  479×322 98 KB         \\n         Screenshot 2025-12-03 174828  498×324 120 KB         \\n The images attached show the shelf as it is moved forward and backward, and how the pointlights change when I do so. ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "building-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-04T00:49:53.787Z"}
