721	devforum	4103409	How do I make good water tiles?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4103409	3D Modeling	Visual artifacts and visible seams (grid border effect) at the boundaries of adjacent tiled water parts, particularly when using transparency and glass materials.	Use a single plane mesh instead of multiple block parts and enable the 'DoubleSided' property to ensure the water surface is visible from both sides without internal edge artifacts.	t	intermediate	{MeshPart,DoubleSided,Glass}	{}	t	A plugin or script could be used to programmatically replace tiled block geometry with a single optimized plane mesh or automatically set the DoubleSided property on generated mesh instances.	168	10	9	2025-11-28 23:04:34.581	2026-01-08 17:18:42.339193	{"views": 168, "content": " I am trying to make water tiles for a map, which fit together nicely. The issues are the following: \\nThe tiles have some issues mixing together (tile edges visible on water surface, and underneath the surface) \\nI am unsure exactly how I want to, and how to make an underwater effect (I plan to use a GUI and maybe lighting) \\nI am currently using a reflective smooth plastic for the surface (slightly transparent), with glass under it, and then with a mainly transparent part. I have also tried using glass as the base, and various other combinations. I mainly just need tips making the water tiles look nice, and blend together nicely. \\n Underneath (no lighting) \\n         image  842×348 29.5 KB         \\nSurface \\n         image  807×326 29.9 KB         \\nUnderneath (lighting effects + gui) \\n         image  945×381 19.6 KB         \\nSide view (sides of the water likely wont be visible in game, or atleast very rarely visible) \\n         image  1154×462 80.8 KB         ", "upvotes": 10, "category": "building-support", "comments": 9, "created_at": "2025-11-28T23:04:34.581Z"}
