888	devforum	4195276	RoProxy doesn't support cookie authentication API endpoints?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4195276	Networking	RoProxy strips the Cookie header from outgoing requests for security reasons, causing authentication failures (401 Unauthorized) when attempting to access authenticated Roblox API endpoints via the proxy.	Self-host a private proxy server to maintain control over request headers, as public proxies like RoProxy intentionally omit sensitive authentication data.	t	intermediate	{HttpService,develop.roblox.com}	{"Authentication cookie is empty","User is not authenticated",401}	f	A coding agent could provide a boilerplate configuration for a custom proxy server (using Node.js/Express or Python/Flask) that correctly forwards .ROBLOSECURITY cookies and handles X-CSRF-TOKEN validation.	167	3	13	2025-12-29 13:20:39.328	2026-01-08 17:22:54.956867	{"views": 167, "content": " So currently i’m using roproxy to access roblox api endpoints. It’s fine for endpoints that don’t require authentication at all, but for API endpoints that require cookies. Roproxy doesn’t work. \\n For example, I was testing this endpoint for one of my old games just to play around with httpservice: \\n  https://develop.roproxy.com/v2/places/15775684325  \\n As you can see if you go on the URL: “Authentication cookie is empty”. However, if I replace the domain of  roproxy.com  with  roblox.com  it immediately grants me all the information I want. Only problem is httpservice obviously can’t access this endpoint directly through the roblox domain.   \\n In the script, i’ll get a status code of 401 and the error message in the response body says “User is not authenticated”. However, this is literally my own game. And I’ve put my cookie in the cookie header. So my only idea is that this is a problem with roproxy possibly, maybe roproxy doesnt have support for cookies? I’m not sure. I used inspect element on the roproxy domain for my endpoint and I saw there is no cookie request header like there is in the roblox domain. So my only solution would be to self host my own proxy. Or is there something im doing wrong? \\n I write cookie header like this: \\n  [\\"Cookie\\"] = cookie here\\n  ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2025-12-29T13:20:39.328Z"}
722	devforum	4184480	How do you make it so a client script can detect a part that was created from serverScript?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4184480	Networking	A client script is unable to access an object created on the server and passed via RemoteEvent because the object has not yet replicated to the client's workspace (replication race condition).	\N	f	beginner	{OnServerEvent,OnClientEvent,FireClient,SetNetworkOwner,Debris,ApplyImpulse,ObjectValue,task.wait}	{}	t	An agent can suggest using WaitForChild on the client or implementing client-side projectile prediction where the client creates a local visual bullet while the server handles logic.	107	0	4	2025-12-26 02:24:10.998	2026-01-08 17:18:42.846946	{"views": 107, "content": " I’m having issues with my client script not picking up on a part named “Bullet” that was replicated and parented to workspace by a serverscript and then passed onto the client as a objValue. \\n I tried just passing the part as a value and not wrapped in a objvalue, well that failed, so then I tried passing it as a object value and that also failed, the client never seems to recognize the part exists no matter what. \\n Server Script \\n  game.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, mousePosition, Hull, Barrel)\\n\\n\\tlocal bullet = game.ReplicatedStorage.Bullet:Clone()\\n\\tbullet.Parent = workspace\\n\\tbullet.CanCollide = false\\n\\tbullet.CFrame = Barrel.Attachment.WorldCFrame\\n\\n\\ttask.wait()\\n\\tbullet:SetNetworkOwner(player)\\n\\t\\n\\tgame.Debris:AddItem(bullet, 10)\\n\\tlocal objvalue = Instance.new(\\"ObjectValue\\")\\n\\tobjvalue.Value = bullet\\n\\t\\n\\tgame.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired:FireClient(player, objvalue)\\n\\t\\nend)\\n  \\n Local Script \\n  game.ReplicatedStorage.ShotFired.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(objValue)\\n\\tlocal bullet = objValue.Value\\n\\tbullet:ApplyImpulse(bullet.CFrame.LookVector * bullet.AssemblyMass * 500)\\nend)\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-26T02:24:10.998Z"}
723	devforum	4204069	Type Error: Type unknown could not be converted into number	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4204069	Scripting	Luau type checking error 'Type unknown could not be converted into number' occurring in strict mode, likely due to performing arithmetic on a variable or table length (#Lerps) that the type checker cannot verify as a number.	\N	f	intermediate	{BasePart,CFrame,setmetatable,getmetatable,Enum.EasingStyle,Enum.EasingDirection}	{"Type unknown could not be converted into number"}	t	A coding agent could resolve this by ensuring the 'Lerps' table is explicitly typed as an array (e.g., '{Lerp}') and refining the metatable __index definition to properly enable autocomplete and inheritance for the custom class.	154	6	11	2026-01-01 06:30:20.904	2026-01-08 17:18:42.944777	{"views": 154, "content": " Hi DevForum users! \\n So while scripting, i changed the code to be strict, but when trying to specify types, for some reasson, some parts of the code have this weird thing. \\n         image  624×138 6.36 KB         \\n This is how i define the types: \\n  export type Lerp = {\\n\\tCompleted : any,\\n\\tStopped   : any,\\n\\tDeleted   : any,\\n\\tObject    : BasePart,\\n\\tStarting  : CFrame,\\n\\tDTime     : number,\\n\\tLoop      : number,\\n\\tTime      : number,\\n\\tPlaying   : boolean,\\n\\tReverse   : boolean,\\n\\tId        : number,\\n\\tAlpha     : number,\\n\\tValue     : CFrame,\\n\\tInfo      : LerpInfo\\n}\\n\\nexport type LerpService = typeof(setmetatable({}::{\\n\\tcreate : () -&gt; Lerp\\n}, {}::{\\n\\t__index       : typeof(getmetatable(   ({}::Lerp)  )),    -- returns CarControls\\n}))\\n  \\n And here is how i construct the new Lerp (which is my class) \\n  function LerpService.create(Object: any, Property: {[any]: CFrame}, LerpInfo: LerpInfo): Lerp\\n\\tlocal Name: any, Value: any = GetTableValues(Property)\\n\\n\\tlocal Lerp = setmetatable({}:: Lerp,LerpService)\\n\\tLerp.Completed = GoodSignal.new()\\n\\tLerp.Stopped   = GoodSignal.new()\\n\\tLerp.Deleted   = GoodSignal.new()\\n\\tLerp.Object    = Object \\t\\t\\t:: BasePart\\n\\tLerp.Starting  = Object.CFrame\\n\\tLerp.DTime     = 0\\n\\tLerp.Loop      = 0\\n\\tLerp.Time      = 0\\n\\tLerp.Playing   = false\\n\\tLerp.Reverse   = false\\n\\tLerp.Id        = #Lerps + 1\\n\\tLerp.Alpha     = 0\\n\\tLerp.Value     = Value              :: any\\n\\tLerp.Info      = LerpInfo or LerpService.NewLerpInfo(1,Enum.EasingStyle.Linear,Enum.EasingDirection.Out,0,false,0) :: LerpInfo\\n\\tCreationWarnings(Lerp, Lerp.Info)\\n\\n\\tDebug.print(\\"Lerp (\\"..Lerp.Id..\\") created:\\",Lerp)\\n\\treturn Lerp\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2026-01-01T06:30:20.904Z"}
725	devforum	4202178	Purpose of a single script architecture	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4202178	Scripting	Understanding the benefits and implementation best practices of Single Script Architecture (SSA) in Roblox, specifically regarding module coupling and the use of module loaders.	\N	f	intermediate	{}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a boilerplate framework for Single Script Architecture, including a module loader with Init/Start lifecycle methods and dependency injection to reduce coupling.	135	7	5	2025-12-31 16:41:32.533	2026-01-08 17:18:47.104573	{"views": 135, "content": " Hi. I will be honest. I have started a lot of probjects but completed non in 2025. Part of the reason is due to the fear of messy code. I am using a  single script architecture  and I am wondering what are the real benefits of using a single script architecture. I heard a lot about reusability but I am wondering if there are other benefits. \\n Usually my systems/services do need to require each other(they do not have circular dependencies). However, I am told that that is a bad practice as they are then coupled together. \\n Also, should systems/services be loaded using a module loader? should Init function take in parameters? \\n Once again, I really want to know more about the benefits of single script architecture and also on your experience where it really help you to organsie your code ", "upvotes": 7, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-31T16:41:32.533Z"}
727	devforum	4205521	How to create a Knit signal from the CLIENT to the CLIENT (solution)	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4205521	Scripting	Creating a client-to-client communication signal within the Knit framework where Knit.CreateSignal() is unavailable on the client-side.	Manually require the Signal module from the project packages and instantiate a new signal using Signal.new() within the controller instead of relying on Knit's server-side Signal creation method.	t	intermediate	{Knit,UserInputService.GamepadConnected,UserInputService.GamepadDisconnected,Signal}	{"tried to call a nil value"}	t	A coding agent could identify when a developer is trying to use server-style signal creation on the client in Knit and suggest importing the base Signal library to handle internal controller events.	78	2	2	2026-01-01 17:51:31.934	2026-01-08 17:18:47.804176	{"views": 78, "content": " Hello everyone. So this isn’t exactly a problem but instead, something I haven’t found anywhere on the internet but on ChatGPT with a few prompts and I’d like to help people save their time. \\n Usually when you want to send a piece of information from the server to the client or vice-versa, you’d do something like: \\n  --Side: Server.\\nlocal newSignal = Service.Client.CreateSignal();\\nnewSignal:Fire(player, newInfo);\\n  \\n And then: \\n  --Side: Client\\nService = Knit.GetService();\\nService.newSignal:Connect(function(newInfo)\\n   print(\\"Got new info:\\", newInfo);\\nend);\\n  \\n Cool. But what if I want to similarly warn all my controllers (client side) that something on the client side happened that is interesting to many controllers? If I wasn’t clear enough, I’ll give you an example. \\nI was trying to warn all my controllers (UIController, AimController, etc…) that the client connected a gamepad (device switch). That way, UIController could instantly change icons accordingly to the new device type. \\nThe solution is: We, naturally, have a InputController that listens to UserInputService.GamepadConnected/Disconnected. That exact same controller will create the signal and fire it when needed. \\n  --Side: Client\\n\\nfunction InputController:KnitStart()\\n    local function warnEveryone()\\n    --???\\n    end;\\n    UserInputService.GamepadConnected:Connect(warnEveryone)\\n    UserInputService.GamepadDisconnected:Connect(warnEveryone)\\nend;\\n  \\n We can’t use Knit.CreateSignal() here, I’ve tried and it says that we tried to call a nil value. \\nThe solution is to go straight to the Packages.Signal module and use the ‘new’ function to manually create ourselves a signal like so: \\n  --Side: Client\\nlocal SignalModule = require(ReplicatedStorage.Packages.Signal);\\n\\n\\nfunction InputController:KnitStart()\\n    self.newSignal = SignalModule.new();\\n    local function warnEveryone()\\n        self.newSignal:Fire(newDevice);--This will warn everyone that used InputController.newSignal:Connect(function)\\n    end;\\n    Use", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2026-01-01T17:51:31.934Z"}
729	devforum	4203861	AnimationTrack limit of 32 tracks for one Animator exceeded, new animations will not be played. with preloading anims	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4203861	Animation	Roblox Animator exceeds the hard limit of 32 simultaneously playing AnimationTracks during mass preloading because AnimationTrack:Stop() is not instantaneous and tracks remain in the playing state until the next Stepped event.	Throttling the preloading sequence by monitoring Animator:GetPlayingAnimationTracks() and yielding with task.wait() if the count is 32 or higher before attempting to play and stop the next track.	t	intermediate	{ContentProvider,Animator,AnimationTrack,GetPlayingAnimationTracks,PreloadAsync,LoadAnimation,Play,Stop,RunService.Stepped}	{"AnimationTrack limit of 32 tracks for one Animator exceeded, new animations will not be played."}	t	Create a wrapper or utility module for animation loading that includes a 'throttle' check against the GetPlayingAnimationTracks count to prevent engine-level limit warnings.	211	1	5	2026-01-01 04:25:56.913	2026-01-08 17:18:49.639976	{"views": 211, "content": " I have this script to preload animations (and their events) by playing them and stopping them instantly on load. It works like a charm and prevents weird lag or stutter when playing an animation for the first time. However, now that I have over 32 animations to load, it gives me this error in my console. Nothing is actually broken and everything still loads fine but it’s just annoying and was wondering if anyone knew a better way to load animation events or prevent the error from throwing? Here is my module \\n  local ContentProvider = game:GetService(\\"ContentProvider\\")\\n\\nlocal AnimationPreloader = {}\\nAnimationPreloader.__index = AnimationPreloader\\n\\nfunction AnimationPreloader.new(character, animations)\\n\\tlocal self = setmetatable({}, AnimationPreloader)\\n\\tself.Character = character\\n\\tself.Animator = character:WaitForChild(\\"Humanoid\\"):WaitForChild(\\"Animator\\")\\n\\tself.Animations = {}\\n\\tself.Tracks = {}\\n\\n\\tlocal assetsToLoad = {}\\n\\tfor _, anim in ipairs(animations) do\\n\\t\\ttable.insert(assetsToLoad, anim)\\n\\tend\\n\\tContentProvider:PreloadAsync(assetsToLoad)\\n\\n\\tfor _, anim in ipairs(animations) do\\n\\t\\tlocal track = self.Animator:LoadAnimation(anim)\\n\\t\\tself.Animations[anim.Name] = anim\\n\\t\\tself.Tracks[anim.Name] = track\\n\\t\\ttrack:Play()\\n\\t\\ttrack:Stop()\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\treturn self\\nend\\n\\nfunction AnimationPreloader:GetTrack(name)\\n\\treturn self.Tracks[name]\\nend\\n\\nfunction AnimationPreloader:Play(name, fadeTime, loop)\\n\\tlocal track = self.Tracks[name]\\n\\tif track then\\n\\t\\ttrack:Play(fadeTime or 0)\\n\\t\\tif loop then\\n\\t\\t\\ttrack.Looped = true\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn track\\nend\\n\\nreturn AnimationPreloader\\n  ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2026-01-01T04:25:56.913Z"}
