738	devforum	4199447	Issues with c4 like note7	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4199447	Networking	Replication failure and 'attempt to index nil with Position' error when passing an Instance reference through a BridgeNet signal to other clients.	Retrieve the tool or handle instance from the activator's character on the receiving client side instead of relying on the passed Instance parameter, ensuring the reference exists in the local workspace.	t	intermediate	{ReplicatedStorage,CollectionService,BridgeNet,Explosion,Sound,task.wait}	{"attempt to index nil with 'Position'","RemoteEvents is not a valid member of [ReplicatedStorage]"}	t	A coding agent could identify that Instance objects passed through remote signals (or BridgeNet) may not be replicated or accessible on the receiving client at the time of execution, and suggest passing the Player or a string path instead, or adding a WaitForChild check.	88	0	3	2025-12-30 19:49:45.008	2026-01-08 17:19:00.280236	{"views": 88, "content": " Hello everyone, so i am trying to make a c4 like note7, without using remote events, (using bridgenet) But the problem, is that it works for one player and not for the other players. \\n Client: \\n  local replicated = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal collection = game:GetService(\\"CollectionService\\")\\n\\nlocal bridgeNet = require(replicated.SPH_Assets.Modules.BridgeNet)\\n\\nlocal repC4 = bridgeNet.CreateBridge(\\"C4ReplicationStuff\\")\\n\\ncollection:GetInstanceAddedSignal(\\"Note7\\"):Connect(function(note7:Tool)\\n\\tlocal handle = note7:WaitForChild(\\"Handle\\")\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal cooldown = false\\n\\n\\tlocal updtick = 2\\n\\n\\tlocal function Tick()\\n\\t\\tupdtick = updtick * 0.9\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tlocal function Boom(Pos)\\n\\t\\tlocal exp = Instance.new(\\"Explosion\\")\\n\\t\\texp.Position = Pos\\n\\t\\texp.BlastRadius = 20\\n\\t\\texp.BlastPressure = 2500000\\n\\t\\texp.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\tlocal expsound = Instance.new(\\"Sound\\")\\n\\t\\texpsound.SoundId = \\"rbxassetid://12222084\\"\\n\\t\\texpsound.Volume = 1\\n\\t\\texpsound.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\texpsound:Play()\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tlocal function TickSound(handleclone)\\n\\t\\twhile updtick &gt; 0.05 do\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(updtick)\\n\\t\\t\\tTick()\\n\\t\\t\\thandleclone.Click:Play()\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tBoom(handleclone.Position)\\n\\t\\tcooldown = false\\n\\t\\tupdtick = 2\\n\\t\\tHandle.Transparency = 0\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tlocal function ToolActivated(Handle)\\n\\t\\tif not cooldown then\\n\\t\\t\\trepC4:Fire(Handle)\\n\\t\\t\\tcooldown = true\\n\\t\\t\\tHandle.Plant:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal handleclone = Handle:Clone()\\n\\t\\t\\tHandle.Transparency = 1\\n\\t\\t\\thandleclone.CanCollide = true\\n\\t\\t\\thandleclone.Parent = workspace\\n\\t\\t\\tHandle.Plant.Ended:Wait()\\n\\t\\t\\thandleclone.Click:Play()\\n\\t\\t\\tTickSound(handleclone)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\trepC4:Connect(function(Handle)\\n\\t\\tToolActivated(Handle)\\n\\tend)\\n\\t\\n\\tnote7.Activated:Connect(function()\\n\\t\\tToolActivated(handle)\\n\\tend)\\nend)\\n  \\n Server: \\n  local replicated = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\n\\nlocal bridgeNet = require(replicated.SPH_Assets.Modules.BridgeNet)\\n\\nlocal repC4 = bridgeNet.CreateBridge(\\"C4ReplicationStuff\\")\\n\\nrepC4:Connect(function(plr, handle)\\n\\trepC4:FireAllInRangeExcept(plr, handle.Position, 125)\\nend)\\n  \\n V", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-30T19:49:45.008Z"}
740	devforum	4204070	Part growing slow	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4204070	Scripting	Sequential axis resizing is causing delays due to a yielding loop within a custom function, and performance is degrading over time due to an infinite instance-spawning loop.	Remove the wait(0.1) yielding inside the Add function to allow calculations to finish instantly, use task.wait() for better accuracy, and remove the infinite while-loop that spawns parts in the RemoteEvent listener.	f	beginner	{Vector3.new,RemoteEvent.OnServerEvent,RemoteEvent.FireAllClients,Instance.new,SetAttribute,GetAttribute,task.wait}	{}	t	Refactor the script to update all components of the Vector3 size at once rather than calling a yielding function for each axis, and identify the memory leak caused by the 'while true do' loop spawning parts.	113	4	11	2026-01-01 06:31:03.548	2026-01-08 17:19:01.616081	{"views": 113, "content": " For some reason my part is growing slowly, when it should all be growing at the same time, does anyone know how to fix this? It’s supposed to grow once every second, and that’s working perfectly fine. \\n  local function Add(numb1,numb2)\\n\\tlocal result = numb1\\n\\tfor i = 1,numb2 do\\n\\t\\tnumb1 = numb1 + 1\\n\\t\\twait(0.1) --To let it think\\n\\tend\\n\\tscript.Parent:SetAttribute(\\"Result\\",numb1)\\n\\tgame.ReplicatedStorage.RemoteEvent:FireAllClients(script.Parent:GetAttribute(\\"Result\\"),numb1,numb2)\\n\\t\\n\\tgame.ReplicatedStorage.RemoteEvent.OnServerEvent:Wait()\\nend\\n\\nlocal function WaitForChild(item,name)\\n\\tlocal child = item:FindFirstChild(name)\\n\\t\\n\\tif child then return child end\\n\\t\\n\\twhile true do\\n\\t\\tchild = item:FindFirstChild(name)\\n\\t\\tif child then return child end\\n\\t\\titem.ChildAdded:Wait()\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\ngame.ReplicatedStorage.RemoteEvent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(plr,numb,result)\\n\\tif numb == result then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\twhile true do --Punish it so it can learn\\n\\t\\t\\twait()\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal workspace = WaitForChild(script:FindFirstAncestorOfClass(\\"DataModel\\"),\\"Workspace\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal newPart = Instance.new(\\"Part\\",script:FindFirstAncestorOfClass(\\"DataModel\\"):FindFirstChild(workspace.Name))\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n\\nwhile true do\\n\\tAdd(script.Parent.Size.X, 1)\\n\\tscript.Parent.Size = Vector3.new(script.Parent:GetAttribute(\\"Result\\"),script.Parent.Size.Y,script.Parent.Size.Z)\\n\\n\\tAdd(script.Parent.Size.Y, 1)\\n\\tscript.Parent.Size = Vector3.new(script.Parent.Size.X,script.Parent:GetAttribute(\\"Result\\"),script.Parent.Size.Z)\\n\\n\\tAdd(script.Parent.Size.Z, 1)\\n\\tscript.Parent.Size = Vector3.new(script.Parent.Size.X,script.Parent.Size.Y,script.Parent:GetAttribute(\\"Result\\"))\\n\\n\\twait(1)\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 4, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2026-01-01T06:31:03.548Z"}
