747	devforum	4205415	RBXScriptConnection	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4205415	Scripting	Confusion regarding whether RBXScriptSignal:Connect() returns the result of the passed callback function or an RBXScriptConnection object.	The :Connect() method always returns an RBXScriptConnection object, which is used to manage the event (e.g., Disconnect). The return value of the callback function passed to Connect is ignored by the engine because the callback is executed asynchronously when the event fires.	t	beginner	{RBXScriptConnection,RBXScriptSignal,Touched,Connect}	{}	t	An AI coding agent can identify this pattern and explain that event handlers are 'fire-and-forget' callbacks where return values cannot be captured by the scope that established the connection.	164	28	10	2026-01-01 17:12:49.435	2026-01-08 17:19:07.914965	{"views": 164, "content": " I find this a bit confusing. \\n  local Part = script.Parent\\n\\nlocal connection = Part.Touched:Connect(function(otherPart)\\n    return otherPart\\nend\\n  \\n Which will the  connection  in that code be, a  BasePart  or a  RBXScriptConnection ? ", "upvotes": 28, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 10, "created_at": "2026-01-01T17:12:49.435Z"}
749	devforum	4202078	Weak metatables not working?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4202078	Scripting	Weak table entries (mode 'k') are not disappearing immediately after the key reference is set to nil due to non-deterministic Garbage Collection timing.	Garbage collection in Luau is not immediate. To observe the entry being removed, you must wait for a GC cycle to occur or force memory pressure to trigger one, as setting a reference to nil only makes the object eligible for collection.	t	intermediate	{setmetatable,__mode}	{}	f	A coding agent could provide a conceptual explanation of Luau's incremental garbage collector and suggest testing methods like creating temporary allocations to trigger a collection cycle.	103	8	7	2025-12-31 15:56:23.673	2026-01-08 17:19:12.010177	{"views": 103, "content": " I’m trying to set up a metatable with weak key references, but for some reason, it’s not working as it did before? \\n  local weakTable = setmetatable({}, {__mode = \\"k\\"})\\n\\nlocal reference = {}\\nweakTable[reference] = \\"hi\\"\\n\\nprint(weakTable) -- {[Table(CA5DF4CB4152A33E)] = \\"hi\\"}\\nreference = nil\\nprint(weakTable) -- should print \\"{}\\" but prints {[Table(CA5DF4CB4152A33E)] = \\"hi\\"}\\n  \\n Am I misremembering how weak metatables are handled? Is this a bug? \\nThanks for reading   ", "upvotes": 8, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2025-12-31T15:56:23.673Z"}
751	devforum	4202665	Need Help: Getting Services that are not children of DataModel	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4202665	Scripting	Programmatically retrieving a complete list of all Roblox Services, including those that are not currently instantiated as children of the DataModel (game).	Utilize the ReflectionService:GetClasses() method to fetch all Instance-derived classes and filter for those ending with the 'Service' naming convention, then call game:GetService() to instantiate or retrieve them.	t	intermediate	{DataModel,ReflectionService,GetService,GetChildren,GetClasses,ConfigService,MessagingService,MemoryStoreService}	{"is not a service"}	t	A coding assistant can implement the ReflectionService logic to dynamically generate a list of available services for plugins, autocomplete features, or debugging tools.	157	2	13	2025-12-31 19:37:23.251	2026-01-08 17:19:13.223029	{"views": 157, "content": " So, I have this plugin that I’m making that get’s the Services by looking at the Children of the game DataModel. I just came across ConfigService and tried to require it using my plugin. And as it’s not a children of the game DataModel I cannot quick Require it. I cannot check if some other payed plugins like Require Autocomplete can do it as I cannot pay for them. So: \\n \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  \\nGet a list of all Services containing also Services that are not Children of the game DataModel \\n \\n \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  \\nLooked up on the Api, Docs, Tried serching in the code of some other free plugins and Messing up with some stuff in Studio. \\n \\n \\n This is the code I use rn to Get the Services: \\n  local function GetServices()\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal Services: {Instance} = {}\\n\\t\\n\\tfor _, Child in game:GetChildren() do\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t-- Avoid having services with spaces like [\\"Run Service\\"] as variable names\\n\\t\\tlocal ServiceName = string.gsub(Child.Name, \\" \\", \\"\\")\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t-- Check if it's actually a service\\n\\t\\tlocal Success, Error = pcall(function()\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Service = game:GetService(ServiceName)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tif Service == nil then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\terror(\\"[Autocomplete] \\" ..ServiceName ..\\" is not a service\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif Success then\\n\\t\\t\\ttable.insert(Services, Child)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\treturn table.freeze(Services)\\nend\\n  ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2025-12-31T19:37:23.251Z"}
752	devforum	4204974	Pause Music When WindowFocusReleased And Vice Versa	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4204974	Scripting	The script uses game:GetChildren() which only iterates through top-level services, failing to find Sound and SoundGroup objects nested within those services.	Replace game:GetChildren() with game:GetDescendants() to recursively search through all objects in the game hierarchy for Sound and SoundGroup instances.	t	beginner	{UserInputService,WindowFocusReleased,WindowFocused,GetChildren,GetDescendants,Sound,SoundGroup}	{}	t	An automated linter or coding assistant can detect when a script attempts to find specific instance types (like Sounds) using GetChildren on the DataModel (game) or a Service, and suggest using GetDescendants or searching within a specific relevant service like SoundService.	105	4	4	2026-01-01 14:14:47.423	2026-01-08 17:19:14.255868	{"views": 105, "content": " I’m trying to create a system which pauses all sounds in game when the window loses focus (Switching to other tab) and resume all sounds in game when the window focuses. \\n I tried to create the system but it didn’t work. \\n This is my script: \\n  local UIS = game.UserInputService\\n\\nUIS.WindowFocusReleased:Connect(function()\\n\\tfor i, things in game:GetChildren() do\\n\\t\\tif things:IsA(\\"Sound\\") or things:IsA(\\"SoundGroup\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tthings:SetAttribute(\\"OriginalVolume\\", things.Volume)\\n\\t\\t\\tthings.Volume = 0\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tif things:IsA(\\"Sound\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif things.IsPlaying then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tthings:SetAttribute(\\"WasPlaying\\", true)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tthings:Pause()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\telseif things:IsA(\\"SoundGroup\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tthings.Volume = 0\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n\\nUIS.WindowFocused:Connect(function()\\n\\tfor i, things in game:GetChildren() do\\n\\t\\tif things:IsA(\\"Sound\\") or things:IsA(\\"SoundGroup\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal OriginalVolume = things:GetAttribute(\\"OriginalVolume\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tthings.Volume = OriginalVolume\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tif things:IsA(\\"Sound\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif things:GetAttribute(\\"WasPlaying\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tthings:Resume()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\telseif things:IsA(\\"SoundGroup\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tthings.Volume = OriginalVolume\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend)\\t\\n  \\n Can somebody help me to create this system? \\n Thank you, \\nXMLcard ", "upvotes": 4, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-01T14:14:47.423Z"}
