793	devforum	4203087	Client Side Moving Platforms	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4203087	Networking	Instance replication race condition where RemoteEvent parameters arrive as nil on the client because the referenced Instance (Platform) has not yet replicated to the client's workspace.	Use CollectionService to tag platforms and handle them via a local manager script, or place the client-side logic inside a script parented to the platform so it only runs once the platform exists for that client.	t	intermediate	{RemoteEvent,TweenService,RunService,CollectionService,Players.PlayerAdded,FireClient,OnClientEvent,StreamingEnabled}	{"the LocalScript sees the platform parameter as nil"}	t	A coding agent could refactor the system to use a 'Component' pattern with CollectionService, where the client watches for specific tags and applies the Tween/RunService logic to newly arrived instances automatically.	102	2	4	2025-12-31 22:18:27.594	2026-01-08 17:19:59.058265	{"views": 102, "content": " Hi everyone! \\n I am trying to create a moving platform for a platformer game. I want the platform movement to be client side. Currently, my platform in the workspace has a script attached that runs this code (in the real project I have this ran from a ModuleScript). \\n  local Platform = script.Parent\\n\\nfunction Slide(Platform)\\n\\tlocal SlideEvent = PlatformEvents:WaitForChild(\\"SlideEvent\\")\\n\\tlocal SlideDistance = Platform:GetAttribute(\\"SlideDistance\\") or 10\\n\\tlocal SlideTime = Platform:GetAttribute(\\"SlideTime\\") or 2\\n\\tlocal function onPlayerAdded(Player)\\n\\t\\tSlideEvent:FireClient(Player, Platform, SlideDistance, SlideTime)\\n\\tend\\n\\tPlayers.PlayerAdded:Connect(onPlayerAdded)\\nend\\n\\nSlide(Platform)\\n  \\n I have a RemoteEvent in ReplicatedStorage that a LocalScript in StarterPlayerScripts is listening to with this code \\n  local function Slide(Platform, SlideDistance, SlideTime)\\n\\tlocal TweenService = game:GetService(\\"TweenService\\")\\n\\tlocal RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\n\\t-- tween the platform movement\\n\\tlocal SlideTweenInfo = TweenInfo.new(SlideTime, Enum.EasingStyle.Cubic, Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, -1, true)\\n\\tlocal Tween = TweenService:Create(Platform, SlideTweenInfo, {Position = Platform.Position * Vector3.new(SlideDistance, 0, 0)})\\n\\tTween:Play()\\n\\t-- update velocity with RunService\\n\\tlocal PrevPosition = Platform.Position\\n\\tRunService.Stepped:Connect(function(_, deltaTime)\\n\\t\\tlocal CurrentPosition = Platform.Position\\n\\t\\tlocal DeltaPosition = CurrentPosition - PrevPosition\\n\\t\\tlocal Velocity = DeltaPosition / deltaTime\\n\\t\\tPlatform.AssemblyLinearVelocity = Velocity\\n\\t\\tPrevPosition = CurrentPosition\\n\\tend)\\nend\\nSlideEvent.OnClientEvent:Connect(Slide)\\n  \\n The error I am having is that when I try to test the game, the LocalScript sees the platform parameter as nil and does nothing. I think this is to do with the player loading before the workspace, so when we call the slide function the platform has not loaded in yet and therefore we send nil. I have tried only sending the event when t", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-31T22:18:27.594Z"}
770	devforum	4204570	Is Tweening shapes possible?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4204570	Animation	Attempting to animate a BasePart's Shape property using TweenService, which is unsupported for non-numeric types.	Tweening is not possible for Enum properties like Shape because they lack numeric interpolation. Geometry in Roblox cannot be natively morphed; you must use alternatives like swapping parts, MeshPart deformations, or transparency fading between two shapes.	t	beginner	{TweenService,TweenInfo,BasePart.Shape,Enum.PartType}	{}	t	A linter or coding assistant can validate the properties table in TweenService:Create() to ensure the target properties are tweenable types (e.g., number, Vector3, CFrame, Color3) and flag Enums or booleans as invalid.	95	8	3	2026-01-01 11:14:23.515	2026-01-08 17:19:32.968411	{"views": 95, "content": " Im experimenting with my code out of pure curiosity. \\n Im trying to tween a sphere into a block shape. Is this possible? \\n I have tried this: \\n  function animation.Test(x:BasePart)\\n\\tlocal info = TweenInfo.new(3, Enum.EasingStyle.Sine, Enum.EasingDirection.Out, 0, false, 0.5)\\n\\n\\tlocal properties = {\\n\\t\\t[\\"Shape\\"] = Enum.PartType.Block\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tlocal tween = tweenServ:Create(x, info, properties)\\n\\n\\ttween:Play()\\nend\\n  \\n it is not working so far, but I would love to hear what can or cannot happen with this type of code. \\n All responses appreciated! ", "upvotes": 8, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2026-01-01T11:14:23.515Z"}
772	devforum	3899437	How do i actually use profile store in practice	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/3899437	DataStore	Efficiently synchronizing and accessing player data from ProfileStore on the client for GUI updates without creating an excessive number of RemoteEvents for individual stats.	The thread suggests creating ValueInstances (like NumberValue or StringValue) inside a 'Data' folder within the Player object to replicate values automatically, though a reply warns this may cause unnecessary network overhead and security visibility issues.	f	intermediate	{ProfileStore,DataStore,RemoteEvent,RemoteFunction}	{}	t	Generate a centralized data-bridge module that uses a single RemoteEvent to fire state updates to the client, or utilizes Attributes on the Player object for automatic replication of simple key-value pairs.	233	6	8	2025-08-25 18:31:04.254	2026-01-08 17:19:38.725851	{"views": 233, "content": " I wondered how do i actually use profile store. Right now i find it really not really practical (most probably because im used on using normal datastores). I don’t know how to easily access data from the client for example for making GUIs display a stat value without making absurdly high amount of remote events as i have like 15 stats in my game. \\n I’ve been trying to make it somehow modular so a module script would do the work for me, but it just never works. Tried using remote functions to get the data from server to client and a one single remote event to handle all the stats, but it never works. ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2025-08-25T18:31:04.254Z"}
774	devforum	4179243	How to make an automatic Teleporter system	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4179243	Scripting	Implementing a system to automatically teleport up to 8 players to unique spawn points based on a match state or 'Timeline' value.	Iterate through the current player list using a loop (ipairs) and use the loop index to assign each player to a corresponding index in the spawn points array.	t	beginner	{Players:GetPlayers,HumanoidRootPart,MoveTo,RespawnLocation,task.spawn,task.wait}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a state-listener for a StringValue and a loop that assigns character CFrame or RespawnLocation based on an array of Parts.	279	6	12	2025-12-24 08:42:57.98	2026-01-08 17:19:39.359145	{"views": 279, "content": " How do you make an automatic teleporting system with 8 different spawn points one for each Player? And buy using a Timeline System to know when it is a match or lobby time or the teleporting time! \\n Here’s the script: \\n  local SpawnPoint = {\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"1\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"2\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"3\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"4\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"5\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"6\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"7\\"],\\n\\tgame.Workspace[\\"Spawn System\\"][\\"8\\"]\\n}\\n\\nlocal Timeline = game.ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild(\\"Timeline\\")\\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\n\\n\\nlocal occupiedSpawns = {}\\nlocal spawnCooldown = 10\\n\\n\\nfunction getAvailableSpawn()\\n\\tfor _, spawn in ipairs(SpawnPoint) do\\n\\t\\tif not occupiedSpawns[spawn] then\\n\\t\\t\\treturn spawn\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn nil\\nend\\n\\n\\nfunction occupySpawn(spawn)\\n\\tif spawn then\\n\\t\\toccupiedSpawns[spawn] = true\\n\\t\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(spawnCooldown)\\n\\t\\t\\toccupiedSpawns[spawn] = nil\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nfunction TeleportPlayer(player)\\n\\tif not player or not player.Character or not player.Character:FindFirstChild(\\"HumanoidRootPart\\") then\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal availableSpawn = getAvailableSpawn()\\n\\tif availableSpawn then\\n\\t\\toccupySpawn(availableSpawn)\\n\\t\\n\\t\\tplayer.Character:MoveTo(availableSpawn.Position)\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"No available spawn points!\\")\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nlocal function shouldTeleport()\\n\\tif Timeline and Timeline.Value then\\n\\t\\treturn Timeline.Value == \\"Teleport\\"\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn false\\nend\\n\\n\\nlocal debounce = {}\\n\\nscript.Parent.Touched:Connect(function(hit)\\n\\tif not shouldTeleport() then\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal character = hit.Parent\\n\\tlocal humanoid = character:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\")\\n\\t\\n\\tif humanoid then\\n\\t\\tlocal player = Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(character)\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif player and not debounce[player] then\\n\\t\\t\\tdebounce[player] = true\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tTeleportPlayer(player)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\ttask.spawn(function()\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttask.wait(1)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdebounce[player] = nil\\n\\t\\t\\tend)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 12, "created_at": "2025-12-24T08:42:57.980Z"}
776	devforum	4194522	Best way to port an existing large game to Rojo/VS Code? (Script Dumping)	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194522	Scripting	Automatically exporting and converting an existing Roblox Studio project hierarchy and scripts into a Rojo-compatible local file structure for external IDE use.	Use the 'rbxlx-to-rojo' tool to convert a saved .rbxlx file into a Rojo project, or utilize a script sync plugin to sync changes from Studio back to the disk.	t	intermediate	{Rojo,ServerScriptService,ReplicatedStorage,rbxlx}	{}	t	An automated agent could parse the XML of an .rbxlx file to generate a corresponding folder tree and a 'default.project.json' configuration file automatically.	296	13	13	2025-12-29 06:19:15.492	2026-01-08 17:19:43.038773	{"views": 296, "content": " Hello everyone! \\n I have been developing a game for several months entirely inside Roblox Studio. It has a significant amount of code. \\n I recently decided to switch to an external IDE (like VS Code, Cursor, or Google Antigravity) using  Rojo . However, I don’t want to manually copy and paste every single script into files on my computer. \\n  My Question:  \\nIs there a plugin, tool, or script known in 2025 that can “dump” or export my current Roblox game structure (ServerScriptService, ReplicatedStorage, etc.) into a ready-to-use Rojo file structure ( .lua  files and folders) on my PC? \\n Basically, I want to reverse the process: turn my existing game instance into a Rojo project folder so I can start working externally immediately without losing my hierarchy. \\n Thanks in advance for the help! ", "upvotes": 13, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 13, "created_at": "2025-12-29T06:19:15.492Z"}
