787	devforum	4203225	Struggling to efficiently move 1000 assemblies	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4203225	Scripting	High CPU frame time (latency) in BulkMoveTo and notifyVisuallyMovingPrimitives when updating the CFrames of 1,000 multi-part assemblies simultaneously.	Replacing multi-part R6 assemblies (consisting of 18 instances each) with a single-part skinned mesh (S1) rig. This reduced BulkMoveTo time from 6ms to 2.5ms by decreasing the number of primitives the engine has to process per move.	t	advanced	{BulkMoveTo,Enum.BulkMoveMode.FireCFrameChanged,CFrame,AnimationController,Animator,Motor6D,WeldConstraint}	{}	t	A script could be used to automate the distance-based and visibility-based throttling (LOD system) for BulkMoveTo, or to batch CFrame calculations into a single array to minimize table allocations per frame.	159	8	6	2025-12-31 23:14:18.126	2026-01-08 17:19:52.51597	{"views": 159, "content": " I am currently working on a zombie system with goal of achieving 1000 zombies at 144+ FPS. I have optimized their behavior, and replication, but got stuck with movement as I am sitting at 45 FPS. \\n I use   BulkMoveTo   for movement, it takes ~6 ms a frame, which is excessive, but the engine also has  notifyVisuallyMovingPrimitives  taking up ~3 ms of additional frame time. Rendering itself takes ~6 ms. To reach 144 FPS, I got ~7 ms to finish a single frame, I am currently way above that. \\n          a  1277×149 94.8 KB         \\n         a - highlighted  1277×149 72.6 KB         \\n          b  478×167 37.9 KB                  c  341×243 35.9 KB         \\n         d  319×107 13.5 KB         \\n Movement code boils down to this snippet: \\n  local parts: {BasePart} = {}\\nlocal cframes: {CFrame} = {}\\n\\nlocal function onUpdate()\\n\\ttable.clear(parts)\\n\\ttable.clear(cframes)\\n\\n\\tlocal index = 0\\n\\tfor _, zombie in zombies do\\n\\t\\tif shouldUpdate(zombie) then\\n\\t\\t\\tindex += 1\\n\\t\\t\\tparts[index], cframes[index] = zombie.Root, zombie.CFrame\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tworkspace:BulkMoveTo(parts, cframes, Enum.BulkMoveMode.FireCFrameChanged)\\nend\\n  \\n The  shouldUpdate  function is used to throttle updates to reduce the number of zombies that are updated per frame, it takes distance and visibility into account. \\n   Before you reply: \\n \\n I use custom R6 rig that looks and functions like one, but it is optimized and designed to work without   Humanoid  . \\n         e  194×183 3.06 KB         \\n I do NOT use  Humanoid  instance. \\n All parts have their   CanCollide  ,   CanQuery  ,   CanTouch  , and   AudioCanCollide   set to  false . \\n All parts are set to be   Massless   and have their   CollisionFidelity   set to   Box  . \\n The   PrimaryPart   is set to the root part, which is   Anchored   and has   RootPriority   of  1 . \\n Assemblies are created by the client, fully client-sided. \\n Each assembly is made up of 18 instances, specifically:\\n \\n   MeshPart   (10x) \\n   Motor6D   (6x) \\n   WeldConstraint   (3x) \\n   SurfaceAppea", "upvotes": 8, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-12-31T23:14:18.126Z"}
791	devforum	4200243	Splits in Parts creating unintended Physics Behavior	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4200243	Physics	Inconsistent or unintended physics bouncing when a sphere part (Enum.PartType.Ball) rolls or bounces over the seam where two adjacent parts meet, despite the surfaces being flush.	\N	f	advanced	{Enum.PartType.Ball,RunService.Heartbeat}	{}	f	While the engine behavior itself cannot be automated away, a coding agent could assist in writing a custom Raycast or Spherecast-based physics controller to replace the default Roblox physics for the ball, which would avoid collision artifacts at part seams.	93	0	4	2025-12-31 01:05:45.37	2026-01-08 17:19:56.015393	{"views": 93, "content": " [This is marked under “Scripting Support” due to it involving Heartbeat Updates and not Map Design] \\n I’ve been working on a re-write for my golfing game, Let’s Go Golfing! and I’ve been struggling to find a solution to the largest issue that has been causing problems for the longest time, I nicknamed it a “Part Split” where the seem of two parts meet causing weird bounces, even though the ball should bounce off like they’re a single part. \\n Here’s a screenshot example I made in a testing environment: \\n         image  488×439 53.6 KB         \\n Let me be clear: The maps themselves cannot be changed to fix this, as the engine uses differing parts to determine game interactions (such as the green, sand, water, etc), so splits in parts are inevitable. \\n I’ve tried wrangling the physics engine before but it only caused even more problems, such as stuttering collisions, freezing, and many others. \\nI’ve also looked into a predictive physics model but I’ve never managed to make anything accurate, even when only trying to predict a single frame in the future. Even gone as far as looking into making a custom physics engine, but quickly backed off that idea because I want to avoid making drastic changes in physics, as doing so will force a full data wipe to a game that’s already established. \\n But as for right now, I’ve run out of ideas, so I’m looking for some help. \\nI know this is a lot to ask for so if no solution is found then it’ll have to stay for now. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-31T01:05:45.370Z"}
792	devforum	4195857	Help getting a table of player's badges	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4195857	Networking	Retrieving a comprehensive list of all badges a player has ever earned across the Roblox platform from within a game script.	BadgeService does not provide a method to list all badges for a user. Instead, developers must use HttpService to request data from the Roblox Web API (https://badges.roblox.com/v1/users/{userId}/badges) through a proxy server, as Roblox game servers cannot make direct requests to Roblox domains.	t	advanced	{BadgeService,HttpService}	{}	t	Create a script using HttpService to perform a GET request to a proxy service (like RoProxy) targeting the Roblox Badges Web API endpoint.	88	0	4	2025-12-29 17:08:09.582	2026-01-08 17:19:56.332151	{"views": 88, "content": " Hey! Sorry if this is the wrong category to post this in. But I wanted to know if it’s possible to get a table of all the badges a player has ever received, if so any help would be appreciated! ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-29T17:08:09.582Z"}
