796	devforum	2863730	How do I scale a model on one axis?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/2863730	Scripting	Programmatically scaling a Model object along a single axis while maintaining the relative structure of its components.	Iterate through the model's descendants, identify BaseParts, and multiply their Size property by a Vector3 representing the scale factor for the desired axis. Note: This specific reply solution does not account for repositioning parts to maintain spatial integrity.	t	intermediate	{GetDescendants,IsA,BasePart,Vector3,Size}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a robust function that not only scales the individual Part sizes but also scales the relative CFrame offsets of each part from the Model's PrimaryPart or Pivot to prevent the model from breaking apart.	526	4	7	2024-03-03 13:07:45.56	2026-01-08 17:20:01.422343	{"views": 526, "content": " You can write your topic however you want, but you need to answer these questions: \\n \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  Keep it simple and clear! \\nI want to scale a model on one axis using a script \\n \\n \\n  What is the issue?  Include screenshots / videos if possible! \\nI haven’t been able to find any ways of doing this \\n \\n \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Did you look for solutions on the Developer Hub? \\nI’ve looked through the devforum, but I seem to be the only one trying to do this specific thing lol \\n \\n ", "upvotes": 4, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2024-03-03T13:07:45.560Z"}
797	devforum	4203019	How to handle Scripts with Children (Hierarchy) on local file system?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4203019	Scripting	Maintaining script-to-script parent-child hierarchy when syncing Roblox Studio scripts to a local file system where files cannot contain other files.	Use the 'init' pattern: create a folder named after the parent script and place the script's content in a file named 'init.luau' (or 'init.server.luau'/'init.client.luau') inside that folder, alongside its children scripts.	t	intermediate	{"Script Sync"}	{}	t	Create a script or CLI tool to automatically refactor single .luau files into the folder/init.luau structure whenever a child object is added to a script in the hierarchy.	109	0	2	2025-12-31 21:53:39.99	2026-01-08 17:20:02.242544	{"views": 109, "content": " I am currently migrating my game to an external IDE using the  Script Sync  feature. I’ve run into a file system compatibility question regarding script hierarchy \\n In Roblox Studio, a Script can be a parent of other Scripts (e.g., a  Library  ModuleScript containing a  Services  ModuleScript inside it). However, on Window, a file cannot have children, only folders can \\n To maintain this hierarchy locally, I am planning to use the “Init Script” pattern (similar to Rojo). Could you confirm if this is the correct naming convention for the native Script Sync to recognize them as a single script with children? \\n My proposed structure: \\n \\n Instead of a file named  Library.luau , I create a Folder named  Library . \\n Inside that folder, I create the main script as  init.luau . \\n I place the child scripts inside that same folder. \\n \\n For example  Library.luau  →  Libarary.init.luau ,   GUIs.client.luau  →  .GUIsinit.client.luau ,  Framework.server.luau  →  Framework.init.server.luau  \\n Is this the correct workflow for the new Sync feature to reconstruct the hierarchy properly back in Studio? ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-31T21:53:39.990Z"}
800	devforum	4184358	Tile info doesnt save to a table	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4184358	Scripting	Table data inserted into a ModuleScript on the client does not persist or replicate across the client-server boundary, leading to empty tables when accessed from different environments.	\N	f	beginner	{table.insert,require,Instance.new,Color3.fromRGB,UDim2.new}	{}	t	A coding assistant could identify that the user is modifying a ModuleScript in ReplicatedStorage from a LocalScript and explain that these changes do not replicate to the Server. It would recommend using RemoteEvents to transmit the tile data to the server for global storage.	230	6	26	2025-12-26 01:20:18.824	2026-01-08 17:20:06.381427	{"views": 230, "content": " \\n \\n   What do you want to achieve?   \\nA NES tile system like, well the NES. \\n \\n \\n   What is the issue?   \\nMy issue is that the tiles are not being added to the tile ROM even thou I call  table.insert()  on the tile table (on a module script) it isn’t adding anything \\n \\n \\n   What solutions have you tried so far?   Did you look for solutions on the Creator Hub? \\nI tried changing values, printing for debbuging and  other things like that, \\nAfter that, you should include more details if you have any. Try to make your topic as descriptive as possible, so that it’s easier for people to help you! \\n \\n \\n The server loads tiles into the players POV by passing it through replicated storage, this works, the tile data is on a module script inside Replicated storage too, only accesed by client, coloring of tiles work, but the tile’s data isnt added to the tile data table (or what seems like it) \\n  EXAMPLE OF WHAT A TILE SHOULD LOOK LIKE!  \\n0: the darkest color in the pallet \\n1: middle color on the pallet \\n2: lightest color on the pallet \\n3: background color (one color only) \\n pallets work fine! Just rendering the tiles is wrong (the colors load just the black and white \\n  [1] = {\\n\\t2,1,0,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t3,3,3,3,3,0,3,3,\\n\\t3,3,1,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t3,3,2,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t3,0,3,3,3,3,3,0,\\n\\t3,3,3,3,0,3,3,3,\\n}\\n  \\n   HERES WHAT MODULE CONTAINING THE TILE DATA LOOKS LIKE   \\n  local charRom = {}\\nlocal bgTileTable = {\\n\\t--[[\\n\\t[999] = { -- blank tile\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t\\t3,3,3,3,3,3,3,3,\\n\\t},\\n\\t]]\\n}\\nlocal spriteTable = {\\n\\t\\n}\\nfunction charRom.addTileData(info) -- what i dont understand, because its printing but nothing gets added?\\n\\tprint(info)\\n\\ttable.insert(bgTileTable,info)\\n\\t\\nend\\nfunction charRom.getSpecificBgTileByIndx(indx)\\n\\treturn bgTileTable[indx]\\nend\\nfunction charRom.getBgRomData()\\n\\treturn bgTileTable\\nend\\nfunction charRom.getSpecificSpriteData()\\n\\t-- to be w", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 26, "created_at": "2025-12-26T01:20:18.824Z"}
