804	devforum	4200130	Looking to figure out a way to swap control & camera focus between two rigs without respawning or cloning either of them?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4200130	Scripting	Swapping player control and camera focus between two rigs without the Player.Character property logic deleting or respawning the original model.	Change the Workspace.CurrentCamera.CameraSubject to the target rig's Humanoid and use ContextActionService or UserInputService to map keyboard inputs to the target rig's movement, or manually re-parent the original character back to Workspace immediately after reassigning Player.Character.	t	intermediate	{Player.Character,CameraSubject,UserInputService,ContextActionService,PlatformStanding,Humanoid}	{}	t	Create a module that captures input via ContextActionService and pipes MoveDirection or position updates to a target rig while toggling the CameraSubject and disabling the default character's control script.	130	5	6	2025-12-31 00:20:32.218	2026-01-08 17:20:10.463923	{"views": 130, "content": " I’m trying to have it so that when I click the SWAP button, keyboard control switches over to the big guy in the back. The methods I have found end up deleting the original player model if I switch the Player.Character property and respawning me, and I can’t do that because this is for my character in a roleplay game and respawns will mess up the character customization stuff. \\n I also plan to have an animation play where the original player character climbs up onto the back of the big guy and accesses a completely different button set so generally it’s just important the two models do not get cloned or deleted. \\n I was thinking a potential solution would be to just set the player’s PlatformStanding to true, bind WASD, Shift and Spacebar to different movement things in a LocalScript and have that move the big guy around, but I’m not sure where to find documentation or tutorials on how to do that. If someone has the method or knows where to lea