805	devforum	4192747	Optimizing Chunk Replication	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4192747	Networking	High bandwidth consumption and inefficient data serialization when replicating large voxel chunk data (16x255x16) from server to client.	Implement custom binary serialization using the 'buffer' API instead of JSON. This includes mapping block names to numeric IDs, encoding orientation as small integers, packing colors into 24/32-bit integers, and using 1D sparse arrays to represent block positions.	t	advanced	{buffer,HttpService}	{}	t	A coding agent can generate Luau functions to serialize and deserialize custom data structures using the 'buffer' library's write/read methods (e.g., buffer.writeu8, buffer.writeu32) to replace heavy JSON strings.	128	5	5	2025-12-28 17:33:43.314	2026-01-08 17:20:12.239243	{"views": 128, "content": " Im working on a voxel engine that uses chunks, pretty much just minecraft. I store all the chunk data on the server and i replicate that data to the client. The issue is that the chunk data is really big, the chunk size is  16, 255, 16  with each block in the chunk having a  {}  attached to it for block data. \\n What the chunk data looks like: \\n  local chunks = {\\n\\t[Chunk_Position] = { --&gt; this is what im sending\\n\\t\\t[Block Position] = {\\n\\t\\t\\tName = \\"BlockName\\",\\n\\t\\t\\tOrientation = BlockOrientation,\\n\\t\\t\\tTint = TintColor\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n}\\n  \\n Currently im converting the chunk data into a json and converting the json into a buffer and then compressing that buffer, but its still allot of data being sent. ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-28T17:33:43.314Z"}
