810	devforum	4200503	[FUSION] How do I animate hotbar icons?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4200503	UI	Difficulty animating or tweening UI elements inside a Fusion ForValues loop because elements are destroyed and recreated when the state updates, losing internal animation state.	\N	f	intermediate	{Fusion,ForValues,TweenService}	{}	t	An AI could suggest a pattern using a custom component class or a 'Computed' state for each item that maintains a stable reference, or suggest using 'ForKeys' with unique IDs to prevent reconciliation from recreating the instances.	174	15	12	2025-12-31 02:54:57.554	2026-01-08 17:20:16.622744	{"views": 174, "content": "  type item = {\\n    model: Instance,\\n    isEquipped: boolean\\n}\\n\\nscope:ForValues(itemsInInventory, function(use, scope, info: item)\\n  local index = table.find(use(itemsInInventory),info)\\n\\n  return m_item.New(scope, info.model.Name, index)\\nend),\\n\\nm_networker:BindEvent(\\"UpdateBackpackUI\\", function(items: {item})\\n  itemsInInventory:set(items)\\nend)\\n  \\n I want to tween my item icons but I dont know a way of doing so. Because im using ForValues, i can’t really use any fusion values per icon to tween because the icons just get deleted when i update the inventory. ", "upvotes": 15, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 12, "created_at": "2025-12-31T02:54:57.554Z"}
