916	devforum	4166949	Experience ban does not sync with ban manager and experience	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4166949	Networking	Desynchronization between Experience-level and Universe-level bans where a ban remains active but is not visible in the Ban Manager, causing persistent Error 600.	The ban was specific to the Experience rather than the Universe. Running an unban script with 'ApplyToUniverse = false' successfully cleared the orphaned ban.	t	intermediate	{"Open Cloud API","Ban Manager",Players:UnbanAsync}	{"Error 600"}	t	A script or tool could be created to check and clear bans at both the Universe and Place levels simultaneously to prevent orphaned ban states.	75	0	2	2025-12-20 16:20:44.707	2026-01-08 17:23:55.12423	{"views": 75, "content": "  Summary:  \\nI was testing the new Roblox ban feature using the Open Cloud API while building a Discord bot for our moderators. To verify everything worked, I repeatedly banned and unbanned my own account. At some point, either due to sending too many requests too quickly or a brief Roblox server disruption, the ban state stopped syncing. Since then, I’ve been stuck as banned, even though the ban manager, API, etc., reports that I’m unbanned. \\n  Full Explanation  \\nI created and tested the ban and unban commands of a Discord bot I developed by banning and unbanning myself several times. After confirming that permanent bans worked correctly, I tested the time ban command as well. I entered a value slightly over 1,000 days, which the bot correctly converted into seconds for the API. I verified the ban by attempting to join the game, checked the ban list command (which also worked), and then unbanned myself. The bot reported the unban as successful. After that, I went to sleep and didn’t join the game for about two months, since development had already shifted to a new project and I was only working on moderation commands on the side. A few weeks ago, I noticed that I was still banned. \\n ● The first thing I tried was the Roblox Game Ban Manager, but I didn’t appear on the banned list at all. So I manually added a new ban and then unbanned myself again, hoping it would force a sync. This didn’t work. \\n ● I then tried unbanning myself through the Discord bot again, which also failed. \\n ● Another developer ran an unban script from the in game console (since Studio does not allow ban or unban requests), but that didn’t work either. \\n ● I also confirmed that there were no alternative accounts or other bans affecting the experience, there is literally no one on the ban list. \\n I waited a bit, nothing changed. \\nI switched devices, same issue. \\nI checked every place inside the same universe and even all other experiences under the same group, nothing that might cause this issue", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-20T16:20:44.707Z"}
