823	devforum	4201474	What does the error "Internal error: Lambda has non-function type blocked-156306" mean?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4201474	Scripting	Luau internal error 'Lambda has non-function type blocked' occurring in the new type solver when using the Type Function API with recursive structures.	The issue is a confirmed bug in the Luau engine's new solver. A temporary workaround is to cast the return type to 'any', though the official fix requires an engine update from the Luau development team.	t	advanced	{"Type Function API",types.singleton,types.newtable,types.readproperty,types.setproperty}	{"Internal error: Lambda has non-function type blocked-156306","TypeError: Type inference failed to complete, you may see some confusing types and type errors."}	t	An automated agent can identify this as an upstream compiler bug. It can suggest applying a temporary 'any' cast to affected type functions or switching to the old Luau solver if possible until the GitHub issue is resolved.	78	2	3	2025-12-31 10:53:48.809	2026-01-08 17:20:33.962466	{"views": 78, "content": "          image  487×116 5.41 KB         \\nWhile I have tried to ensure the logic within the  discover()  function is sound, I am concerned that I might be missing a fundamental constraint of the Type Function API that triggers this  *blocked*  state. \\n Could someone please review the recursive structure below and explain what this internal error indicates? \\n Heres the full code for reference: \\n  --!strict\\n\\ntype IndexAndValue = {Index:any,Value:any}\\n\\nexport type FlattedTable = {\\n\\tTables:{\\n\\t\\t[string]:{[string]:IndexAndValue}\\n\\t},\\n\\tId:string\\n}\\n\\ntype function GetFlattedTableType(unflattedTable:type)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal s = types.singleton\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal tables = types.newtable()\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal id = tostring(unflattedTable)\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal function discover(t:type):type?\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif not t:is(\\"table\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\treturn nil\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal tableId = tostring(t)\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal infoTableAlreadyExists = tables:readproperty(s(tableId))\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif infoTableAlreadyExists then\\n\\t\\t\\treturn infoTableAlreadyExists\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal infoTable = types.newtable()\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal infoTable_LEN = 0\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\ttables:setproperty(s(tableId),infoTable)\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tfor index, readAndWrite in t:properties() do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal value = t:readproperty(index)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t-- type checker do not understand it btw (fix it roblox!!!!)\\n\\t\\t\\tif value == nil then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tif index:is(\\"table\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal convertedIndex = discover(index)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif convertedIndex then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tindex = convertedIndex\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend \\n\\n\\t\\t\\tif value:is(\\"table\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlocal convertedValue = discover(value)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif convertedValue then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvalue = convertedValue\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal indexAndValue = types.newtable{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t[s(\\"Index\\")] = index,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t[s(\\"Value\\")] = value\\n\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tinfoTable:setproperty(s(tostring(infoTable_LEN + 1)),indexAndValue)\\n\\t\\t\\tinfoTable_LEN += 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\treturn types.newtable{ [s(\\"Id\\")] = s(tableId) }\\n\\t\\t\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\tdiscover(unflattedTable)\\n\\t\\n\\treturn types.newtable{\\n\\t\\t[s(\\"Tables\\")] = tables,\\n\\t\\t[s(\\"Id\\")] = s(id),\\n\\t}\\n\\t\\nend\\n\\n--type function GetUnflatte", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-31T10:53:48.809Z"}
917	devforum	4174636	How to filter randomly generated text	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4174636	Scripting	Filtering procedurally generated text for NPC names through TextService when there is no originating sender's UserID to pass into FilterStringAsync.	\N	f	intermediate	{TextService:FilterStringAsync,GetNonChatStringForUserAsync,GetNonChatStringForBroadcastAsync}	{}	t	Create a standardized wrapper for TextService that handles system-generated strings by using a fallback UserID (such as the Game Owner's ID or the target Player's ID) to fulfill the API requirement.	110	2	7	2025-12-22 21:55:20.224	2026-01-08 17:23:58.950437	{"views": 110, "content": " To start off im not  entirely sure  just what category this would go into, so if this would make sense some where else please let me know. \\n I have been working on a game that procedurally generates the map, and i added in a system that generates NPC’s to go along with it: \\n  local preExistingNames = {}\\n\\nfunction genName(char)\\n\\tprint(char)\\n\\tlocal alphabet = {\\"a\\", \\"b\\", \\"c\\", \\"d\\", \\"e\\", \\"f\\", \\"g\\", \\"h\\", \\"i\\", \\"j\\", \\"k\\", \\"l\\", \\"m\\", \\"n\\", \\"o\\", \\"p\\", \\"q\\", \\"r\\", \\"s\\", \\"t\\", \\"u\\", \\"v\\", \\"w\\", \\"x\\", \\"y\\", \\"z\\"}\\n\\tlocal length = math.random(3,20)\\n\\tlocal name = \\"\\"\\n\\trepeat\\n\\t\\tlocal letter = alphabet[math.random(1,#alphabet)]\\n\\t\\tif math.random(1,2) == 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\tletter = string.upper(letter)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tname = name..letter\\n\\t\\tlength -= 1\\n\\tuntil length &lt;= 0\\n\\tif table.find(preExistingNames,name) then\\n\\t\\tlocal numOfName = 0\\n\\t\\tfor i,v in preExistingNames do\\n\\t\\t\\tif v == name then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tnumOfName += 1\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\ttable.insert(preExistingNames,name)\\n\\t\\tname = name..\\"_\\"..tostring(numOfName)\\n\\tend\\n\\tchar.Name = name\\n\\tchar.Humanoid.DisplayName = name\\nend\\n  \\n Its not much of a “ system ” though as its just randomly picking letters and then randomly deciding whether or not to capitalise them, the problem is since its random it could generate something inappropriate, and roblox’s built in textfiltering service requires a userID as to moderate the text:  TextService:FilterStringAsync(text, fromUserId) . \\n Im not really sure what to do about this as giving NPCs random names was a big part of this and im not just going to write a really long table with random letters. \\n The thing is roblox even mentions this exact issue on their  page about text filtering  yet give no answer on that (understandably as its not exactly normal) \\n         image  956×378 37.2 KB         \\ni honestly don’t know what to do and any help would be appreciated ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2025-12-22T21:55:20.224Z"}
