826	devforum	4202104	Jittery movement when updating cframe	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4202104	Scripting	Visual jitter or stuttering when updating an anchored part's CFrame using RunService loops (BindToRenderStep, Heartbeat, or Stepped).	\N	f	intermediate	{RunService,BindToRenderStep,RenderStepped,Heartbeat,Stepped,CFrame,Vector3,Enum.RenderPriority}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest replacing manual CFrame updates with TweenService for built-in interpolation or advise on syncing movement with the camera's RenderPriority to eliminate visual lag.	64	0	1	2025-12-31 16:08:34.895	2026-01-08 17:20:40.213427	{"views": 64, "content": " Hi, I’m trying to move a part smoothly using  RunService:BindToRenderStep , but the movement appears jittery no matter what I do. \\n Here’s the script I’m using: \\n  local RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\n\\nlocal part= workspace:WaitForChild(\\"Part\\")\\nlocal velocity = Vector3.new(15,0,0) \\n\\nRunService:BindToRenderStep(\\"UpdatePos\\", Enum.RenderPriority.Character.Value,function(dt)\\n\\tpart.CFrame = part.CFrame + velocity * dt\\nend)\\n  \\n Things I’ve already tried: \\n \\n Changing the render priority (Camera, Character, Input, etc.) \\n Using other update loops ( RenderStepped ,  Heartbeat ,  Stepped ) \\n Making sure the part is anchored \\n Testing both in Studio and in Play mode \\n \\n No matter what I try, the movement still looks jittery. \\n Is this caused by how CFrame updates work, floating-point precision, or something related to how Roblox renders/interpolates parts? Is there a recommended way to achieve smooth constant movement like this? \\n Any help or explanation would be appreciated. Thanks! \\nhere is a video: \\n  \\n    \\nnote: in studio it is even more jittery but on video its less jittery because of the recording  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-12-31T16:08:34.895Z"}
