846	devforum	4199275	How can I create a working raft in Studio?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4199275	Physics	Implementing a driveable raft using physics constraints that reacts to VehicleSeat input without causing physics instability or unintended floating.	Use AlignPosition and AlignOrientation constraints. Set the Y-level of the AlignPosition to the water's surface height (manually or via raycasting) and update the position/orientation based on the raft's LookVector multiplied by speed and the VehicleSeat's Throttle/Steer values.	t	intermediate	{VehicleSeat,qPerfectionWeld,Motor6D,BodyVelocity,LinearVelocity,AlignPosition,AlignOrientation}	{}	t	An AI agent could generate a boilerplate script that listens for property changes on a VehicleSeat and applies the corresponding vector mathematics to AlignPosition and AlignOrientation instances.	64	0	2	2025-12-30 18:43:07.153	2026-01-08 17:21:23.725776	{"views": 64, "content": " Hello, hello! I’ve been trying to implement a driveable raft in my game for the past couple hours, but can’t figure out how it works. So far, I’ve tried inserting a VehicleSeat with qPerfectionWeld to weld it together, which looks good. Then, the VehicleSeat didn’t do anything. \\n I tried searching for what to add (like motor6d) and couldn’t figure that out. \\n Then, I manually welded everything and tried the same, and it also didn’t work. \\n I’ve tried BodyVelocity and LinearVelocity and controlling them using a script that reads when the VehicleSeat has changes in Steer or Throttle (from  this  post), but they make it float. \\n Any ideas on how to implement this? I know it’s a bit strange, but I want the raft to look like it’s moving on its own (i.e. no rotating “mill” things). \\n Thanks for reading this far, and I’d appreciate any input. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-30T18:43:07.153Z"}
847	devforum	4197324	Deforming mesh water around the hull of a ship, how possible is this?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4197324	Scripting	Preventing mesh-based water from clipping inside a ship's hull in real-time while the ship is moving, specifically without using the 'glass' transparency rendering trick.	\N	f	advanced	{SmartBones,Bones}	{}	t	A coding agent could implement a script to dynamically reposition bones in a Water Mesh based on the ship's CFrame and bounding box, or utilize the EditableMesh API to displace vertices below the hull's height map.	122	3	6	2025-12-30 02:28:03.549	2026-01-08 17:21:26.273351	{"views": 122, "content": " I was tasked with modelling a ship for a game my friend is developing, and part of the ship’s model will be below the water line. What options do we have for making water not appear below decks? \\nWe obviously cannot use terrain water for this, and planned on making custom water anyways. \\n This boat is a vehicle, and it will move and is drivable by players, so this deformation has to be done live \\n          image  1296×744 34.4 KB         \\n          Screenshot 2025-12-29 191304  1048×424 37.8 KB         \\n I suggested using bones to deform water around the hull of the ship, but the scripter says this will create too much lag, but we haven’t tried it yet because they are unwilling to do it because they believe it will just cause lag. Does anyone have experience with this? Would it actually cause this much lag? \\n Another idea I had is making a custom water part that is pre-deformed in blender around the hull of the ship, it would still be animated like regular water, and the actual ocean water mesh would only deform in a large rectangle around the ship, but the custom ship water mesh would create a seamless blend between the two, covering the hole. Would it cause less lag by only making the water deform in a basic rectangle like this? \\n We could also only make these calculations happen for players below deck, and only for people who are close enough to actually see it. For example, if you are on ship A and see ship B in the distance, players on ship A do not need to have ship B’s water deformation calculated. They can’t even see it, so what’s the point? \\n Someone suggested we use terrain deformation and just make water deform or replace into air inside the hitbox of the ship’s hull which could work but it might also cause a significant amount of lag, according to the scripter \\n We also cannot use the glass method to make water not render below decks, it would interfere with particle effects. \\n Perhaps there is a method to use a mesh without deforming at all, and just m", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2025-12-30T02:28:03.549Z"}
848	devforum	4199485	Vehicle Weapon Controls Help	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4199485	Scripting	How to handle user input for vehicle-mounted weapons while a player is sitting in a VehicleSeat, including the proper location for the client-side script.	Use ContextActionService to bind inputs specifically when the player is in the vehicle, or UserInputService with checks for the player's seat status. The script can be placed in StarterPlayerScripts or StarterCharacterScripts.	t	intermediate	{ContextActionService,UserInputService,VehicleSeat}	{}	t	An agent could generate a template LocalScript that listens for the Humanoid.Seated event, checks if the seat is a vehicle, and then uses ContextActionService to bind 'Fire' and 'Aim' actions to RemoteEvents.	77	4	8	2025-12-30 20:04:10.752	2026-01-08 17:21:27.924879	{"views": 77, "content": " Hello developers, \\n I am trying to create a vehicle system where players are able to drive vehicles around text that have weapons built in. \\n I wanted the weapons to function similar to how the game “Armored Patrol” does it.  \\n   \\n       \\n\\n       Roblox \\n   \\n\\n   \\n       \\n\\n  ARMORED PATROL  \\n\\n   Tank &amp; helicopter war game made by Wingman8\\n\\nAlmost everything is fully destructible \\n\\n\\n   \\n\\n   \\n    \\n    \\n   \\n\\n    \\n \\n\\n The user is able to both drive the vehicle as well as control a variety of weapons depending on what’s available on the vehicle. I noticed while playing that the player uses a tool in their backpack to control the vehicle. I’m not sure if this is necessary to achieve the same affect the game has. \\n I already have a system for driving vehicles I am just unsure on how to take input from the player that is inside a vehicle seat in order to control a weapon attached to the vehicle. \\n I have not really tried anything yet related to this as I’m not really sure what direction to go in as I haven’t seen much information on a topic like this. If anybody could provide any 