859	devforum	4196141	Animated textures not in sync	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196141	Scripting	Animated textures using a shared frame counter and time accumulator within a loop result in out-of-sync animations and inconsistent speeds across multiple instances.	Refactor the logic to avoid shared global variables inside the update loop. Each texture should either have its own state or, preferably, derive its current frame from a global time-based calculation (like os.clock()) to ensure perfect synchronization.	t	intermediate	{RunService.Heartbeat,CollectionService:GetTagged,CollectionService:GetInstanceAddedSignal,CollectionService:GetInstanceRemovedSignal,Texture.OffsetStudsU,Texture.OffsetStudsV}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the animation logic to use a deterministic mathematical formula (e.g., frame = math.floor(os.clock() * fps) % totalFrames) which eliminates the need for individual state tracking and ensures all textures are synced globally.	238	25	70	2025-12-29 18:51:41.486	2026-01-08 17:21:49.015444	{"views": 238, "content": " Hey guys, today I was working on a script for animated textures in my game, but have ran into an issue. My current problem is that duplicates of the same texture (in this case water) play their animations at varying speeds instead of playing at the same time. I have little idea why this behavior is occurring, as I’d assume the script should be firing off for every tagged part at the same time. I really want to fix this, since its obviously visually distracting. Below will be the current module script which is required by a server script, for additional some context. Any and all help will be greatly appreciated &lt;3 \\n   \\n     \\n  local animatedTexturesModule = {}\\n\\n--Services\\nlocal RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\nlocal CollectionService = game:GetService(\\"CollectionService\\")\\n\\n--Variables\\nlocal animatedTextures = CollectionService:GetTagged(\\"AnimatedTexture\\")\\n\\nlocal frames = 1 --Number of frames in a spritesheet\\nlocal currentFrame = 1\\n\\nlocal rows = 1 --Number of rows in a spritesheet\\nlocal columns = 1 --Number of columns in a spritesheet\\n\\nlocal currentRow = 0\\nlocal currentColumn = 0\\n\\nlocal fps = 30\\n\\nlocal targetRate = 0.15 --The lower this number, the faster the animation will play\\nlocal accumulatedTime = 0\\n\\n--RunService connection\\nlocal animatedTexturesRunService = RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function(deltaTime)\\n\\tfor _, texture in ipairs(animatedTextures) do\\n\\t\\tif texture:IsA(\\"Texture\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal size = texture.Parent.Size --The spritesheet should be on the FRONT of the part\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\taccumulatedTime = accumulatedTime + deltaTime\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t\\tif accumulatedTime &gt;= targetRate then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif texture:HasTag(\\"Water\\") then --Water\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tframes = 32\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\trows = 6\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcolumns = 6\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttexture.StudsPerTileU = columns * size.X\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttexture.StudsPerTileV = rows * size.Y\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcurrentColumn = currentColumn + 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif currentColumn &gt; columns then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcurrentColumn = 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcurrentRow = currentRow + 1\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif currentFrame &gt; frames then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tcurrentRow", "upvotes": 25, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 70, "created_at": "2025-12-29T18:51:41.486Z"}
860	devforum	4198321	Drag detector lags when getting far away	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4198321	Physics	DragDetector objects experience lag, slow movement, and collision failure (clipping) when moving away from the player or interacting with other physics objects like bowling pins, likely due to network ownership issues.	\N	f	intermediate	{DragDetector,CanCollide}	{}	t	Check if NetworkOwnership is assigned to the player interacting with the ball to ensure low-latency physics simulation.	39	1	1	2025-12-30 11:10:47.669	2026-01-08 17:21:51.114449	{"views": 39, "content": " Hi! I’m working on my bowling alley! Everything here is like it should except the ball: when the ball is with the pins, it goes extremely slow, and lags, and it wouldn’t even hit the pins properly, but just goes through like if CanCollide was off. But when I am in another bowling game with more lanes, it works like it should. In their alleys, they use the bowling balls as tool. But in my game, I’m using them with dragdetector. But this issue only happens to the following game: All others seems to work like expected. \\nConclusion: The bowling ball gets extremely slow and laggy when it approaches the pins. \\n \\n I have more problems before, but this is the worste one. \\n This is how I mean:  \\n(EB) \\n ", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-12-30T11:10:47.669Z"}
861	devforum	4197948	How to create a NPC which chases the player	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4197948	Scripting	NPC pathfinding lag where the character only walks to the player's previous position because the script waits for all waypoints to be completed before recalculating the path.	Continuously check the distance the player has moved (e.g., if distance moved > 0.5 studs) and recalculate the path immediately instead of waiting for the current waypoint loop to finish. Additionally, use direct MoveTo calls when the player is in line of sight to reduce computational overhead.	t	intermediate	{PathfindingService,Humanoid:MoveTo,MoveToFinished,PathfindingService:CreatePath,ComputeAsync,GetWaypoints}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor the waypoint loop into a state-based system or use a 'break' condition inside the loop that triggers when the distance between the NPC's target position and the player's current position exceeds a specific threshold.	139	4	5	2025-12-30 07:35:10.938	2026-01-08 17:21:51.548477	{"views": 139, "content": " Hello Everyone, \\n Recently I’ve been trying to create a Bear which chases the player once they get close enough. My only problem with this is shown in the video below, the bear pathfinds and then walks to the player’s old position if they move \\n  \\n     \\n Here’s my code for the bear, also it’s best that the bear pathfinds instead of just spamming  :MoveTo()  to the Player’s HumanoidRootPart \\n  local function move()\\n    --some variables\\n\\n\\t--// Calculate Path and Move towards Player\\n\\tlocal newPath = PathfindingService:CreatePath({\\n\\t\\tCosts = {\\n\\t\\t\\tWater = math.huge, -- Avoid Water\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t})\\n\\n\\tnewPath:ComputeAsync(mob_torso.Position, characterPosition)\\n\\tlocal waypoints = newPath:GetWaypoints()\\n\\n\\tif not waypoints then\\n\\t\\twarn(\\"Waypoints in mob is nil, Mob:\\", mob_model)\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\tlocal WalkAnimTrack = self.WalkTrack\\n\\t\\t\\n\\tWalkAnimTrack:Play()\\n\\tfor _, waypoint: PathWaypoint in waypoints do\\n\\t\\tmob_humanoid:MoveTo(waypoint.Position)\\n\\t\\tmob_humanoid.MoveToFinished:Wait()\\n\\tend\\n\\tWalkAnimTrack:Stop()\\nend\\n  \\n Help Would be greatly appreicated! ", "upvotes": 4, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-30T07:35:10.938Z"}
862	devforum	4192003	How to apply impulse on character?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4192003	Physics	Incorrect calculation of impulse for character models caused by summing AssemblyMass multiple times, resulting in an excessively high force applied to the assembly.	Use the AssemblyMass property of a single part within the character (such as the HumanoidRootPart) to calculate the impulse, as this property already represents the total mass of the entire welded assembly.	t	beginner	{ApplyImpulse,AssemblyMass,HumanoidRootPart,PrimaryPart,Workspace:FindPartOnRayWithIgnoreList}	{}	t	A static analysis tool or linter could detect when AssemblyMass is being summed within a loop over children of the same Model/Assembly and flag it as a logical error.	249	5	39	2025-12-28 12:09:59.673	2026-01-08 17:21:56.440423	{"views": 249, "content": " If we want to apply impulse to part we do this: \\n  local part = Instance.new(\\"Part\\")\\npart:ApplyImpulse(Vector3.new(50, 0, 0) * part.AssemblyMass)\\n  \\n And we expect that part will have deltaPosition of  Vector3.new(50, 0, 0)  after one second. \\n But when I try to do the same thing with character, meaning taking mass of the whole model and applying impulse to  HumanoidRootPart , I don’t have the same behaviour. Instead character goes much further away. \\n How do I get the standard behaviour? \\n Here is a project that you can use: \\n Press “F” to apply impulse to  Vector.new(50, 0, 0)  to  Character . \\n  forum.rbxl  (135.4 KB) ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 39, "created_at": "2025-12-28T12:09:59.673Z"}
868	devforum	4196289	How do I handle player speed?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196289	Networking	Balancing input responsiveness and server-side security when modifying player WalkSpeed for mechanics like sprinting and crouching.	Handle speed changes directly on the client to ensure instant feedback, while simultaneously sending state signals to the server. The server then validates these signals against the character's physical velocity and current game state to prevent speed hacking.	t	intermediate	{Humanoid,WalkSpeed}	{}	t	A coding agent can implement a boilerplate system featuring a client-side input controller for state management and a server-side validation script that calculates movement magnitude relative to expected speed limits.	99	2	4	2025-12-29 19:51:33.713	2026-01-08 17:22:08.040654	{"views": 99, "content": " I want to know how I should be handling player speed with crouching, sprinting, and anything that affects walk speed. If I let the server handle all the speed changes, crouching would feel delayed because I need to send a signal to request a speed change. But if I let the client handle all the speed changes, it would feel janky because every time I want to change the player’s speed on the server, I would need to send a signal to the client. I can’t split client and server handling because that would just create a tangled mess. ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-29T19:51:33.713Z"}
863	devforum	4198151	Reserve server should not be provided with reserved server access code	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4198151	Networking	Conflicting properties in TeleportOptions: attempting to set ShouldReserveServer to true while also manually providing a ReservedServerAccessCode.	Remove the ReservedServerAccessCode assignment when ShouldReserveServer is set to true, as the latter automatically generates a reserved server code.	t	beginner	{TeleportOptions,TeleportService,TeleportAsync,ReserveServerAsync,TeleportPartyAsync}	{}	t	A static analysis tool or linter could detect if both ShouldReserveServer and ReservedServerAccessCode are assigned to the same TeleportOptions object.	59	0	2	2025-12-30 09:38:42.092	2026-01-08 17:21:57.181289	{"views": 59, "content": " You can write your topic however you want, but you need to answer these questions: \\n \\n \\n I’m trying to make a system for teleporting to another game \\n \\n \\n every time I try to teleport to the game. I get the same error \\n  \\n \\n \\n i I didn’t find any forum posts with the same issue. and I tried using TeleportToPrivateServer() \\n \\n \\n here is my code \\n  local function timer()\\n\\tfor i=0,10 do\\n\\t\\tlocal tim = 10 - i\\n\\t\\tscript.Parent.BillboardGui.TextLabel.Text = 'teleport in...'..tim\\n\\t\\ttask.wait(1)\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\n\\n\\tlocal options = Instance.new('TeleportOptions')\\n\\n\\t\\n\\toptions.ShouldReserveServer = true\\n\\toptions.ReservedServerAccessCode = tp:ReserveServerAsync(82060784106986)\\n\\n\\tif #plrs == 1 then\\n\\t\\n\\t\\ttp:TeleportAsync(82060784106986,plrs,options)\\n\\t\\t\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\ttp:TeleportPartyAsync(82060784106986,plrs,options)\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\ttimer()\\n\\t\\n\\nend\\ntimer()\\n  ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-30T09:38:42.092Z"}
