869	devforum	4197296	MemoryStoreService and "Distributed Locking"	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4197296	DataStore	Implementing distributed locking or leader election to prevent multiple servers from redundantly regenerating global stock simultaneously using MemoryStoreService.	\N	f	intermediate	{MemoryStoreService,MemoryStoreHashMap,MessagingService,UpdateAsync,GetAsync,SubscribeAsync}	{}	t	Provide a boilerplate implementation of a mutex/lease system using a specific key in MemoryStoreService where the first server to successfully call UpdateAsync with a short TTL becomes the 'generator' for that period.	68	1	3	2025-12-30 02:15:22.5	2026-01-08 17:22:10.835681	{"views": 68, "content": " I am trying to create a global restocking system where every player is giving the same stock generated from RNG. To do this, I need to use memorystoreservice for cross-server communication. \\n The problem is, I am seriously worried about race conditions. Some told me that the UpdateAsyc function has a built in session locking feature but other resources (i.e. copilot  ) tell me it’s not enough. \\n I am very familiar with ProfileStore and how it offers this kind of functionality but I don’t know how to implement a system like that with servers and memorystore. I am also very confused at what TTL is supposed to be, is it for session locking? \\n This is my code. Should I just leave it as is? It would help if ya’ll could help me catch any mistakes as well. thank youuuu   \\n  local players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\nlocal repStore = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal memStore = game:GetService(\\"MemoryStoreService\\")\\nlocal msgServ = game:GetService(\\"MessagingService\\")\\nlocal sss = game:GetService(\\"ServerScriptService\\")\\n\\nlocal events = repStore.ServerToClient\\nlocal updateShopTimeEvent = events.UpdateYokaiShopTime\\nlocal updateShopStockEvent = events.UpdateYokaiShopStock\\n\\nlocal binds = sss.Binds\\nlocal paidRestockApprovedEvent = binds.PaidRe