871	devforum	4196979	Hitbox damage broken	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196979	Scripting	Cumulative damage increase per hit caused by redundant event connections to the Touched signal.	The developer likely has the Touched event connection nested inside a function or loop that runs multiple times, causing multiple listeners to fire on every touch. The solution is to move the connection outside the repeating block or use a debounce variable to prevent multiple executions.	t	beginner	{BasePart.Touched,BasePart.CanTouch,Humanoid.Health,Instance.new,Debris.AddItem,BodyVelocity,Humanoid.LoadAnimation}	{}	t	An automated linter or AI agent can detect if an event connection like ':Connect' is placed inside a loop or a frequently called function, which is a common pattern for event stacking bugs.	66	0	3	2025-12-29 23:53:52.914	2026-01-08 17:22:14.021618	{"views": 66, "content": " so im making a npc system where when the npc hits you it deals 15 damage then pauses for 2 seconds being unable to deal damage or move but for some reason the hitbox i made that stays on the npc the whole time i just turn the cantouch on and off keeps increasing its damage by 10 every hit and i didn’t add that, is there any reason why this would happen? ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-29T23:53:52.914Z"}
872	devforum	4190677	A better option than WaitForChild	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4190677	Scripting	Standard Instance:WaitForChild is inefficient for complex client-side loading because it lacks customizable polling intervals and can cause 'infinite yield' warnings or unnecessary delays due to fixed internal logic.	Creating a custom module (SAFEWAIT) that uses task.wait with user-defined polling intervals and timeouts to offer a more performant and granular alternative to the engine's default WaitForChild.	t	intermediate	{WaitForChild,FindFirstChild,task.wait}	{"Infinite yield possible"}	t	A coding agent could generate a custom 'WaitUntil' utility function that implements a while-loop using task.wait and FindFirstChild with configurable timeout and interval parameters.	472	31	33	2025-12-28 00:35:22.472	2026-01-08 17:22:16.155735	{"views": 472, "content": "  Hello everyone    , I hope you’re all doing well. This is my first post, so I’ll introduce myself briefly. I’ve been creating Roblox games for almost seven years now, and this past year I’ve been refining my skills in the internal workings of the game. Certainly, after mastering Lua programming, as the saying goes, once you understand a topic, you can then suggest things because you truly grasp it. \\n Anyway, I simply wanted to share a simple alternative for those looking for a solution to WaitForChild, a nightmare for many fellow scripters, I’m sorry, but it’s true. \\n I’ve been searching like crazy for an alternative to waitforchild, but I haven’t found a framework for these child settings, like waitforchild or findfirstchild. I’m referring to something more customizable and optimized. Below, I’ll list the main problems, especially with waitforchild. I might cover findfirstchild another day. \\n  Main problems with WaitForChild:  \\n-Well, I want to tell you that when I started using waitforchild—because we’ve all used it without question when we started programming, trusting in it—I ran into my first big problem. When I created my 10th game, studying and improving it with each game, I think that’s what we do. But here I saw an error I hadn’t seen before. I repeat, I was very new to it, but waitforchild is NOT RELIABLE, especially if you’re searching for something in the workspace from the client. I’m referring specifically to that issue, without forgetting client preloading. \\n It didn’t load an asset I had; it was an egg in the workspace, being searched for with waitforchild from the client… This is where the terror of every novice coder began. Sorry if I’m talking too much about such a simple solution, but it’s my first post. Thanks for your patience. Besides, I think we like reading these posts and seeing them as crazy adventures of each of the members of [the community/group]. Roblox developer, well, the terror began, it showed up in yellow saying it wasn’t loadin", "upvotes": 31, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 33, "created_at": "2025-12-28T00:35:22.472Z"}
873	devforum	4197082	Looking for any way to create a roguelike item upgrade system	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4197082	Scripting	Synchronizing player statistics (Base, Addition, Multipliers) between server and client when stored in a ModuleScript, as updates on one side do not reflect on the other.	\N	f	intermediate	{ModuleScript,GetChildren}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a boilerplate RemoteEvent-based replication system that synchronizes a central server-side stat table to individual clients whenever a 'Set', 'Pure', or 'Multiplier' value is modified.	56	0	1	2025-12-30 00:42:40.878	2026-01-08 17:22:17.245941	{"views": 56, "content": " I have spent  ages  trying to understand how I’m supposed to do this!? I clearly need some help to understand player handlers and don’t know what I’m doing. I’m trying to make the stats via module scripts, and handle all through updates to it, but it doesn’t update on both the client and server: the code is as such: \\n  local Stats = {\\n\\n\\t[\\"Pure\\"] = {\\n\\t\\t[\\"Health\\"] = 100\\n\\t},\\n\\n\\t[\\"Multiplier\\"] = {\\n\\t[\\"Health\\"] = 1\\n\\t}\\n\\t[\\"Set\\"] = {\\n\\t\\t[\\"Health\\"] = 100\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nlocal Stats2 = Stats\\n\\nlocal function updateStats(Stat)\\nif Stat then\\n\\t\\tif Stat.Name == \\"Set\\" and Stat:GetChildren() then\\n\\t\\t\\tfor I,Value in pairs(Stat:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\t\\tStats2[Stat.Name][Value.Name] = Value.Value \\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\telseif Stat.Name == \\"Pure\\" and Stat:GetChildren() then\\n\\t\\t\\tfor I,Value in pairs(Stat:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\t\\tStats2[Stat.Name][Value.Name] = Stats[Stat.Name][Value.Name] + Value.Value \\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\telseif Stat.Name == \\"Multiplier\\" and Stat:GetChildren() then\\n\\t\\t\\tfor I,Value in pairs(Stat:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\t\\tStats2[Stat.Name][Value.Name] = Stats[Stat.Name][Value.Name] + Value.Value \\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\nend\\n\\nfunction Stats2.Update(mod)\\n\\tupdateStats(mod)\\nend\\