874	devforum	4194519	Status effect system causing lag when ending	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194519	Scripting	Performance lag and frame freezing occurring when destroying status effect scripts and their associated UI elements upon expiration.	\N	f	beginner	{RemoteEvent,WaitForChild,FireClient,OnClientEvent,Humanoid,task.wait,Destroy}	{}	t	Refactor the 'script-per-effect' architecture into a centralized Status Effect Manager. Replace the individual while-loops with a single system using RunService or a central task scheduler, and implement UI object pooling to avoid the overhead of constant instantiation and destruction.	71	1	3	2025-12-29 06:17:44.668	2026-01-08 17:22:27.133237	{"views": 71, "content": " Essentially, I want to make a basic status effect system. The way I went about it is having several status effects stored in a file within server storage that can be cloned into a folder in players. The scripts would act independently of each other and be simple enough to use as a framework for other status effects. I went through and programmed each one myself. \\n Problem is: whenever they end, I freeze for around a half second to a full second. I checked with most status effects, and they all end this way. Here’s a quick overview of how they work; Main script and parent of all other attributes, this handles the status effects main job. Inside that script, there’s two intvalues, one for strength and duration, meaning they can be shortened or extended from abilities. There is also a local script for handling UI effects, and a remote event so the main script can communicate to the local script. \\n I’d really appreciate a way to optimize these so I don’t get this hefty lag, its very very annoying. Any other recommendations for my current system are also very appreciated! I’m still a beginner scripter, and while I’m proud of myself, I want this to not be infuriating to play with. I’ll attach the main script, the gui script and a video of what happens (using my slowness effect as example): \\n both strength and duration are set to 5 in this example. \\n Main script (serverside): \\n  local timeleft = script.Length\\nlocal Strength = script.Strength\\nlocal char = script.Parent.Parent\\nlocal hum = char:FindFirstChildOfClass(\\"Humanoid\\")\\nlocal event = script.TimeTick\\n\\nlocal plr = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(char)\\n\\nlocal states = char:WaitForChild(\\"Stats\\")\\nlocal defaultWalk = states.WalkSpeed.Value\\nlocal defaultRun = states.SprintSpeed.Value\\n\\nprint(tostring(defaultWalk) .. \\" | \\" .. tostring(defaultRun))\\n\\nwhile true do\\n\\tif timeleft.Value &gt; 0 then -- checks if effect is ended\\n\\t\\ttimeleft.Value -= 1 -- tick\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tstates.WalkSpeed.Value = defaultWalk * (0.1 * Strength.Value)\\n\\t\\tsta", "upvotes": 1, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-29T06:17:44.668Z"}
875	devforum	4196599	My RemoteEvent and RemoteFunction abstraction doesn't work! Please help!1!11!	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4196599	Networking	Parameter misalignment in RemoteEvent.OnServerEvent where the 'name' argument is missing or replaced by subsequent arguments when using a custom networking abstraction module.	\N	f	intermediate	{RemoteEvent,RemoteFunction,OnServerEvent,OnServerInvoke,FireServer,FireClient,InvokeServer,Players.LocalPlayer}	{}	t	An automated tool could check for consistency between the number of arguments passed in :FireServer() versus those defined in the .OnServerEvent:Connect() callback. It could also detect if the 'self' parameter is being correctly passed in method calls (dot vs colon notation), which is a common cause of argument shifting in Lua.	82	3	14	2025-12-29 21:39:16.252	2026-01-08 17:22:28.327005	{"views": 82, "content": " I can only make it closer to working on the client, by replacing all  self._remoteEvent  and  self._remoteFunction  by  script:FindFirstChildwhichIsA(\\"RemoteEvent\\")  and for the RemoteFunction the same. But I feel like it would be a hack and I thought, maybe someone smarter can figure it out. Furthermore after getting the Events correctly, in the  .OnServerEvent  part of the code, instead of getting the name parameter, it is replaced by the agruments after it. Although the player argument is passed correctly. \\n If you see any additional bugs, please notify me! \\n Here is the code: \\n  local Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\n\\nlocal isServer = Players.LocalPlayer == nil\\n\\nlocal Communicator = {} :: Communicator\\n\\nfunction Communicator.init(self: Communicator, Modules)\\n\\tif isServer then\\n\\t\\tself._AsyncBindsServer = {} :: { [string]: { (Player, ...any) -&gt; () } }\\n\\t\\tself._SyncBindsServer = {} :: { [string]: { (Player, ...any) -&gt; any } }\\n\\n\\t\\tself._remoteEvent = Instance.new(\\"RemoteEvent\\", script)\\n\\t\\tself._remoteFunction = Instance.new(\\"RemoteFunction\\", script)\\n\\n\\t\\tself._remoteEvent.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player: Player, name: string, ...)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Binds = self._AsyncBindsServer[name]\\n\\t\\t\\tif not Binds then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, bind in Binds do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tbind(player, ...)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\n\\t\\tself._remoteFunction.OnServerInvoke = function(player: Player, name: string, ...)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Binds = self._SyncBindsServer[name]\\n\\t\\t\\tif not Binds then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, bind in Binds do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\treturn bind(player, ...)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tself._AsyncBindsClient = {} :: { [string]: { (...any) -&gt; () } }\\n\\n\\t\\tself._remoteEvent = script:WaitForChild(\\"RemoteEvent\\")\\n\\t\\tself._remoteFunction = script:WaitForChild(\\"RemoteFunction\\")\\n\\n\\t\\tself._remoteEvent.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(name: string, ...)\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Binds = self._AsyncBindsClient[name]\\n\\t\\t\\tif not Binds or #Binds &lt; 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\treturn\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tfor _, bind in Binds do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tbind(...)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend)\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nif isServer", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 14, "created_at": "2025-12-29T21:39:16.252Z"}
