890	devforum	4194566	Gun System Hitscan help: How do other games overcome client-server time delays?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194566	Networking	Latency-induced hit registration failures in server-side hitscan systems where the server's view of player positions lags behind the client's view.	Implement a 'shooter-first' hit detection model where the client performs the initial raycast for immediate feedback, then sends the data to the server for sanity checks, including distance verification, obstruction checks, and optionally 'lag compensation' by rewinding player positions.	t	intermediate	{Raycast,ViewportPointToRay,Mouse.Hit.Position,Camera.CFrame.Position}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a boilerplate framework for a RemoteEvent-based hit detection system that includes client-side raycasting and a server-side validation script that checks magnitude and line-of-sight.	95	8	5	2025-12-29 06:40:08.133	2026-01-08 17:22:58.875412	{"views": 95, "content": " Hello everyone. \\n For the past few days I’ve been reworking my gun system and decided it would be a good opportunity to test it out, so me and my friends got in a testing game and tried it. The issue we had most of the time was the fact that it didn’t feel like hitscan. \\n I made the gun system using Raycasting, where like every other system I get the origin and the mouse position and shoot a raycast. Raycasting is of course done on the server, which has led to some issues. One issue being that when I shot directly at my opponent, the shot didn’t register. \\n This differs heavily from other games I’ve played like Frontlines or Rivals where they’re bullets feel exactly like how hitscan should. How do these games handle their hitscan fast enough? What can I do to make my hitscan feel better and less delayed? ", "upvotes": 8, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-29T06:40:08.133Z"}
