898	devforum	4194033	Strange bug with Enum.RotateType.MovementRelative	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194033	Scripting	Camera spins rapidly when attached to the character's head in first person unless Enum.RotateType is explicitly set to MovementRelative, even though it is the documented default.	\N	f	intermediate	{Enum.RotateType,UserGameSettings,Enum.CameraType.Scriptable,CFrame}	{}	t	Create a boilerplate script that explicitly initializes UserGameSettings.RotateType to ensure consistent camera behavior regardless of engine defaults.	70	0	1	2025-12-29 02:21:53.012	2026-01-08 17:23:14.677208	{"views": 70, "content": "   Ok so… \\n I’m working with MovementRelative and CameraRelative from RotateType in UserGameSettings. \\n   What is the bug? \\n Well, when I DON’T specify the RotateType, when I attach the camera to the character’s head, it starts spinning SUPER FAST (because the camera is connected to the character). BUT if I set the RotateType to ‘MovementRelative’, it works fine. Like… what? \\n Um… I checked the ‘Default RotateType’ and it’s ‘MovementRelative’… so, why do I have to SPECIFY the RotateType AGAIN? \\n (I forgot to specify… I’m working with Scriptable camera and CFrame for attach the camera to the head. Also, the game is in first person, and this only happens in first person.) \\n   Video with the bug: \\n   \\n     \\n   That’s all? \\n Yes. Please, help. I don’t know if this is a Roblox issue or if this is how MovementRelative works. I would appreciate any response. Thank you. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-12-29T02:21:53.012Z"}
899	devforum	4194306	How to hide player character?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194306	Networking	Preventing the default replication of player character position and models to other clients to stop exploiters from using ESP or wall-hacks in competitive games.	\N	f	advanced	{}	{}	t	A script could be generated to implement a custom character replication system that uses RemoteEvents to send position data only to clients within a certain range or team, while keeping the physical character model in a non-replicating container like ServerStorage.	115	0	5	2025-12-29 04:25:53.196	2026-01-08 17:23:15.73076	{"views": 115, "content": " Hello I just want to hide the player character and make the hidden player’s position hidden also from exploiter. It seem so simple but I have thought about it for hours and haven’t think of a way to do it on Roblox. The problem is the default character system always replicate to all client and there isn’t a simple way to make it not do that. I have came up with a solution that I really do not want to have to do but its like a custom character system and control that fire the position to the server and the server only replicate the location to player that should be able to see the character. But like I kinda need the server authority for the character because making a custom character anti cheat for my game would be a disaster because I have multiple character already made with custom speed and mobility ability. \\n So I’m wondering if I’m just overthinking this and is there is a easier way to hide a player’s character and their position from exploiters? ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-29T04:25:53.196Z"}
