901	devforum	4194234	Slight delay/ stutter with linear velocity	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194234	Physics	Stuttering and delay when applying LinearVelocity for knockback on characters or NPCs due to network ownership latency.	Adjust network ownership of the affected assembly to the client for local responsiveness, or switch to using Part:ApplyImpulse() for instantaneous physics calculations rather than a sustained velocity constraint.	t	intermediate	{LinearVelocity,ApplyImpulse,SetNetworkOwner}	{}	t	An AI agent can provide template code that safely sets network ownership to the server (SetNetworkOwner(null)) or a specific player, and demonstrates how to apply a vector-based impulse for knockback effects.	61	2	3	2025-12-29 03:47:27.251	2026-01-08 17:23:19.303901	{"views": 61, "content": " I’m using linear velocity for knockback force but after the initial hit, the character hesitates for a second before having the force fully applied. \\n Is it better to apply the force on the client? (and if so, how would that work with NPCs) \\n Id love to know if anyone knows how to fix the delay or alternative methods for this. Thank you! \\n Very simple linear velocity \\n   \\n     ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-29T03:47:27.251Z"}
902	devforum	4194119	Ability System Networking Flow	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4194119	Networking	Designing a secure and synchronized networking architecture for an ability system that prevents client-side animation exploits while handling hitboxes and victim state manipulation.	Utilize Server Authority features to control animation replication and input. Maintain a server-side dictionary of permitted animations per player state to validate and forcibly terminate unauthorized tracks played by the client.	t	advanced	{PlayerModule,AnimationTrack,task.defer}	{}	t	A script could generate a server-side validation handler that checks AnimationIds against an allowed list when tracks are played and automatically handles the cleanup of unauthorized client-initiated animations.	76	2	4	2025-12-29 03:01:31.348	2026-01-08 17:23:21.845919	{"views": 76, "content": " I am trying to make an ability system similar to one found in mostly any game/battlegrounds. I can figure out the cooldown system and whatnot, but I am having a hard time deciding for a good flow with abilities. \\nEssentially, this is the current flow without network: \\n \\n Player presses ability \\n Player gets put in animation \\n Hitbox plays at some point after a delay \\n If a player is in hitbox, the animation continues, and the victims position/rotation is changed to match animation, and an animation is played for victim. \\n At some points during animation, damage is dealt to the victim \\n \\n Previously, I was thinking of having a system with animation markers that would report damage and moments where to deal them. But since client has authority over its model, it could just play whatever animation it’d want. \\nBut what is the best flow then? I thought of having clientsided hitreg for the hitbox that’s sanitychecked by the server (current m1 system as well) and then just having server playing damage after some delays. But this could cause desync between clients, although I think it wouldn’t be that relevant since it’s only timing with animation. \\nI also wanted to spawn vfx at specific moments, which markers would’ve been perfect for but now I am unsure after realizing this major security flaw. \\n I am just posting to see if people know what the standard for this is, if there is a better way I am not seeing, etc. Please criticize my idea. ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-29T03:01:31.348Z"}
903	devforum	4193623	How to tell if a user holds their mouse in a plugin widget	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4193623	UI	Detecting mouse button press and release events inside a Roblox plugin widget, as PluginMouse signals primarily fire when interacting with the 3D viewport.	Instead of using plugin:GetMouse(), listen to the InputBegan event on a specific GUI object within the widget. This provides an InputObject representing the press. By connecting to the InputObject's 'Changed' signal, you can reliably detect the 'End' state (release) regardless of whether the cursor has moved off the widget or original element.	t	intermediate	{plugin:GetMouse(),UserInputService,InputBegan,InputObject,DockWidgetPluginGui,Enum.UserInputType,Enum.UserInputState}	{}	t	A coding agent can provide boilerplate code for GUI interaction lifecycles in plugins, specifically implementing the InputObject.Changed pattern for drag-and-drop or long-press mechanics.	93	6	5	2025-12-28 23:11:38.813	2026-01-08 17:23:24.441958	{"views": 93, "content": " Hello, I’m currently making a widget and I want to know how to track the user holding their mouse. inside the widget. \\n I’m doing this via detecting when when they mouse.ButtonUp and mouse.ButtonDown but I noticed that for some reason the pluginMouse only triggers signal when they’re inside of roblox studio instead of the widge.t \\n  -- HoldPrinter.lua (Local Studio Plugin)\\n-- Prints START HOLD and END HOLD with duration using plugin:GetMouse().\\n\\nlocal mouse = plugin:GetMouse()\\n\\nlocal holding = false\\nlocal startedAt = 0\\n\\nprint(\\"[HoldPrinter] Loaded. Click and hold LMB anywhere in the viewport.\\")\\n\\nmouse.Button1Down:Connect(function()\\n\\tprint(\\"print go\\")\\n\\t-- If somehow we get repeated downs without an up, ignore.\\n\\tif holding then return end\\n\\n\\tholding = true\\n\\tstartedAt = os.clock()\\n\\tprint((\\"[HoldPrinter] START HOLD @ %.6f\\"):format(startedAt))\\nend)\\n\\nmouse.Button1Up:Connect(function()\\n\\tprint(\\"yes\\")\\n\\tif not holding then return end\\n\\n\\tlocal endedAt = os.clock()\\n\\tlocal duration = endedAt - startedAt\\n\\tholding = false\\n\\n\\tprint((\\"[HoldPrinter] END HOLD @ %.6f (duration: %.3fs)\\"):format(endedAt, duration))\\nend)\\n  \\n And when I click,  I see no output  \\n I’m wondering if theres a different method that does use UserInputService or PluginMouse like dedicated for widgets ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-28T23:11:38.813Z"}
904	devforum	698243	What does caching mean?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/698243	DataStore	Lack of understanding regarding the definition of 'caching' and its practical application within Roblox game development.	Caching is the process of storing data in local memory (such as a Lua table) after it is retrieved or calculated, so that subsequent requests for that data can be served faster without re-executing the original logic or making external API calls. In Roblox, this is specifically used to manage player data by modifying a local variable during a session and only saving to the DataStoreService at specific intervals or when the player leaves, which helps stay within rate limits.	t	beginner	{DataStoreService}	{}	t	A coding agent can provide standard boilerplate code for a caching layer or data manager that automatically handles the synchronization between in-game variables and DataStore entries.	2527	4	6	2020-07-30 19:46:30.31	2026-01-08 17:23:26.244187	{"views": 2527, "content": " I have seen several people talk about caching, I don’t know what it is ", "upvotes": 4, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 6, "created_at": "2020-07-30T19:46:30.310Z"}
905	devforum	4193715	Client to other client communication	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4193715	Networking	Communicating directly between clients without a server-side intermediary and addressing latency in the client-server-client relay pattern.	Direct client-to-client communication is impossible in Roblox; developers must use RemoteEvents to send data to the server, which then relays it to other clients.	t	beginner	{BindableEvent,RemoteEvent}	{}	f	A coding agent could provide boilerplate code for a RemoteEvent relay system and suggest optimization techniques like client-side prediction or interpolation to handle the perceived delay.	159	3	9	2025-12-28 23:58:45.157	2026-01-08 17:23:27.404912	{"views": 159, "content": " I was under the impression that bindable events will be fired on all clients in the server, but its only the clients own realm. meaning i cant use bindable events in the client to signal  other players. \\n is there a way that I can signal client to all clients without a server script inbetween? ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 9, "created_at": "2025-12-28T23:58:45.157Z"}
906	devforum	4192952	Is this good code?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4192952	Scripting	Review and optimization of a tool script for animation playback and hit detection with leaderstat updates, specifically concerning code cleanliness and architecture.	Feedback provided suggests avoiding 'hanging' scripts directly inside instances (naive architecture), minimizing global variable usage, and considering security implications of client-side logic, though a full refactored version was not provided.	f	beginner	{script.Parent,FindFirstAncestorWhichIsA,GetPlayerFromCharacter,WaitForChild,LoadAnimation,GetPartsInPart,GetTags,Activated,Deactivated,Instance.new}	{}	t	A coding agent could refactor this script into a proper client-server model, moving sensitive state updates (leaderstats) to the server via RemoteEvents and modularizing the tool logic to use a single controller script rather than per-tool scripts.	213	9	8	2025-12-28 18:51:53.791	2026-01-08 17:23:30.628773	{"views": 213, "content": " Hi, i just wanted to know if this code is good it works but i am just asking if it is clean? \\n  local tool = script.Parent\\nlocal handle = tool.Handle\\n\\nlocal plr = script:FindFirstAncestorWhichIsA(\\"Player\\") or game:GetService\\"Players\\":GetPlayerFromCharacter(tool.Parent)\\n\\nlocal anim:Animation = tool:WaitForChild(\\"R15Slash\\")\\n\\nlocal debounce = false\\nlocal debouncecooldown = .5\\n\\nlocal activated = false\\n\\nlocal function Animate()\\n\\tlocal char = tool.Parent\\n\\tif char:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\") then\\n\\t\\tlocal hum:Humanoid = char:FindFirstChild(\\"Humanoid\\")\\n\\t\\tlocal animator:Animator\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif hum:FindFirstChild(\\"Animator\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tanimator = hum:FindFirstChild(\\"Animator\\")\\n\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\tanimator = Instance.new(\\"Animator\\", hum)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal loadedanim = animator:LoadAnimation(anim)\\n\\t\\tloadedanim:Play()\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nlocal function sickledeactivate()\\n\\twait(0.05)\\n\\tactivated = false\\nend\\n\\nlocal function sickleturbo()\\n\\tif debounce == false then\\n\\t\\tdebounce = true\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tAnimate()\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tfor i,hit in game.Workspace:GetPartsInPart(handle) do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tfor i,v in hit:GetTags() do\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tif v == \\"wheat\\" then\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tplr.leaderstats.wheat.Value += 1\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\twait(debouncecooldown)\\n\\t\\t\\tdebounce = false\\n\\n\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nscript.Parent.Activated:Connect(sickleturbo)\\n\\nscript.Parent.Deactivated:Connect(sickledeactivate)\\n\\n  \\n thanks ", "upvotes": 9, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 8, "created_at": "2025-12-28T18:51:53.791Z"}
907	devforum	4193687	Pathfinding clipping and going through corners of walls	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4193687	Scripting	Roblox PathfindingService generates waypoints that clip through wall corners, causing NPCs to get stuck despite adjustments to AgentRadius and WaypointSpacing.	Enable the 'PathfindingUseImprovedSearch' property located within the Workspace properties to improve the search algorithm's accuracy.	t	intermediate	{PathfindingService,AgentRadius,WaypointSpacing,PathfindingUseImprovedSearch}	{}	t	A coding agent can set the 'PathfindingUseImprovedSearch' property in the Workspace or implement a post-processing script that performs raycasts between waypoints to check for wall collisions and offset them away from corners.	66	2	3	2025-12-28 23:45:46.353	2026-01-08 17:23:30.992536	{"views": 66, "content": " I’m using Roblox’s pathfinding service to compute and create my paths, however for specific paths, the path is clipping the corners of walls and making my NPC get stuck as shown. Adjusting AgentRadius and WaypointSpacing don’t seem to help avoid this. No modifiers are used in the parts for the walls. I would like to find another way of correcting this other than hacky ways such as duplicating the wall and making it slightly bigger or costs so it goes around. Any ideas to fix this? Thanks. \\n          image  790×1050 38.6 KB         ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-28T23:45:46.353Z"}
