939	devforum	4176931	How to improve my footsteps module	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4176931	Scripting	High client memory usage and performance overhead caused by creating individual .Touched event connections for every instance in a large collection of parts.	Use event delegation by connecting a single .Touched listener to the player's HumanoidRootPart instead of the environment parts, then check the hit object's parent or tag to trigger specific sounds.	t	beginner	{CollectionService:GetTagged,Humanoid.FloorMaterial,GetPropertyChangedSignal,BasePart.Touched}	{}	t	Identify loops that attach event listeners to multiple instances of the same type and suggest refactoring to a centralized listener or using spatial query APIs like Workspace:GetPartBoundsInBox.	108	3	5	2025-12-23 16:51:52.7	2026-01-08 17:24:46.781784	{"views": 108, "content": " Hey guys, today I’ve been working on a footsteps system for the player which will be expanded upon in the future, but for now just simply plays sounds depending on the floor material or part touched. I need help coming up with reliable ways to optimize this script going forward, as I’ve noticed my game’s client memory usage is going too far up for my comfort. Sorry if this is a bizarre request for the forum, I just don’t have any friends that code to help me out here \\n  local footstepsModule = {}\\n--Services\\nlocal Players = game:GetService(\\"Players\\")\\nlocal ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\")\\nlocal CollectionService = game:GetService(\\"CollectionService\\")\\n\\n--Variables\\nlocal clientVariables = require(ReplicatedStorage.Modules.Data.clientVariables)\\nlocal player = Players.LocalPlayer\\nlocal character = player.Character or player.CharacterAdded:Wait()\\nlocal humanoid = character.Humanoid\\nlocal footstepSound = character.HumanoidRootPart:WaitForChild(\\"Running\\")\\n\\nlocal wildGrass = CollectionService:GetTagged(\\"WildGrass\\")\\n\\n--Sounds\\nlocal rustlingGrass = ReplicatedStorage.Assets.Sounds.SE.Overworld.rustlingGrass\\n\\nlocal grass = ReplicatedStorage.Assets.Sounds.SE.Overworld.Footsteps.grass\\nlocal plastic = ReplicatedStorage.Assets.Sounds.SE.Overworld.Footsteps.plastic\\n\\n--Floor material changed\\nlocal floorMaterialChanged = humanoid:GetPropertyChangedSignal(\\"FloorMaterial\\"):Connect(function()\\n\\tfootstepSound.PlaybackSpeed = 1\\n\\tfootstepSound.Volume = 0.5\\n\\tif humanoid.FloorMaterial == Enum.Material.Grass then\\n\\t\\tfootstepSound.SoundId = grass.SoundId\\n\\telseif humanoid.FloorMaterial == Enum.Material.Plastic then\\n\\t\\tfootstepSound.SoundId = plastic.SoundId\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n\\n--On wild grass touched\\nlocal function onWildGrassTouched()\\n\\tif humanoid then\\n\\t\\trustlingGrass:Play()\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nfor _, part in ipairs(wildGrass) do\\n\\tpart.Touched:Connect(onWildGrassTouched)\\nend\\n\\nreturn footstepsModule\\n  ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-23T16:51:52.700Z"}
