947	devforum	4180131	Issue with room generation	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4180131	Scripting	Implementing procedural room generation using a backtracking algorithm and collision detection with GetPartsInPart to prevent overlaps.	\N	f	intermediate	{WaitForChild,GetChildren,GetPivot,PivotTo,OverlapParams,GetPartsInPart,GetDescendants,ToObjectSpace,Inverse}	{"Cannot generate rooms - no valid configuration found!","Cannot place first room!","Failed to generate all rooms. Only generated ..."}	t	A coding agent could assist by refining the backtracking logic to prevent infinite loops, optimizing the spatial query using WorldRoot:Raycast or Region3 for better performance, and ensuring CFrame math for entrance-to-exit alignment is mathematically robust.	107	2	5	2025-12-24 15:44:02.169	2026-01-08 17:25:02.779321	{"views": 107, "content": "  activator = game.Workspace:WaitForChild(\\"activado\\")\\nnumOfRoomsToGeneratePart = game.Workspace:WaitForChild(\\"num of rooms\\")\\ndebounce = false\\n\\nlocal function shuffleArray(array)\\n\\tlocal shuffled = {}\\n\\tfor i = 1, #array do\\n\\t\\tshuffled[i] = array[i]\\n\\tend\\n\\tfor i = #shuffled, 2, -1 do\\n\\t\\tlocal j = math.random(1, i)\\n\\t\\tshuffled[i], shuffled[j] = shuffled[j], shuffled[i]\\n\\tend\\n\\treturn shuffled\\nend\\n\\nactivator.ClickDetector.MouseClick:Connect(function()\\n\\tif debounce then return end\\n\\tdebounce = true\\n\\tactivator.SurfaceGui.TextLabel.Text = \\"...\\"\\n\\tfor _, part in pairs(workspace[\\"current rooms\\"]:GetChildren()) do\\n\\t\\tif part.Name ~= \\"start\\" then part:Destroy() end\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\tlocal numOfRoomsToGenerate = tonumber(numOfRoomsToGeneratePart.SurfaceGui.TextBox.Text)\\n\\tlocal allRoomTypes = workspace[\\"room types\\"]:GetChildren()\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal triedAtPosition = {}\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal placedRooms = {}\\n\\tlocal currentIndex = 1\\n\\n\\twhile currentIndex &lt;= numOfRoomsToGenerate do\\n\\t\\ttask.wait()\\n\\t\\tlocal lastExitCFrame\\n\\t\\tif currentIndex == 1 then\\n\\t\\t\\tlastExitCFrame = workspace[\\"current rooms\\"].start.exit.CFrame\\n\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\tlastExitCFrame = placedRooms[currentIndex - 1].exit.CFrame\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif not triedAtPosition[currentIndex] then\\n\\t\\t\\ttriedAtPosition[currentIndex] = {}\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tlocal availableRoomTypes = {}\\n\\t\\tfor _, roomType in ipairs(allRoomTypes) do\\n\\t\\t\\tif not triedAtPosition[currentIndex][roomType.Name] then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttable.insert(availableRoomTypes, roomType)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tif #availableRoomTypes == 0 then\\n\\t\\t\\ttriedAtPosition[currentIndex] = nil\\n\\t\\t\\tif #placedRooms == 0 then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\twarn(\\"Cannot generate rooms - no valid configuration found!\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tbreak\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal lastRoom = table.remove(placedRooms)\\n\\t\\t\\tlastRoom:Destroy()\\n\\t\\t\\tcurrentIndex = currentIndex - 1\\n\\n\\t\\t\\twarn(\\"Backtracking to position \\" .. tostring(currentIndex))\\n\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\tlocal shuffledRooms = shuffleArray(availableRoomTypes)\\n\\n\\t\\tlocal placed = false\\n\\t\\tlocal selectedRoomTemplate = nil\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tfor _, roomTemplate in ipairs(shuffledRooms) do\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal room = roomTemplat", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 5, "created_at": "2025-12-24T15:44:02.169Z"}
948	devforum	4188778	Extreme Lag With CFraming Humanoids When EvaluateStateMachine is Disabled?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4188778	Physics	Disabling Humanoid.EvaluateStateMachine or the FallingDown HumanoidStateType causes significant performance degradation and high CPU usage from RaycastBroadphase and RaycastTerrain calls when CFraming Humanoid models.	\N	f	advanced	{Humanoid.EvaluateStateMachine,Humanoid:BulkMoveTo,Enum.HumanoidStateType.FallingDown,PVInstance:PivotTo,Humanoid.BreakJointsOnDeath,Humanoid.RequiresNeck,Humanoid.AutomaticScalingEnabled,Humanoid.AutoRotate}	{}	f	A coding agent could perform a static analysis check to warn developers that disabling EvaluateStateMachine or the FallingDown state currently triggers a known engine bug that increases Raycast overhead instead of reducing it.	95	6	4	2025-12-27 11:02:08.078	2026-01-08 17:25:04.358448	{"views": 95, "content": " For context, I’m working on a RTS game with lots of units, here’s context on its pipeline: \\n \\n the server handles pathfinding and other calculations, sending unit position data to clients (every 1/10th of a second) \\n the client then attempts to interpolate (lerp) and render NPC models over the received unit position data (every render step) \\n \\n Additional details: \\n \\n I use  :BulkMoveTo()  for batch-CFraming all NPC models over position data. \\n I disabled BreakJointsOnDeath, RequiresNeck, AutomaticScalingEnabled, and AutoRotate on the Humanoids. \\n \\n Stresstesting 400 units, here’s a comparison of what I experience with EvaluateStateMachine enabled and disabled, \\n   EvaluateStateMachine enabled \\n   \\n     \\n   EvaluateStateMachine disabled \\n   \\n     \\n    \\n It’s not that I “need EvaluateStateMachine to be disabled”, but moreso just genuinely curious as to why this could even happen in the first place? You’ll notice how the FPS continously sinks down, it’s so odd. To be honest, I assumed disabling EvaluateStateMachine would help with performance- \\n And I want to really specify, I literally changed absolutely nothing except for EvaluateStateMachine between these two videos. You can see how the received network bandwidth relatively stays near 10 Kb/s, so there’s no issue with networking, it is seriously just the CFraming… \\n And yes I tested this with  .CFrame  being directly set rather than using  :BulkMoveTo()  and nope, same behavior, same lag. \\n I’m just curious as to why this even happens? Does anybody have an idea as to why? ", "upvotes": 6, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-27T11:02:08.078Z"}
949	devforum	4188870	Can i assign players to servers based on their level?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4188870	Networking	Implementing level-based server matchmaking using cross-server communication and teleportation.	Use MessagingService to communicate player levels across different server instances and TeleportService to move players to the server that matches their level range.	t	intermediate	{MessagingService,TeleportService}	{}	t	A coding agent can generate a framework using MessagingService:SubscribeAsync to listen for server capacity/level updates and TeleportService:TeleportToPlaceInstance to move the player once a match is found.	92	2	4	2025-12-27 11:50:58.122	2026-01-08 17:25:05.170122	{"views": 92, "content": " So, my question is: \\n 1- I have a Player A, that has a level of 200 on a game, and i have a player B, that has a level of 210, when player A joins the game, if the game finds another server that is not full and has a player B of level 200-299, can i teleport player A to the B player’s server? \\n 2- If yes, will this affect analystics of roblox? Bc for example, a player joins the game, and get instantly teleported to another server, will roblox consider he played the game for 10 seconds, left and then rejoined? ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-27T11:50:58.122Z"}
950	devforum	4188687	Will These Tables Leak Memory?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4188687	Scripting	Potential memory leaks from creating and discarding local tables inside a high-frequency RenderStepped loop.	The tables are local to the function scope and have no external references after the function execution, making them eligible for garbage collection. While it creates 'GC pressure', it does not constitute a memory leak.	t	beginner	{RunService.RenderStepped,task.synchronize,Workspace:BulkMoveTo,Enum.BulkMoveMode}	{}	t	A static analysis tool or linter can identify table allocations inside RunService events and suggest table recycling (table.clear) to reduce garbage collector overhead.	186	7	9	2025-12-27 10:07:30.764	2026-01-08 17:25:08.056001	{"views": 186, "content": " I have a RTS system where the server sends unit position data to the client, and the client renders NPC models over this data. This data is looped over and rendered through  .RenderStepped , \\n  local npcTransform -- imagine this table is being updated everytime the server sends position data\\n\\nRNS.RenderStepped:ConnectParallel(function(deltaTime)\\n\\tlocal npcPartRender = {}\\n\\tlocal cframeRender = {}\\n\\n\\tfor npcHRP, transformData in npcTransform do\\n\\t\\tlocal calculatedPosition = ...\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\ttable.insert(npcPartRender, npcHRP)\\n\\t\\ttable.insert(cframeRender, calculatedPosition)\\n\\tend\\n\\n\\ttask.synchronize()\\n\\tworkspace:BulkMoveTo(npcPartRender, cframeRender, Enum.BulkMoveMode.FireCFrameChanged)\\nend)\\n  \\n I’m referring to  npcPartRender  and  cframeRender , and I recognize that: \\n \\n new tables are being made every render step \\n the tables are assumingly never referred to by any function after each render step \\n \\n Should I worry about the table not being garbage collected and piling up as a memory leak? ", "upvotes": 7, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 9, "created_at": "2025-12-27T10:07:30.764Z"}
952	devforum	4187218	Smooth camera menu lerp tween problem thing	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4187218	Scripting	Implementing a smooth camera parallax effect for a menu where the camera rotation is driven by mouse position without causing jitter or 'spazzing' behavior.	Calculate a target CFrame based on the normalized offset of the mouse from the center of the screen, then use CFrame:Lerp or a spring module to smoothly transition the camera towards that target relative to a fixed origin point.	f	beginner	{RunService,RenderStepped,CFrame,Lerp,ViewportSize,GetMouseLocation,UserInputService}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a robust boilerplate using RenderStepped that calculates a target rotation from screen-space mouse coordinates and applies it to a base CFrame using a lerp function with a delta-time adjusted alpha.	72	2	7	2025-12-26 23:15:21.713	2026-01-08 17:25:12.267224	{"views": 72, "content": " Heya, I am making one of those generic menu screen effects for the camera, where the camera gets offsetted by the position of the mouse until a certain point. I tried making my own code but because I have no idea what I’m doing it didnt work the way I intended it to. It works but I am clueless on how I would make it smooth, since its not smooth in this state. And yes I have looked through the internet for answers but I cannot find any smooth ones. \\n CODE: \\n  --//VARIABLES//--\\nlocal camera = workspace.Currentcameraera\\nlocal camerapart = workspace:WaitForChild(\\"CameraPositionPartThingPlaceholderUltimate\\")\\nlocal mouse = game:GetService(\\"Players\\").LocalPlayer:GetMouse()\\n\\n--/Constants/--\\nlocal SMOOTH_FACTOR = 0.2\\n\\n--//ACTIONS//--\\n\\n--/Move camera/--\\ngame:GetService(\\"RunService\\").RenderStepped:Connect(function()\\n\\tlocal goalX = math.rad((((mouse.Y - mouse.ViewSizeY / 2) / mouse.ViewSizeY)) * -maxTilt)\\n\\tlocal goalY = math.rad((((mouse.X - mouse.ViewSizeX / 2) / mouse.ViewSizeX)) * -maxTilt)\\n\\t\\n\\tcamera.CFrame = camerapart.CFrame:Lerp(\\n\\t\\tcamera.CFrame * CFrame.Angles(goalX, goalY, 0),\\n\\t\\tSMOOTH_FACTOR\\n\\t)\\nend)\\n  \\n Any help is appreciated! ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 7, "created_at": "2025-12-26T23:15:21.713Z"}
953	devforum	4161702	Raycast Suspension Problem	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4161702	Physics	Raycast suspension height decreases as the vehicle's distance from the world origin (0, 0, 0) increases.	\N	f	intermediate	{UserInputService,Humanoid,os.clock,Workspace:Raycast}	{}	t	Review the vector math in the suspension logic. This issue typically occurs when world-space coordinates are incorrectly used in a local-space calculation or when a Raycast's direction vector is calculated using a target position rather than a displacement vector (Target - Origin).	98	2	3	2025-12-18 22:15:24.862	2026-01-08 17:25:14.446656	{"views": 98, "content": " hello everyone. i’m writing my own raycast vehicle suspension system and have encountered a problem. basically, the further away the suspension is from 0, 0, 0, the shorter the suspension height becomes. any idea how to fix this? \\n         image  1040×270 45.6 KB         \\n the local script responsible for controlling the vehicle: \\n  local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer\\nlocal char = player.Character\\nlocal humanoid = char:WaitForChild(\\"Humanoid\\")\\nlocal inputService = game:GetService(\\"UserInputService\\")\\n\\nlocal inputs = {\\n\\tThrottle = 0,\\n\\tSteer = 0,\\n\\tDrift = false,\\n}\\nlocal currentPressedInputs = {\\n\\tW = false,\\n\\tS = false,\\n\\tA = false,\\n\\tD = false,\\n\\tShift = false,\\n\\tQ = false,\\n\\tF = false\\n}\\n\\nlocal function onInputBegan(input, gameProcessed)\\n\\tif gameProcessed or not char.Humanoid.Sit or char.Humanoid.SeatPart.Name ~= \\"DriverSeat\\" then return end\\n\\t\\n\\tif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.W then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Throttle = 1\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.W = true\\n\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.S then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Throttle = -1\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.S = true\\n\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.A then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Steer = -1\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.A = true\\n\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.D then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Steer = 1\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.D = true\\n\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift or input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.RightShift then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Drift = true\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.Shift = true\\n\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.Q then\\n\\t\\tinputs.Charging = true\\n\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.Q = true\\n\\tend\\nend\\n\\nlocal function onInputEnded(input, gameProcessed)\\n\\tif gameProcessed then return end\\n\\tif char.Humanoid.Sit == false then return end\\n\\tif char.Humanoid.SeatPart.Name == \\"DriverSeat\\" then\\n\\t\\tif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.W then\\n\\t\\t\\tif currentPressedInputs.S == false then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tinputs.Throttle = 0\\n\\t\\t\\telseif currentPressedInputs.S == true then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tinputs.Throttle = -1\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\tcurrentPressedInputs.W = false\\n\\t\\telseif input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.S then\\n\\t\\t\\tif currentPressedInputs.W == false then", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-18T22:15:24.862Z"}
954	devforum	4188550	Trying to Understand the Limits of Parallel Lua	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4188550	Scripting	Confusion regarding the mapping of Actors to CPU threads in Parallel Luau and whether a single script/Actor can spawn multiple simultaneous parallel threads using task.desynchronize().	Each Actor instance is allocated to a single thread at a time for parallel execution. To utilize multiple CPU cores/threads, a developer must create multiple Actor instances and distribute tasks across them, as work within a single Actor is executed sequentially on its assigned thread.	t	intermediate	{task.desynchronize,task.synchronize,RunService.RenderStepped,Actor.BindToMessageParallel,Actor.SendMessage,RBXScriptSignal.ConnectParallel}	{}	t	Create a boilerplate generator that takes a function and automatically sets up an Actor-based worker pool with a distributor script to handle task load balancing across multiple cores.	86	3	3	2025-12-27 08:50:59.632	2026-01-08 17:25:19.655531	{"views": 86, "content": " so about parallel lua, lets say i have a .RenderStepped \\n  local array = {}\\nRNS.RenderStepped:Connect(function(deltaTime)\\n    for _,v in array do\\n        runFunction1(v)\\n    end\\n    \\n    task.synchronize()\\n    runFunction2()\\nend)\\n  \\n if i run this single script under a single actor, can i split each runFunction1() into their own  seperate  parallel threads with  task.desynchronize()  ? \\n or will it only loop through runFunction1() in the same parallel thread for that actor \\n and if so, does that mean that an actor only has access to two threads, a serial thread and its own parallel thread? and that’s why you have to make multiple actors to utilize multiple threads? ", "upvotes": 3, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-27T08:50:59.632Z"}
