958	devforum	4188114	Animations messing with head rotation script	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4188114	Animation	Character animations are overriding or distorting programmatic head rotation applied via Neck.C0, leading to erratic head movement and restricted range of motion.	\N	f	intermediate	{RunService,RenderStepped,CFrame,ToObjectSpace,fromEulerAnglesYXZ,Lerp,RemoteEvent}	{}	t	A coding agent could suggest modifying the script to use Motor6D.Transform instead of C0, as Transform is reset every frame by animations, or demonstrate how to apply rotations after the animator step to ensure the script has the final say in the head's orientation.	74	0	1	2025-12-27 05:20:32.238	2026-01-08 17:25:31.678259	{"views": 74, "content": " \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  Keep it simple and clear! \\nI want to make it so the head rotation (head looks where camera is looking) is unaffected by animations \\n \\n \\n  What is the issue?  Include screenshots / videos if possible! \\nThe animations in my game do mess with the rotation, for example when you look to the side while running, the head looks up like crazy, and on  the idle I can only turn my head left, not right.  \\n \\n \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Did you look for solutions on the Creator Hub? \\nI tried removing the head keyframes from the animations, which did work, but the animations felt super bland and some require some level of animation for the head. \\n \\n \\n This is the script I use for the head rotation. \\n  local YOffset = Neck.C0 -- original neck offset\\n\\n-- settings\\nlocal HEAD_ROTATION_ALPHA = 0.15\\nlocal REPLICATION_DELAY = 1 / 8\\nlocal lastReplication = 0\\n\\nRunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function(dt)\\n\\tdt = math.min(dt * 60, 1)\\n\\n\\tif Player:GetAttribute(\\"HeadMovementEnabled\\") then\\n\\t\\tlocal camDir = Root.CFrame:ToObjectSpace(Camera.CFrame).LookVector\\n\\t\\tlocal yaw = math.asin(camDir.X)     -- left/right\\n\\t\\tlocal pitch = math.asin(camDir.Y)   -- up/down\\n\\n\\t\\tlocal targetCFrame = YOffset * CFrame.fromEulerAnglesYXZ(pitch * -1,0, yaw * -1)\\n\\t\\tNeck.C0 = Neck.C0:Lerp(targetCFrame, HEAD_ROTATION_ALPHA * dt)\\n\\n\\t\\tif os.clock() - lastReplication &gt; REPLICATION_DELAY then\\n\\t\\t\\tlastReplication = os.clock()\\n\\t\\t\\tReplicatedStorage.Remotes.Player.HeadMovement:FireServer(targetCFrame)\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\telse\\n\\t\\tNeck.C0 = YOffset\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  \\n   \\n    \\n \\n     ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2025-12-27T05:20:32.238Z"}
