968	devforum	4187446	Can you allow rain to go around a roof rather than completely stopping it?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4187446	Scripting	Implementing localized rain occlusion for particle emitters using raycasting to detect indoor areas instead of toggling the entire system.	Create a grid of rain emitters above the player and raycast downwards for each; disable only the specific emitters that hit a roof or cover so rain continues to fall in open areas.	t	intermediate	{ParticleEmitter,WorldRoot:Raycast}	{}	t	Generate a script that manages a dynamic grid of ParticleEmitters following the player, performing periodic raycasts to update the 'Enabled' property based on whether the raycast hits an obstruction.	78	5	2	2025-12-27 00:40:38.157	2026-01-08 17:25:51.981273	{"views": 78, "content": " I am currently working on a weather system for an upcoming project. I added a detection module to check whether players are indoors or outdoors. The result feels unrealistic. I want to know if there is a way to make rain emit around a part instead of passing through it. The rain uses a single particle emitter parented to a part with a high emission rate, so I am unsure if I need to split the emitter’s parts or resize it to wrap around roofs. The video below shows the rain stopping once the camera gets detected as indoors. I would rather have the rain flow around the roof instead of stopping entirely. \\n              \\n ", "upvotes": 5, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-27T00:40:38.157Z"}
