987	devforum	4182431	Camera Change On Mobile Not Preserving Rotation	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4182431	Scripting	Switching CameraType from Enum.CameraType.Track back to Enum.CameraType.Custom via a GUI button on mobile causes the camera rotation to unexpectedly shift 30-90 degrees, a behavior not present on desktop.	\N	f	intermediate	{CameraType,CameraSubject,Enum.CameraType.Track,Enum.CameraType.Custom,Enum.CameraType.Scriptable,RunService.RenderStepped,CFrame}	{"Unable to find humanoid for cam reset"}	t	A coding agent could attempt to implement a camera transition wrapper that utilizes task.defer() or task.wait() before re-enabling Custom CameraType to avoid race conditions with mobile touch-input handling.	84	2	4	2025-12-25 11:16:53.469	2026-01-08 17:26:30.535684	{"views": 84, "content": " Hello, I’m running into a mobile-only camera issue where switching the camera from  CameraType.Track  on a part then back to  CameraType.Custom  via a GUI button causes the camera rotation to shift around 30-90 degrees. This does not happen on desktop or when canceling via a keyboard input. It is such a one-off I have no clue why its doing it. \\n Some context: this camera work is done via a local script and below is the module script that handles the camera: \\n  local KickCamera = {}\\n\\n-- Set the camera to track the ball\\nfunction KickCamera.Start(ball)\\n\\tlocal RunService = game:GetService(\\"RunService\\")\\n\\tlocal cam = workspace.CurrentCamera\\n\\tcam.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Track\\n\\tcam.CameraSubject = ball\\nend\\n\\n-- Reset the camera back to the player\\nfunction KickCamera.Stop(player)\\n\\tlocal cam = workspace.CurrentCamera\\n\\tcam.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Custom\\n\\t\\n\\tlocal humanoid = player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChildOfClass(\\"Humanoid\\")\\n\\tif not humanoid then error(\\"Unable to find humanoid for cam reset\\") return end\\n\\t\\n\\tcam.CameraSubject = humanoid\\nend\\n\\nreturn KickCamera\\n  \\n The flow is like this in the local player script: Create Ball → KickCamera.Start(ball) → Click the button → button calls KickCamera.Stop(player) → Camera returns but it snaps counter-clockwise a few degrees → Crash Out \\n Again this works perfectly clicking the button desktop or when using a key press to call the KickCamera.Stop method. I have tried storing the camera CFrame before the  Start  method and then restoring it after the stop method but that didn’t work either. I even waited for the render step to finish before attempting to restore the camera CFrame. \\n Has anyone experienced something similar and could offer some advice or help? The closest thing I found to this was this thread here:  Changing CameraType to Custom Resets Camera Position  but its been apparently fixed so I assume I am doing something wrong or misunderstanding some fundamental operation related to cameras in mobile ", "upvotes": 2, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2025-12-25T11:16:53.469Z"}
