975	devforum	4183846	What are some good techniques that I can employ with my games for better organization?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4183846	Scripting	Optimizing Roblox game project structure and script organization beyond basic manager-script patterns.	Utilize Single Script Architecture (SSA) with central handlers, implement Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) using metatables, apply decoupling and abstraction principles, and consider Finite State Machines (FSM) for complex logic.	t	intermediate	{metatables}	{}	t	A coding agent can generate boilerplate directory structures and loader scripts for Single Script Architecture (SSA) or scaffolds for Finite State Machine modules.	155	15	11	2025-12-25 21:16:44.031	2026-01-08 17:26:06.82564	{"views": 155, "content": " I’m trying to fix my organization for future games. \\n Currently, I divide scripts into modules, and classes, and a respective manager script that manages each module. I feel like this isn’t the best way to do it, but it’s how I do it. \\n I’m in the process of researching ECS (Entity Component Systems) for better organization, and to structure my projects better. I wanted to experiment and try to create something with that, just to see how it felt, as I’m familiar with the term: Composition over Inheritance, and how you’re not supposed to use inheritance in areas that composition would prove to be better. \\n I’m trying to get better at scripting, and I thought I should ask around, and try to see how other people do things, so I can learn from it. \\n So, if you have some pointers into improving my organization, or just want to show me how you organize, I would greatly appreciate it. \\n I’m sorry if this question has been asked before, I just want to personally ask, and find out how others organize things. ", "upvotes": 15, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 11, "created_at": "2025-12-25T21:16:44.031Z"}
