977	devforum	868270	How do I make a Skinned Mesh into a ragdoll with a script?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/868270	Physics	Creating a procedural ragdoll for a Skinned Mesh where BallSocketConstraints applied to Bones do not result in movement or rotation.	The user achieved a result by applying BallSocketConstraints to the bone hierarchy, although it resulted in 'shaking' which they accepted as a solution.	t	intermediate	{Bone,BallSocketConstraint,Instance,Attachment,GetDescendants}	{}	t	Create a script that iterates through a Skinned Mesh hierarchy, generates Attachments at each Bone's position, and links them using BallSocketConstraints or HingeConstraints based on the joint type.	11338	54	20	2020-11-13 03:03:07.28	2026-01-08 17:26:10.539903	{"views": 11338, "content": " \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  I want to turn a Skinned Mesh of a Half-Life 2 character into a ragdoll \\n \\n \\n  What is the issue?  None of the bones move. \\n https://gyazo.com/cf958ecfc5cdd86e290f6fa96de93b21  \\n \\n \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Tried making the ball socket joints attachments 0 and 1 to the bone and it’s parent and if it has no parent attachment 1 is attachment 0. \\n \\n \\n This is the script I created. \\n  for i,v in pairs(script.Parent:WaitForChild(\\"RootPart\\"):GetDescendants()) do\\n\\tif v:IsA(\\"Bone\\") then\\n\\t\\tlocal attachment = Instance.new(\\"BallSocketConstraint\\", v)\\n\\t\\tattachment.Name = \\"ragdolljoint\\"\\n\\t\\tattachment.Attachment0 = v\\n\\t\\tif v.Parent:IsA(\\"Bone\\") then\\n\\t\\t\\tattachment.Attachment1 = v.Parent\\n\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\tattachment.Attachment1 = v\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\tend\\nend\\n  \\n It makes no errors and the bones don’t rotate or move. \\n edit: this is way later and i LOVE IT  https://gyazo.com/44f9c7a2826dcffa597d94cf09c8c77f  ", "upvotes": 54, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 20, "created_at": "2020-11-13T03:03:07.280Z"}
