984	devforum	4185777	Detecting infinite loops or permanent yields in .Start functions without blocking Loader	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4185777	Scripting	The ModuleLoader loop is blocked when a module's .Start() function yields infinitely or runs an infinite loop, preventing subsequent modules from loading.	Wrap the .Start() call in a separate thread using task.spawn() and implement a watchdog timer using task.delay() to detect if the module takes too long to initialize. Alternatively, redesign services to handle their own asynchronous tasks so the loader can return immediately.	t	intermediate	{pcall,require,task.spawn,task.delay,ModuleScript}	{}	t	A coding agent could generate a standard 'Service Runner' utility that wraps module execution in a task.spawn with a timeout check and a custom error handler to log failures without stopping the main execution thread.	69	0	3	2025-12-26 14:07:20.914	2026-01-08 17:26:24.434729	{"views": 69, "content": " Hi everyone, \\n I’m building a ModuleLoader in Roblox that goes through all my Handlers (ModuleScripts) and calls their  .Start()  function if it exists. My loader works fine for normal handlers, but I have a problem: \\n If a  .Start()  function contains an infinite loop or yields forever, the loader gets stuck and can’t continue loading the remaining services. Using  pcall  only catches errors, but it  doesn’t help with blocking functions . \\n \\n   Here’s my loader (very simple): \\n  local Loader = {}\\n\\nfunction Loader.Load(Services : {ModuleScript})\\n\\t\\n\\tfor _, Service in Services do\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal Success, Result = pcall(require, Service)\\n\\t\\tif Success then\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"[MODULE-LOADER]: Service: '\\"..Service.Name..\\"' Loaded.\\")\\n\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\twarn(\\"[MODULE-LOADER]: Service: '\\"..Service.Name..\\"' Failed to load. Error:\\", Result)\\n\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif Result.Start then\\n\\t\\t\\tlocal Success, ErrorMessage = pcall(Result.Start) -- If Ts Yields, the Loader Yields too\\n\\t\\t\\tif Success then\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"[MODULE-LOADER]: Service: '\\"..Service.Name..\\"' Started.\\")\\n\\t\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\t\\twarn(\\"[MODULE-LOADER]: Service: '\\"..Service.Name..\\"' Failed to Start. Error:\\", Result)\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t\\n\\t\\telse\\n\\t\\t\\tprint(\\"[MODULE-LOADER]: Service: '\\"..Service.Name..\\"' has no Start function.\\")\\n\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\n\\tend\\n\\t\\nend\\n\\n-- No get function. Services get other modules with require for autocomplete, not that deep gng\\n\\nreturn Loader\\n  \\n    \\n   My only Solution was This: \\n  local Success, ErrorMessage = pcall(function()\\n\\ttask.spawn(Result.Start)\\nend)\\n  \\n But I don’t think this will catch errors inside  Result.Start , because  pcall  only wraps the call to  task.spawn . Since  task.spawn  runs  Result.Start  in a new thread,  pcall  returns immediately and cannot detect any errors that happen inside  Result.Start  itself. \\n    \\n   Goal \\n If a .Start() function yields, the Loader will print that a specific functions yields, \\nand it will just continue looping trough the Handlers. ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 3, "created_at": "2025-12-26T14:07:20.914Z"}
