1000	devforum	4182487	OnClient Event error, can't find the player	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4182487	Scripting	The developer is incorrectly expecting the 'Player' object to be passed as the first argument to the 'OnClientEvent' listener in a LocalScript after calling 'FireClient(Player)' from the server.	In LocalScripts, 'OnClientEvent' does not receive the Player object because the client already has access to it via 'game.Players.LocalPlayer'. The 'Player' argument in the listener should be removed or replaced with 'game.Players.LocalPlayer'.	t	beginner	{FireClient,OnClientEvent,ProximityPrompt,LocalPlayer,ReplicatedStorage}	{}	t	Identify cases where a LocalScript's RemoteEvent.OnClientEvent callback includes a parameter named 'Player' (or similar) when the server-side FireClient only passes the Player object without additional arguments.	82	1	6	2025-12-25 11:50:09.937	2026-01-08 17:26:58.751754	{"views": 82, "content": " I’m trying to make so when you Press Proximity Prompt,  FireClient:()  happens, everything looks normal but when it reaches to the local script, and comes to character variable, it just prints error for the unknown reason. \\nHere is the Server Script: \\n  local Event = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\"):WaitForChild(\\"SanstaDialogueEvent\\")\\n\\nlocal db = true\\n\\nscript.Parent.Triggered:Connect(function(Player)\\n\\tif db == true then\\n\\t\\tdb = false\\n\\t\\tEvent:FireClient(Player)\\n\\t\\tprint(\\"works\\")\\n\\t\\ttask.wait(5)\\n\\t\\tdb = true\\n\\tend\\nend)\\n  \\n Here is the Local Script: \\n  local Event = game:GetService(\\"ReplicatedStorage\\"):WaitForChild(\\"SanstaDialogueEvent\\")\\n\\nlocal dialogue1 = true\\nlocal dialogue2 = false\\nlocal dialogue3 = false\\n\\nEvent.OnClientEvent:Connect(function(Player)\\n\\tprint(\\"also works\\")\\n\\t\\tlocal Character = Player.Character\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tlocal PresentsStats = Player:FindFirstChild(\\"PresentsStats\\")\\n\\t\\tlocal Present1 = PresentsStats:FindFirstChild(\