1013	devforum	4180632	"Auto Spacing" instanced parts around a centered point	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4180632	Scripting	Distributing and centering a dynamic number of parts evenly along a line or axis relative to a specific central point.	Define a start and end point relative to the center part's CFrame, then use linear interpolation (Lerp) to position parts at fractional intervals along that line. Using the formula (i - 1) / (total - 1) for the alpha value ensures the parts span the full length, while adjusting the numerator and denominator can provide padding.	t	intermediate	{Vector3,CFrame,Lerp,Instance.new,BasePart}	{}	t	A coding agent could provide a generic 'Distribute' function that takes a reference point, a direction vector, a spacing amount or total width, and a count to return an array of calculated CFrames.	97	1	6	2025-12-24 18:53:23.241	2026-01-08 17:27:26.617522	{"views": 97, "content": " Hello everyone, \\nIm sure theres an elegant solution somewhere that has flew over my head, if so, let me know as well. This is my current problem: \\n \\n \\n This script attempts to spawn instanced parts behind a centered point (part name is Mechanism) \\n \\n \\n I cant seem to either get the math right, or the actual method of doing it correctly. \\n \\n \\n I’ve tried math formulas that could possibly help center more and more parts across a “line” (which is pretty much what I’m replicating), but I couldn’t get it to work. (Check images below!) \\n \\n \\n  image example of what I mean by “centered on a line”  \\n  Current Functioning  \\n  --Testing work with PartControl Module Script\\nPartControl = require(game.ServerScriptService.PartControl)\\nlocal Spawn = script.Parent.SpawnPart\\nlocal Delete = script.Parent.DeletePart\\nlocal Mechanism = script.Parent.MechanismBox\\n\\nlocal DecidingPartSize = Vector3.new(3,3,3)\\nlocal RecentPart = Mechanism\\nlocal IdentificationNumber = 1\\n\\nlocal PartGap = 3\\n\\nSpawn.ClickDetector.MouseClick:Connect(function