1055	devforum	4167845	How would I go about making a procedurally generated map but with tiles?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4167845	Scripting	Implementing a tile-based procedural map generation system that supports distinct biomes and weighted random tile selection.	Use nested for-loops to iterate over a grid (X, Z) and calculate a height or value using math.noise. This value determines the Y-position or type of the tile. Tiles are then instantiated at those coordinates. Note: The provided solution only covers basic grid generation; the biome and weighted random selection questions remain unanswered.	f	intermediate	{math.noise,Instance.new,workspace}	{}	t	An agent can provide a script that layers multiple noise maps (e.g., one for temperature, one for elevation) to define biomes, and use a lookup table to select specific tile models based on the resulting biome and a random weight.	291	21	21	2025-12-20 21:28:39.446	2026-01-08 17:28:56.25406	{"views": 291, "content": " I have been trying to make a procedurally generating map system that uses tiles, but just cant figure out where to start/how to do it. I have scoured countless videos and forum posts but cannot find one that explains it in a way I can understand. I want to incorporate biomes into this system, too, but there is no videos explaining how to make a procedurally generating tile map with biomes. \\n If anyone can help me find a place to start or help with code as I make this system it would be greatly appreciated, thanks! ", "upvotes": 21, "category": "scripting-support", "comments": 21, "created_at": "2025-12-20T21:28:39.446Z"}
