1080	devforum	4232004	How do Roblox animations work?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4232004	Animation	Understanding the technical implementation of Roblox animations, specifically how KeyframeSequences relate to Motor6D.Transform, why Welds are incompatible, and how the Animator blends tracks.	Animations utilize Pose instances to store CFrame data which is applied to the 'Transform' property of Motor6Ds, Bones, or AnimationConstraints. Welds cannot be animated because they lack a Transform property. The Animator calculates the current pose by interpolating between the two nearest keyframes based on TimePosition and then blending multiple tracks using a normalized weighted blend based on priority and weight.	t	intermediate	{Keyframe,KeyframeSequence,Pose,Motor6D,Weld,Animator,AnimationTrack,AnimationConstraint,Bone,CFrame}	{}	t	An agent could automate the programmatic creation of KeyframeSequences and Poses, or generate custom procedural animation scripts that manipulate the Motor6D.Transform property directly.	65	0	3	2026-01-08 18:14:19.498	2026-01-08 17:30:00.689596	{"url": "https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4232004", "title": "How do Roblox animations work?", "views": 65, "source": "devforum", "replies": 3, "analysis": {"solved": true, "problem": "Understanding the technical implementation of Roblox animations, specifically how KeyframeSequences relate to Motor6D.Transform, why Welds are incompatible, and how the Animator blends tracks.", "category": "Animation", "solution": "Animations utilize Pose instances to store CFrame data which is applied to the 'Transform' property of Motor6Ds, Bones, or AnimationConstraints. Welds cannot be animated because they lack a Transform property. The Animator calculates the current pose by interpolating between the two nearest keyframes based on TimePosition and then blending multiple tracks using a normalized weighted blend based on priority and weight.", "difficulty": "intermediate", "automatable": true, "apis_mentioned": ["Keyframe", "KeyframeSequence", "Pose", "Motor6D", "Weld", "Animator", "AnimationTrack", "AnimationConstraint", "Bone", "CFrame"], "error_messages": [], "automation_hint": "An agent could automate the programmatic creation of KeyframeSequences and Poses, or generate custom procedural animation scripts that manipulate the Motor6D.Transform property directly."}, "category": "scripting-support", "source_id": "4232004", "worker_id": "devforum-1", "created_at": "2026-01-08T18:14:19.498Z", "scraped_at": "2026-01-09T01:28:56.186793"}
