1085	devforum	4219212	How do I make Dress To Impress type of clothes?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4219212	3D Modeling	Implementation of a skinned mesh clothing system for custom R15-style rigs that bypasses standard Layered Clothing in favor of bone-weighted meshes.	\N	f	advanced	{Accessory,Attachment,R15,Humanoid}	{}	f	While the 3D rigging must be done in external software like Blender, a coding agent could automate the runtime attachment process by scripting the parenting of meshes to body parts and syncing Transform/Motor6D data for bone-weighted animations.	50	2	1	2026-01-05 19:15:34.978	2026-01-08 17:30:05.616684	{"views": 50, "content": " I’ve been searching for info and I only found 1 topic which kinda answers what I already know and doesn’t go into any details. \\n I already know that DTI clothes are not layered clothes but rather skinned mesh on top of the body base. But what I don’t know is HOW to implement it.  \\nI am aware that the way DTI made their game isn’t a public information, but I hope that there’s people who are more experienced than me and can help me give ideas for solutions.  I do not expect nor do I want an exact same result anyway, as long as it works - I’m happy.  \\n  Bear with me, I’m a beginner modeler and developer, I’m trying to make a dress up game. I have a ton of questions, but what I’m most curious about right now is:  \\n 1 - How do they attach the clothes to the specific body parts? (Also curious if the process is any different if the clothes have bones with physics, eg. long sleeves) \\n2 - Should clothes be counted as an accessory? If so, then that means they need attachments, right? \\n3 - Would this work if I have a single-mesh body and a non-R15 rig? Or would it be better to have the custom R15 package? (The body making and importing is a whole another story that I have a lot of questions about, but this is about everything I wanna find out about yet) \\n4 - Another thing I noticed is that some items replace the body parts, how is that possible? Is the body part it replaces invisible and does the item have its own “skin” parts that displays on top of that? \\n5 - I’m also kind of curious about equipping the clothes to the body and how to script a button to do that (not a touch brick). \\n6 - Also curious about assigning animations/poses to items. Mainly because I wanted to make a separate pose for feet so that the pose alters between heels and flat shoes or bare feet without replacing the feet entirely. Would it cause a lot of problems for the animations (Even if I make other non-shoes animations/poses without the feet key frames)? \\n This is my first post so I apologize if this i", "upvotes": 2, "category": "building-support", "comments": 1, "created_at": "2026-01-05T19:15:34.978Z"}
1086	devforum	4151404	Adaptive Animations BREAKS R6 rigs entirely when enabled │ End of R6?	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4151404	Animation	Enabling the 'Adaptive Animations' beta feature disables torso rotation and movement for R6 rigs, rendering existing R6 animations non-functional.	\N	f	intermediate	{"Adaptive Animations"}	{}	f	As this is an engine-level bug within a Studio Beta feature, it requires a patch from Roblox engineers rather than a scripting workaround. A coding agent could only assist by identifying R6 rigs in a workspace and notifying the developer to disable the beta feature.	244	10	2	2025-12-14 11:54:34.925	2026-01-08 17:30:10.285942	{"views": 244, "content": " Today, I enabled the Studio Beta “Adaptive Animations” feature, more on the topic of this feature can be found here: \\n  Adaptive Animations  \\n I typically enable all beta features as soon as they come out to get an early feel with them before they’re fully released. However, this one is the most dangerous as enabling it removes all access to rotate and move an R6 rig’s torso completely as seen below,  where an R6 cannot have its torso moved on the main roblox animation engine VS. an R15 rig which can:  \\n  \\n     \\n Now we know Roblox is slowly and secretly trying to move away from R6 by slowly limiting it more and more but if this issue remains, and the feature rolls out fully for all games,  then ALL R6 GAMES will have non-functioning torso movement on all their R6 animations.  \\n As of right now I am forced to disable it, hoping it gets fixed by the time it gets fully rolled out, otherwise my game which supports both R6 and R15 along with other games that include R6 will be forced to reanimate their entire game with a new rig system, effectively destroying the platform as a whole. \\n Now I might be overreacting and I don’t post here much but I never seen something so “possibly threatening” to R6 before. ", "upvotes": 10, "category": "building-support", "comments": 2, "created_at": "2025-12-14T11:54:34.925Z"}
1087	devforum	4210091	How to achieve a gradient glow effect on a limb	https://devforum.roblox.com/t/4210091	UI	Achieving a smooth, rounded gradient glow effect on character limbs without visible sharp edges or blocky corner artifacts from SurfaceGuis.	Use a SurfaceGui with LightInfluence set to 0 to ensure consistent brightness, or potentially use the ForceField material for a native glow effect.	f	intermediate	{SurfaceGui,UIGradient,MeshPart,LightInfluence,ForceField}	{}	t	A script can be used to automatically clone a limb, apply SurfaceGuis to all visible faces, and configure UIGradient properties to ensure seamless transitions.	134	0	4	2026-01-02 22:55:49.443	2026-01-08 17:30:11.597744	{"views": 134, "content": "          image  281×326 49.2 KB         \\n         image  824×724 82.9 KB         \\n \\n  What do you want to achieve?  Keep it simple and clear! \\nA glow effect like the one in the picture. \\n  What is the issue?  Include screenshots / videos if possible! \\nTrying myself with screenguis, the edges make this sharp boundary. \\n  What solutions have you tried so far?  Did you look for solutions on the Creator Hub? \\nI make a clone of the limb, weld it to the limb, and apply screenguis on all sides except for the top, then I add frames with uigradients to all of them. \\n \\n In the first picture, if you look closely, you can see how there is a rounded boundary for the glow effect. In my version however, the sharp edges of the frames are visible. Thank you in advance! ", "upvotes": 0, "category": "building-support", "comments": 4, "created_at": "2026-01-02T22:55:49.443Z"}
